<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<bible xml:lang="bko" backtTranslaltionDefaultLanguage="en" oxes="2.0">
  <book id="REV" stage="Rev" version="A">
    <Annotation class="History">
      <Message author="JSW" created="2009-10-02 04:10:06Z" when="2009-10-02 04:10:06Z" stage="Draft">drafted by Max Jacob, 15 May 2002. Reference: The Contemporary Parallel New Testament, Eight Translation, especially: New Century Version, New American Standard Bible, Contemporary English Version, New International Version and New Living Translation.Corrected 16-20 May 2002. Second revision by Max Jacob, Mus Zacharias and June Jacob, 3-10 February 2003.Mus was using A Handbook on the Revelation to John by Robert G Bratcher and Howaed A Hatton (UBS Handbook Series) to make his Draft. We then make the revision (Max second KML-WhyB.db and Mus' draft). The result was Kml-WhyB.db, which is now send to you. We also use Da Jesus Book (Hawaii Creole) and Ambon Back translation of Revelation in this work. 3 - 13 March 2003, Max, Mus, Barbara did revisions in Kupang (exegetical check). Many of the section headers are based on NASB. 29 Apr - 2 May Consutant check with Kathy Taber at Gereja Paulus Kupang. Advisor: Barbara Translators: June, Mus. UNS: Roni Dionisius Sir (pemuda ll); Rafael Subang (pemuda ll); Ibu Louisa Bais-Solsepa; Sept 2005 Chuck with team fixed some exegetical oversights (marked with **) ; final read thru for NT by Chuck, Adriana, Barbara;</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-02-24 11:58:12Z" when="2014-02-24 11:58:12Z" stage="Consult">Consultant Check: 29 April - 2 May 2003 at Gereja Paulus in Kupang; Consultant: Kathy Taber, approved. Report: Kupang Malay Rev consultant report.doc; Adjustments to REV-May 2009.doc.</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-23 03:07:17Z" when="2015-01-23 03:07:17Z" stage="Rev">Smoothing read thru for Kupang mini-Bible with Chuck, Lena, Rina, Oma at UBB. BackTrans also adjusted.</Message>
    </Annotation>
    <p class="Header" usfm="h">Dunya Model Baru<bt>Dunya Model Baru</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">Yohanis pung tulisan so'al apa yang nanti jadi<bt>Yohanis' writing about what will happen</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">di hari kiamat sampe ada<bt>at the end of the world until there is</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Main" usfm="mt">Dunya Model Baru<bt>a New Model World</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***CHANGE in title"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">***CHANGE in title</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="1" />
      <v n="1-2" />Salam dari beta, Yohanis, andia Yesus Kristus pung orang suru-suru.<bt>Greetings from me, Yohanis, Yesus Kristus' servant.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Di ini tulisan, beta tulis so'al apa yang nanti jadi. Beta dapa tau ini hal dong bagini: Tuhan Allah sandiri yang buka kasi tau memang sang Yesus Kristus. Ju Tuhan Allah suru sang Yesus ko kasi tau Tuhan pung orang suru-suru dong. Ais Yesus suru dia pung ana bua satu dari sorga, ko pi buka kasi lia ini hal samua sang beta, ko biar beta tulis memang. Te sonde lama lai, ini hal dong samua pasti jadi. Jadi bosong musti dengar bae-bae Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata yang Yesus su kasi tau ni.<bt>In this writing, I write about what is going to happen. I got to know these things like this: God himself is the one who revealed them in.advance to Yesus Kristus. And God ordered Yesus to tell the Lord's servants. Then Yesus ordered one of his underlings from heaven (*angels) to reveal show all these things to me, so that I write them in.advance. Cuz (elaboration) much not longer, all these things will surely have happened. So (consequently), you-pl must listen carefully/carefully to God's Words which Yesus has told here. [DISCOURSE (book-level): Gk is distant 3rd person “to his servants”, “to his servant John”, and in vs.3 “the ones who read/whoever reads”. In the Timor region, this comes across as for and about someone else, completely removed from and not relevant to the readers of the letter. The last sentence above makes explicit that this message from Jesus is for the readers of John's letter (see also Ex. Summ. #1 re: “to his servants”).] [NOTE to daughter translations: discuss this with the team when working on it. If they feel the readers can get from vs.3, then This may not be needed in your language. This is not an issue for the consultant to decide on the fly with the UNS's.] [EXEG: recurring phrase in Rev. “the testimony of Jesus”. 1:2; 1:9; 12:11; 12:17; 19:10; 20:4. Much discussion (and disagreement) in the commentaries.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note on “testimony of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** (2009) note on “testimony of Jesus” added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apokálypsis: revealing, let someone know things"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">apokálypsis: revealing, let someone know things that had been hidden but were now to be made known to the right people. More like declassifying information than like letting the cat out of the bag or leaking a story eseémanen: make known by means of signs, foretell, make explicit<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>send ... make clear: Jesus wen send his angel messenja guy [from da sky] fo tell me, John, [all dis stuff,] cuz I one a his worka guys. Dass how he wen make clear all dat stuff. Let somebody know, make um know, make um clear fo dem Follow NIV for format with quotation levels; also Acts 28:25.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Samua orang yang baca ini tulisan sampe orang bisa dengar, na, dong paling ontong. Deng orang yang dengar dia pung isi deng bekin iko dia pung pasán, dong ju ontong. Te dia pung waktu su deka-deka datang na!<bt>Everyone/all people who read this writing to the point that (other) people can hear/listen, na, they are most fortunate. And the people who hear its contents and follow/obey/do according to its message/advice/instructions, they are also fortunate. Cuz (elaboration) its time, is very near [+obviously]. [EXEG: KT: blessed from Gk /makarios/ -- ontong ‘fortunate’, not kasi berkat (which can skew it to giving material blessings. Avoid TB ‘happy’ as that is not really a meaning element of the Gk word.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="makários: fortunate, rather than &quot;happy&quot;. See"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">makários: fortunate, rather than "happy". See the Beatitudes anaginoóskoon: the focus is on reading the letter publicly in church on the one hand, and on hearing it read in public -- more than an individual reading it privately. In any case, this part hasn't happened as of the time he was writing; it's only potential readers and hearers. It's not just the predictions; it's the prophetic revelation of what Jesus is like.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te Tuhan Allah su janji, bilang,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Te Tuhan Allah su janji, bilang, nanti Dia kasi berkat sang samua orang yang baca ini tulisan, ko dengar dia pung isi, deng bekin iko Dia pung pasán. Te dia pung waktu, su mau abis na.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yohanis kirim salam kasi tuju jama'at di propinsi Asia<bt>Yohanis sends greeting to the seven congregations in Asia province</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Salam dari beta kasi Tuhan pung tuju jama'at di propinsi Asia.<bt>Greetings from me to the Lord's seven congregations in Asia province. [NOTE to daughter translations: Repeated greeting in vs.1 and vs.4. vs. 4 in Gk text. vs.1 for local RL conventions, opening the whole letter to the broader audience. vs. 4 narrowed to greet 7 churches.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Beta minta ko Tuhan Allah kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae ko bosong bisa idop aman, dame, deng tanáng. Te Tuhan Allah su ada memang dari dolu-kala. Dia ada sakarang, deng nanti Dia ada tarús sampe salamanya. Beta ju minta ko Dia pung Roh kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae ko bosong bisa idop aman, dame, deng tanáng. Beta lia Dia pung Roh tu, sama ke ada tuju roh yang mangada Tuhan Allah pung korsi parenta.<bt>I request that God show His goodness/grace/ kindness/generosity so that you-pl can live in safety/security (external peace), restored relationships (relational peace), and calm (inner peace) [EXEG: 3 senses of Gk /eirene/]. Cuz (elaboration) God has been from long ago. He is now, and later He will be forever. I also request that His Spirit show His goodness/grace/ kindness/generosity so that you-pl can live in safety/security (external peace), restored relationships (relational peace), and calm (inner peace). I saw His Spirit, like there were seven spirits who face God's ruling chair. [NOTE to daughter translations: Use standard epistle greeting formula for “Grace to you and peace from...”] [EXEG: 7 spirits -- 1) Holy Spirit "symbolism of a sevenfold or complete manifestation of his being", from LXX rendering of Is. 11:2; Ramsey says "a symbolic or allegorical way of expressing the full range of exercise of the Divine power in the seven churches,”; favoured by Hughes, TH M.Crofts, and NLT, but problematic for Rev. 3:1, 4:6 &amp; 5:6 which could be seen as requiring 7 individual entities (in 5:6 going to different locations); 2) the seven archangels of Jewish tradition; favoured by IVP commentary; 3) seven spirits (or angels) of some sort, favoured by all English translations except NLT and Mounce "it would seem that “the seven spirits before [God’s] throne” are best understood as part of a heavenly entourage that has a special ministry in connection with the Lamb."; TH advises "The translation of the phrase in this verse must be quite literal; as with all other symbolic figures and events in this writing,"; Mounce says "the seven spirits of God are enigmatic at best."; challenge is 1) reporting faithfully what John says he saw in his vision, and 2) what does it mean, without insisting that it makes good sense in a book that is full of mind-blowing and far out things.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Trans handbook God who now lives;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Trans handbook God who now lives; Tran handbook and Hughes 7 spirits = Holy Spirit [sambyang sang Dia pung Roh yang Barisi, yang ada sama ke 7 roh di muka Dia pung korsi parenta.] ***DISCUSS -- this rendering should match 3:1, 4:5-6, 5:6 ; M. Crofts suggestion: I am the one who commands/hold the Holy Spirit that is like the seven spirits. ***CHECK out EXEG carefully [Beta yang ada Tuhan Allah pung Roh yang ada pung tuju sisi. // Tuhan Allah pung Roh ada di Beta. Deng itu Roh ada tuju sisi.]</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Beta ju minta berkat deng dame"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Beta ju minta berkat deng dame dari Tuhan Allah pung Roh yang Barisi. Beta lia itu Roh Barisi tu, sama ke ada tuju roh yang mangada Tuhan Allah pung korsi parenta.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="cháris: acting graciously erchómenos: continued activity"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">cháris: acting graciously erchómenos: continued activity on behalf of his people, not just living forever<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>heptà: seven was strongly associated with the idea of completeness. It could be used of the Holy Spirit in all his completeness, all aspects of his being pneumátoon: probably a picturesque way to speak of the Holy Spirit, also used in the Old Testament. Not obake or local spirits or evil spirits or what survives after a person dies or a life force that inhabits people and animals and plants or an angel, or an embodiment of mana (check all of them, and make notes for the consultant)<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>eireénee: general well-being, more than just absence of conflict. Like Hebrew "shalom"</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:4" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani di sini tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;7 roh yang mangada sang Tuhan pung korsi parenta&gt;&gt;. Iko orang yang pintar so'al Alkitab dong, nomer 7 pung arti, andia hal yang cukup, yang langkáp, deng yang sampurna. Andia ko orang ahli saparu bilang, di sini itu 7 roh pung arti bilang, Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi. Deng bagitu, di ayat 4-5 ni, Yohanis ada omong berkat dari 1) Tuhan Allah, dari 2) Dia pung Roh, deng dari 3) Yesus Kristus.<bt>The Yunani language writings here write saying, “7 spirits who face God2's throne”. According to Biblical experts (people who are knowledgable/clever about the Bible, the meaning of number 7 is things that are enough, that are complete, and that are whole. That is why some experts say that here the meaning of those 7 spirits is God2's *Holy Spirit. In that way, in verses 4-5 here, Yohanis is speaking blessing from 1) Lord God, from 2) His Spirit, and from 3) Yesus Kristus.</bt></note><note reference="1:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 3:14, Dunya Model Baru 4:5</note><v n="5" />Beta ju minta ko Yesus Kristus kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae ko bosong bisa idop aman, dame, deng tanáng. Dia salalu omong tarús-taráng so'al apa yang Tuhan Allah kasi tau sang Dia. Dolu Dia mati batúl, ma Tuhan kasi idop kambali sang Dia, ko biar Dia jadi orang partama yang idop kambali dari mati. Dia ju jadi Kapala yang ator samua raja di dunya.<bt>I also request that Yesus Kristus show His goodness/grace/ kindness/generosity so that you-pl can live in safety/security (external peace), restored relationships (relational peace), and calm (inner peace). He always speaks forthrightly about that which God told Him. Previously He really/truly died, but God made Him live again, so that He would become the first person who lives again from death. He is the Head who has oversight over all rajas in the world. [NOTE to daughter translations: Gk term is ambiguous (see notes), and its ambiguities are mirrored by the Kupang. Make sure your rendering skews in the right direction.] [EXEG: Gk here is /archwn/ not /kurios/, so don't force your standard term for ‘lord’ if it doesn't fit here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) deleted /nanti/ in last"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** (2009) deleted /nanti/ in last sentence</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="prootótokos: has a triple sense of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">prootótokos: has a triple sense of "firstborn" and "superior to everything else in its class", as in Colossians 1:15 and "existing before something else"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Tagal Yesus sayang sang kotong, andia ko Dia kasi tumpa Dia pung dara kasi sang kotong. Deng Dia pung mati tu, Dia buka jalan ko kasi lapás sang kotong dari kotong pung sala pung kuasa.<bt>Because Yesus loves us-inc, that's why He shed/spilled His blood (for a high moral cause) for us. With/by that death of his, He opened the way to free/release us from the power/authority of our wrongs. [EXEG: combination of “freed ... by shedding his blood” should evoke the /tumpa dara/ vocabulary which implies dying for a high moral cause.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tagal Yesus sayang sang kotong, andia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Tagal Yesus sayang sang kotong, andia ko Dia pung dara malele sampe Dia mati. Deng Dia pung mati tu, Dia buka jalan ko kasi salamat sang kotong dari kotong pung sala-sala dong.</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 55:4, Lagu Puji dong 89:27</note><v n="6" />Ais Dia angka sang kotong jadi Dia pung rakyat, ko biar kotong karjá kasi Dia pung Bapa, Tuhan Allah. Yesus Kristus memang hebat, deng Dia pung kuasa sonde abis-abis. Itu batúl!<bt>Then He raised us up to become His citizens, so that we would work for His Father God. Yesus Kristus is truly amazing, and His power lasts for forever. That's true! [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hieréis: was one pries guy dat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">hieréis: was one pries guy dat wen say "prieses". "All" may be needed to keep the plural from being understood as "us apostles" or something restrictive; having everybody in the kingdom be a priest is a shocking idea for both Jews and Greeks</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 19:6, Dunya Model Baru 5:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Jadi buka mata ko lia bae-bae! Sakarang Yesus deng Dia pung Bapa ada di sorga. Ma sonde lama lai, te Dia turun datang dalam awan. Samua orang di dunya nanti dapa lia sang Dia. Bagitu ju deng itu orang dong yang dolu tikam sang Dia. Nanti samua suku-bangsa di ini dunya manyasal deng manangis makarereu tagal dong kanál sang Dia. Ini samua memang pasti jadi. Batúl bagitu.<bt>So (consequently), open your eyes to see well! Now Yesus and His Father are in heaven. But not much longer, cuz (elaboration) He will come down in cloud. All people on the world will be able to see Him. Like that also (=including) the people who previously pierced/speared Him. Later all nations in this world will regret and cry loudly because they know/recognise Him then. This all will truly happen. It's true like that. [EXEG: “because of Him” should be something that evokes/reflects His Christness, death, resurrection, Saviour, King, not merely “because they see Him (physically)”. CEV takes “pierced” in an unsupportable direction.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="idoù: starts quotations from Deuteronomy and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">idoù: starts quotations from Deuteronomy and Zechariah. The double "look!" fits the context more dramatically than a single "try look!", which is actually fairly low key and might be used mainly by kids who are wowed by rather simple things érkhetai: implicitly, coming back as Judge, which is what causes all the consternation<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>nephelóon: not like an airplane letting down through a cloud layer for a landing, flaps extended, but with clouds as a beautiful part of the stage setting, an embellishment of his grand entry, as in the medieval paintings páas ophthalmòs: part for the whole, but no reason for not carrying it through in company with a verb<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>exekéntesan: Roman swords were used for both slashing and thrusting, but the spear was used exclusively for penetration. Spears fit better with the crucifixion story as well, without being anachronistic. I guess we don't have Opukaha`ia's biography, but I seem to remember that he narrowly escaped death from either a spear thrust or a javelin throw, which is what his name ("slit belly" from kaha 'slice lengthwise') refers to: Gavan Daws in The Shoal of Time under "Arts of War" mentions spears (for thrusting), javelins (for throwing), and daggers (for stabbing). There was nothing corresponding to a sword; clubs were used instead kópsontai (koptomai): ritualized expression of grief in mourning, such as one sees today in the Palestinian funerals that are shown on TV, with loud outcries and throwing one's body around. People do feel genuinely bad when they do this, and that is the socially accepted way to express how they feel. It's not just weeping quietly or grieving, it's noisy and embarrassing to Westerners. I saw it close at hand in Spain with a North African woman picked up for smuggling drugs. Some commentators think the motivation is a sudden realization of the awful things they have done. Others think people are scared spitless by having the Judge show up when they aren't ready to deal with him, and they know they don't have a chance of getting acquitted. Since the word is most associated with genuine grief, I'd pick remorse -- even if it's too late<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="1:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 7:13, Mateos 24:30, Markus 13:26, Lukas 21:27, 1 Tesalonika 4:17, Sakaria 12:10, Yohanis 19:34, 37</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Tuhan Allah bilang,<bt>God says,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Beta ni,<bt>“I am</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Alfa sampe Omega.<bt>Alpha until Omega.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Beta ni,<bt>I am</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">A sampe Z.<bt>A until Z.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Samua asal dari Beta,<bt>Everything originates from Me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">mulai dari partama sampe abis.<bt>beginning from the first/start until the end.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Beta yang su ada memang dari dolu.<bt>I am the one who has truly been from long ago.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Beta yang ada sakarang.<bt>I am the one who is now.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Deng Beta yang nanti ada tarús sampe salamanya.<bt>And I am the one who later will be continually forever.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te Beta sandiri sa yang paling kuasa!&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) only I alone am the one who is most powerful!” [NOTE to daughter translations: Needs a connector, but /te/ is probably too strong. If you have an /and2/ try that.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eimi: it's only the A to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">eimi: it's only the A to Z that's in first person inside the quotation; the rest is third person and presumably represents John's words, which he repeats later in the book kýrios ho theós: a marked construction<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="1:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 22:13, Kaluar dari Masir 3:14</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yohanis dapa lia Manusia Tulen<bt>Yohanis sees the Ideal/Original Human (*Son of Man)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Tagal kotong samua parcaya sama-sama bilang, Yesus tu, kotong pung Raja, andia ko beta su jadi bosong pung sodara. Ada orang laen yang mara, tagal kotong iko sang Yesus, ais dong bekin sangsara sang kotong samua. Ma Yesus su kasi kuat kotong pung hati, ko biar kotong bisa batahan tarús-tarús. Tagal beta su kasi tau orang so'al Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata, deng ajar so'al Yesus, ada orang yang kabaratan. Andia ko sakarang dong su tangkap deng buang sang beta di ini pulo, yang dia pung nama Patmos.<bt>Because we-inc all believe together that that Yesus, is our Raja, that's why I have become your(p) sibling. There are other people who are angry, because we follow Yesus, so they cause all of us-inc to suffer. But Yesus has strengthened/encouraged our livers, so that we can endure continually. Because I told about God's Words, and taught about Yesus, there were people who objected/had problems with that. That's why now they have captured/arrested and thrown me to this island, whose name is Patmos. [EXEG: recurring phrase in Rev. “the testimony of Jesus”. 1:2; 1:9; 12:11; 12:17; 19:10; 20:4. Much discussion (and disagreement) in the commentaries.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="egenómeen: may imply that he wasn't"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">egenómeen: may imply that he wasn't on Patmos any more when he sent out the letter pátmooi: Patmos Island is about 10 miles long and 6 miles wide, almost exactly the size of Kaho`olawe. It has a small harbor, and is about as far southwest of Ephesus as Kaua`i is from O`ahu (62 miles). It was used by the Romans as a penal colony or concentration camp. It may be that John was on a prison island there because he wouldn't stop preaching, or he could have been a pastor there with the job of preaching. They show tourists a cave he is supposed to have lived in<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>martyrían Ieesóu: the testimony Jesus presented, as in Verse 2 en Ieesóu: most likely goes with "trouble" and "kingdom" and "endurance", not just the last one<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Ais satu kali, pas deng hari sambayang, beta takaná Tuhan Allah pung Roh. Takuju sa, ju beta dengar ada suara karás yang batarea di beta pung balakang. Dia pung bunyi sama ke tarompet.<bt>Then one time, exactly on the worship day, I was affected by God's Spirit. Unexpectedly, I heard a loud voice that shouted from behind me. It's/His sound was like a trumpet.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bahasa daerah can use to'is (ram's"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">bahasa daerah can use to'is (ram's horn) or kulit siput AM kulit bia ; TA pung Roh ada bagarak di beta pung hati / ada kuasa sang beta ; karja di beta pung hati ; turun sang beta* ***CHECK with team; M.Crofts tweek trompet = ram's horn OT, musical instrument NT<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kyriakéei heeméraai: the earliest Christian designation"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">kyriakéei heeméraai: the earliest Christian designation for Sunday: the day for the Lord</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais satu kali, pas deng hari"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Ais satu kali, pas deng hari sambayang, beta takaná Tuhan Allah pung Roh.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Itu suara suru sang beta bilang, &lt;&lt;Yohanis! Beta mau buka kasi lia satu hal sang lu. Samua yang lu lia ni, lu musti tulis. Ais itu, lu musti kirim pi tuju jama'at, andia jama'at di kota Efesus, kota Smirna, kota Pergamus, kota Tiatira, kota Sardis, kota Filadelfia, deng kota Laodikia.&gt;&gt;<bt>That voice ordered me saying, “Yohanis! I want to show you something. All that you see here, you must write. After that, you must send to seven congregations, that is the congregations in Efesus, Smirna, Pergamus, Tiatira, Sardis, Filadelfia, and Laodikia.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Dengar bagitu, ju beta bale balakang ko mau lia sapa yang omong tu. Ma beta dapa lia lampu te'oek tuju biji yang ada tadudu di atas tampa taro lampu yang bekin dari mas.<bt>Hearing like that, then I turned around to see who was speaking. But I saw seven wick lanterns that were sitting on top of a lamp place/stand that was made of gold.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lychnías: lamp holders, poles with lamps"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">lychnías: lamp holders, poles with lamps on top. They might have been made from wood or iron for strength and covered with gold leaf for beauty. Probably not solid gold; they would have weighed tons. The lamps were shallow clay bowls full of olive oil, with a wick lying partly in the oil, the other end burning. One lampstand might have had several oil lamps on it, but 2:5 makes it sound like there was one lampstand for each church, and possibly just one oil lamp per lampstand</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Deng ada satu Orang badiri di itu lampu dong pung teng-tenga. Dia pung rupa sama ke Manusia Tulen. Dia ada pake satu baju panjang sampe di Dia pung kaki, deng salempang satu salimut mas di Dia pung dada.<bt>And there was a Person standing in the middle of those lamps. His appearance/face was like the Ideal Human (*Son of Man). He was wearing a long dress/robe down to His feet, and he wore a golden shoulder sash on his chest.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="salempang - sash"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">salempang - sash</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hómoion hyiòn anthroópou: no article, at"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">hómoion hyiòn anthroópou: no article, at this point not to be identified with Daniel's "Son of Man" figure or Christ, but just "something with a human form" periezoosménon pròs tóis mastóis: not a belt, but either one strip crossing the chest from shoulder to waist, or two strips crossing each other in the middle of the chest. Not an Empress waistline that would make him look like he was in drag. Some commentators suggest it was the way the High Priest dressed, but he had more on his chest than a zooneé<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="1:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 7:13, 10:5</note><v n="14" />Dia pung rambu, puti barisi sama ke kapas.<bt>His hair, was clean white like cotton.</bt><note reference="1:14" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia pung kapala deng Dia pung rambu puti sama ke domba pung bulu puti, deng puti ke salju.&gt;&gt; Dua-dua kasi gambar satu barang yang puti barisi batúl.<bt>The Yunani language writings write saying, “His head and His hair were white like the white fur/wool of sheep, and white like snow (Indo loan, not known except through media).” Both of them give a picture of something that is pure white.</bt></note>Dia pung mata, manyala sama ke api.<bt>His eyes, flashed like fire.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(al) sama ke api manyala ?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">(al) sama ke api manyala ?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="leukaì: what does white symbolize locally?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">leukaì: what does white symbolize locally? In the Bible, it is usually purity, or here it may suggest the wisdom of great age phlòx pyròs: blazing like fire (Daniel 10:6), generally understood to symbolize fierce opposition to enemies. What is the symbolism? burning, intense -- how did Kamehameha I look when he was chasing the O`ahu army up Nu`uanu Valley? ["mean look" DM] Not the evil eye, and not stink eye. But you know he's not going to put up with any opposition or any nonsense. [Literally (in footnote?) "Da eye, jalike da fire!"]<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="1:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 7:9</note><v n="15" />Dia pung kaki, mera manyala sama ke tambaga yang orang bakar dalam api. Dia pung suara, bésar sama ke aer tarjún.<bt>His feet, were shiny red like copper that people burn/bake in the fire. His voice, was loud like a water fall. [NOTE to daughter translations: if they think waterfalls merely tinkle, try “His voice was roaring like large waves breaking (in the west monsoon).” NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="chalkolibánooi: some mixed metal or alloy"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">chalkolibánooi: some mixed metal or alloy like bronze or brass. The exact mix is not known. pepyrooménees: heated, so could be glowing red or white like lava. The heating was done to get rid of the junk. It's not the polished metal after refining (that idea must come from "burnished" in the old translations, not supported by the text no matter what UBS says), but the glowing hot metal during refining (present participle, not aorist)<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="1:14-15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 10:6; Yeskial 1:24, 43:2</note><v n="16" />Di Dia pung tangan kanan, Dia ada pegang bintang tuju biji. Dari Dia pung mulu, ada kaluar satu kalewang mata dua yang tajam. Dia pung muka, bacaya taráng sama ke matahari waktu siang.<bt>In His right hand, He was holding seven stars. From His mouth, there was coming out a double edged fighting sword that was sharp. His face, shone brightly like the sun at noon. [NOTE to daughter translations: CHECK carefully that this is not a blade with two-branches, but a single blade with two sharp edges.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rhomphaía: UBS has the blade of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">rhomphaía: UBS has the blade of a sword (not the handle) extending forward out of his mouth. Either way it boggles the imagination, so here is not a good place to explain anything. It's identifying the symbols, not the description, that's probably important</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Waktu beta dapa lia itu Orang, ju beta jato memang sama ke orang samaput, di muka Dia pung kaki. Ma Dia sonto sang beta deng Dia pung tangan kanan, ais Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ana, é! Jang taku! Te samua-samua asal dari Beta, mulai dari partama sampe abis.<bt>When I saw that Person, then I fell right away like a person who had fainted, before His feet. But He touched me with His right hand, then He spoke saying, “Child, é! Don't be afraid! Cuz (elaboration) everything originates from Me, beginning the first/start until the end. [NOTE to daughter translations: if /samaput/ causes difficulty just say /jato memang di muka Dia pung kaki./]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="próotos: just like A to Z"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">próotos: just like A to Z in Verse 8. The symbols or icons established here get repeated again and again through the book, and they are supposed to be identifiable as the same symbol each time</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 44:6, 48:12, Dunya Model Baru 2:8, 22:13</note><v n="18" />Dolu Beta mati, ma sakarang lu lia dolo! Beta su idop kambali, deng nanti Beta idop tarús sampe salamanya. Deng Beta yang pegang konci yang bisa buka tampa orang mati, ko kasi idop kambali sang dong.<bt>Previously I died, but now you(sg) just look! I live again, and later I will live continually forever. And I am the one who holds the key which can open the place of the dead people in order to make them live again.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***changed last sentence “to (purpose)” --"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">***changed last sentence “to (purpose)” -- “which can (function)” to avoid impression he will do this for everybody.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="idóu: attention getter for the important"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">idóu: attention getter for the important thing that comes next. Pidgin does a lot of this kléis: this is one of the icons that runs throughout the book<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>haaidou: abode of the dead, Hell</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tampa orang mati pung jiwa //"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">tampa orang mati pung jiwa // Deng Beta yang pegang konci ko buka tampa orang mati, ko kasi idop kambali sang dong.</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Lu musti tulis ame samua yang lu lia sakarang ni, deng tulis samua yang nanti jadi.<bt>You must write all which you see now, and write all that will happen later.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="méllei: scheduled by God's authority, inevitable,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">méllei: scheduled by God's authority, inevitable, destined</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Beta kasi tau dolo dia pung arti bagini: itu tuju lampu mas pung arti, andia tuju jama'at. Deng itu tuju bintang yang lu dapa lia di Beta pung tangan kanan ni, andia tuju ana bua dari sorga yang bawa kabar dari Tuhan kasi itu tuju jama'at dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>I will tell first the meaning like this: those seven golden lamps' meaning, is seven congregations. And those seven stars which you saw in My right hand there, they are seven underlings from heaven/angels who bring news from God to those seven congregations.” [NOTE to daughter translations: See note on Gk below, and Ex.Summ. for range of ideas re: these “angel/messengers”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ánggeloi: messengers. People have interpreted them"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">ánggeloi: messengers. People have interpreted them as pastors or representatives of the churches, or guardian angels, or the heavenly guardian or representative of each church. The latter matches an obscure concept found in Daniel 10:13, 20 and 12:1, Matthew 18:10, and Acts 12:15. All the other uses of "anggelos" in Revelation are supernatural beings, so it is probably best not to have these be human preachers. They are involved at a higher level, and there is no warning in the next chapters about them being snatched away if the people don't shape up</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kirim pasán kasi jama'at di Efesus<bt>The Lord Yesus sends instructions to the congregation at Efesus [NOTE to daughter translations: if /pasán/ causes difficulties in the headers for chapters 2-3, just say /TY pung surat kasi.../]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="2" />
      <v n="1" />Ais itu, Manusia Tulen parenta sang beta bilang, &lt;&lt;Yohanis. Lu musti tulis surat satu. Dia pung bunyi bagini:<bt>After that, the Ideal/Original Human (*Son of Man) commanded me saying, “Yohanis, you must write a letter, it's sound is like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Buat jama'at di kota Efesus:<bt>&lt;To the congregation at Efesus city: [EXEG: “angel” is taken as referring to the churches themselves. See Ex. Summ. choice #2; ditto for all 7 letters. See Ex.Summ. and Hughes for wide disagreement on what this could mean.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ini surat ni, dari Beta, andia Yesus. Beta yang pegang tuju bintang di Beta pung tangan kanan. Beta ju yang bajalan kuliling ko lia satu-satu itu tuju lampu mas. Dengar Beta pung omong ni.<bt>This letter here, is from Me, that is Yesus. I hold seven stars in My right hand. I also walk around to see each of those seven gold lamps. Listen to this speaking of Mine. [EXEG: in this region it is more natural for ‘lamps’ (whole) to represent the ‘lampstand’ (part). Otherwise the heavy information load would skew the focus.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="All the &quot;Da One dat ...&quot;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">All the "Da One dat ..." passages in chapters 2 and 3 take "m2" as standard format marker. All the quoted messages that follow them, and their internal breaks, take "m3". Fiesta resets these to "m"; they should be set back before publication. angel: We have interpreted this as an angel, as most commentaries and translations. The criticisms are not applicable to an angel, but to the church. As the messenger, he is to announce these things to them. In Pidgin, we cannot use the singular 'you' to apply to a church; it must be the plural.<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>grápson: UBS recommends starting each section with a quotation margin, but to not give him any attributes in the margin -- they get in the way of the attributes that are given inside the message, which should constitute an adequate identification. Frank has felt that "da Guy" is needed, but that doesn't get in the way peripatóon: walking around, as if tending the flames of the lamps, taking care of the churches<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>lychnióon: oil lamps with wicks extending out over the side. Should not sound like street lights or floor lamps -- anything with a light bulb in it</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="2" />Beta su lia bosong pung idop di kota Efesus bilang, bosong salalu karjá banting tulang kasi sang Tuhan. Kalo ada orang jahat di bosong pung teng-tenga, bosong sonde kasi loos sang dia. Kalo orang datang pakane'o bilang, dia tu, Tuhan pung utusan, bosong salalu pareksa bae-bae dia pung idop, ko dapa tau bilang, orang macam bagitu tu, manusia putar-balek, ko sonde. Ais bosong tola, ko jang dengar sang dia.<bt>I have seen your lives in Efesus city, that you-pl always work yourselves to the bone for the Lord. If there is an evil person in your midsts, you don't give him any opportunity/space. If a person come twisting/lying, saying that he is God's commissioned person (*apostle), you always examine his life carefully, in order to know if/whether a person like that is a liar, or not. Then you reject [him], so that you don't listen to/obey him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sou: everything in the next two"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">sou: everything in the next two chapters is addressed to individuals, not groups. It's the person responsible for the church, not the rank and file of the church, although most of the admonishments have to do with the "messenger"'s responsibility to the rank and file. Commentators equate "messenger" to the pastor, or some representative of the church, or the church's guardian angel (the majority). The only exegetical position that implies plural takes the "angel" to be the presbyters collectively, but there is no support for this in the text. kópon: their persistent and painful struggles to maintain their Christian profession. Should be interpretable as just working hard for a living<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>dyneei: "can" doesn't fit, because it implies you might or might not apostólous: doesn't say who sent them. With Paul it's usually Jesus Christ, but false apostles might be claiming a wider base. Tossup.<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>héures: you found out what they were as a result of testing them</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Biar orang bekin susa sang bosong tagal bosong parcaya sang Beta, ma bosong batahan tarús, sonde tau mondor.<bt>Even if people cause difficulty to you because you believe in Me, but you endure on, without any reversing.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ebástasas: implies that there is an"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">ebástasas: implies that there is an aggravation or unpleasant experience, usually caused by somebody else, that you have put up with</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="4" />Ma Beta lia, bosong ada jato di satu hal. Tagal, dolu waktu bosong baru parcaya sang Beta, bosong basayang satu deng satu. Ma sakarang bosong su sonde bagitu lai.<bt>But I see, you are falling/lacking in one matter. Because, previously when you first believed in Me, you always loved each other. But now you are no longer like that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="proóteen: formerly, earlier = próteron; could"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">proóteen: formerly, earlier = próteron; could also be initial in an ordinal series, but doesn't have to be -- first, when you first believed in me, at the beginning of your Christian life. Despite inspiring talks on the enthusiasm of early love, he's probably saying that things aren't going as well as they were before, without strong emphasis on the starting moment proóteen: Pidgin does use "like" as a conjunction, and it is not ambiguous with the verb because the syntax is different. So please don't automatically modify it into "jalike": test both impartially<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>aphéekes: you have gotten away from your first or earlier love (could be for Christ, could be for other Christians: it doesn't say). Cooling down of fervor</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Jadi bosong musti inga waktu dolu tu! Te sakarang bosong su talalu jao dari yang dolu tu. Andia ko bosong musti barenti suda dari bosong pung sala ni, ko kambali basayang sama ke dolu. Te kalo sonde, nanti Beta datang ame kambali itu lampu mas dari bosong.<bt>So you must remember that former time. Cuz (elaboration) now you are too far from that prior state. That's why you must stop this sin of yours, to return [to the state of] loving each other like previously, cuz (elaboration) you have fallen too far. If not, later I will come take that gold lamp from you. [NOTE: see note on ‘lamps’and ‘lampstands’ above]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="póthen péptookas: think where you were"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">póthen péptookas: think where you were before you fell metanoéin: have a change of heart<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Ma Beta pung hati sanáng sadiki, tagal bosong su tola Nikolai pung ajaran yang dia pung ana bua dong bekin iko. Beta ju tola dong pung bekin-bekin.<bt>But My liver is a bit happy, because you have rejected Nikolai's teaching which his underlings follow. I also reject their (evil/disruptive) deeds.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***tweaked &gt; deeds of Nico dong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">***tweaked &gt; deeds of Nico dong</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="miséis: does Pidgin &quot;hate&quot; apply to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">miséis: does Pidgin "hate" apply to ideas and practices, or only to people? Nikolaïtóon: followers of one Nikolaus, otherwise unknown, who may have taught that the material and spiritual realms are completely separate, and that immoral conduct does not affect the spiritual life. Deibler has "who taught that Christians were to practice idolatry and immorality [historical knowledge]"<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="2:6" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Orang yang pintar so'al Alkitab dong bilang, apa yang Nikolai dong ajar tu, kotong sonde tau.<bt>Experts knowledgable about the Bible say, those teachings of Nikolai are not clear (what they are).</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="7" />Naa! Dengar bae-bae apa yang Tuhan pung Roh ada kasi tau sang Dia pung jama'at dong. Orang yang batahan iko sang Beta sampe dia mati, nanti Beta kasi isin, ko dia bole makan bua dari itu pohon yang ada di Tuhan Allah pung kabón. Te orang yang makan itu pohon pung bua, dia dapa idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>So! Listen well to what the Lord's Spirit is telling His congregations. The person/whoever endures following Me until he dies, later I will give him/her permission to eat fruit from that tree which is in God's garden. Cuz (elaboration) the person/ whoever eats that tree's fruit, he gets/obtains true life that never ends.&gt;&gt;&gt; [NOTE: KT also used in John's gospel and epistles]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="táis ekkleesíais: not just church people"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">táis ekkleesíais: not just church people as individuals, or the people in the Ephesus church, but in the seven different churches John is writing to, or in all churches no matter where they are oús: like Matthew 13:9<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>ho nikóon: may not need an object, but if it does, Deibler suggests "conquers/overcomes the power of Satan" paradeisw: Luke 23:43 implies a pleasant, relaxing place (comes from a Persian word designating an area kept in game for government people to go hunting in as a break from court life). More beautiful than awesome -- we've got piles of awesome places in the book as is, and may as well lighten up when we can. [?]<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="2:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 2:9, Dunya Model Baru 22:2, Yeskial 28:13, 31:8</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kirim pasán kasi jama'at di Smirna<bt>The Lord Yesus sends instructions to the congregation at Smirna</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ais Manusia Tulen sambung Dia pung omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Yohanis, sakarang lu musti tulis surat laen. Dia pung bunyi bagini:<bt>Then that Ideal/Original Human (*Son of Man) connected His speaking saying, “Yohanis, now you must write another letter, it's sound like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Buat jama'at di kota Smirna:<bt>&lt;To the congregation at Smirna city:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ini surat ni, dari Beta, andia Yesus. Samua asal dari Beta, mulai dari partama sampe abis. Dolu Beta mati, ma sakarang Beta su idop kambali. Jadi dengar Beta pung omong ni.<bt>This letter here, is from Me, that is Yesus. Everything originates from Me, beginning from the start/first until the end. Previously I died, but now I live again. So listen to this speaking of mine.</bt><note reference="2:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 44:6, 48:12, Dunya Model Baru 1:17, 22:13</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="9" />Beta su lia bosong pung idop sangsara di kota Smirna. Iko manusia, bosong ni orang malarat. Padahal iko Tuhan, bosong kaya. Ada orang yang mangaku diri Tuhan pung orang, yang omong bekin busuk bosong pung nama bae. Padahal dong tu, bukan Tuhan pung orang. Dong sama ke satu jama'at yang iko-iko setan dong pung bos sa.<bt>I have seen your life of misery in Smirna city. According to humans (thinking), you here are poor/impoverished/unfortunate. Whereas in fact according to God2 (thinking) you are rich/wealthy. There are people who acknowledge themselves to be God's people, who speak making rotten your good name. Whereas in actual fact they, are not God's people. They are like a congregation who just follows along the evil spirit's boss (*Satan). [EXEG: ‘Jews’ here taken as codespeak for a group of people with a special relationship to God. (Also in later verses.) CEV, JG, high level; but commentaries divided.] [NOTE: shifting the “slander” clause to the end would skew the focus. The “I know” phrases signal the writer knows what is causing pain to the readers. From their perspective the symptom is what links empathy to the writer. To background that and front the more abstract reason denudes the potency of the bond.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thlíipsin: rather close to &quot;presha&quot;, in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">thlíipsin: rather close to "presha", in that it implies circumstances that wear you down bit by bit more than by crisis Ioudaíous: Jewish people. John was a Jew, and there was a big colony of Jews in Smyrna. He is probably not talking ethnically, but in terms of their flaunting their special relationship to God, without the kind of behavior that makes it meaningful. The ethnic name alone could confuse the issue<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>synagoogeè tóu Satanáa: characterizes what their worship amounts too. It shouldn't sound like "the Satanist church is on the next corner; that's where they meet". The implication is "they think they are worshipping God in their ordinary Jewish religious meetings, but they aren't; they're acting like Satan's people even when they are at worship". Deibler has "synagogue or congregation of Jews serving not God but Satan [participant identification, implicature of argument and explication of genitive]" satanáa: Satan, "da guy who stay against us", a name for the Devil<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bosong ni, orang malarat di mata"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Bosong ni, orang malarat di mata manusia, padahal bosong kaya di mata Tuhan. (mesolectal)</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Jadi dengar bae-bae. Bosong sonde usa taku, kalo nanti bosong masi dapa susa. Asal bosong tau, setan dong pung bos mau cari orang ko tangkap kasi maso bosong saparu pi dalam bui sampe sapulu hari. Dia pung maksud ko bosong bale balakang kasi tenga sang Beta. Biar dong mau bunu bekin mati sang bosong, ma bosong jang lupa sang Beta. Te orang yang batahan iko sang Beta sampe dia mati, nanti Beta balas dia pung upa, ko dia idop tarús sama-sama deng Beta.<bt>So (consequently) listen carefully. You don't need to be afraid, if/when later you still obtain/experience difficulty. As long as you know, the spirit's boss wants to/is going to find people to capture and put some of you in jail for ten days. His intent is for you to turn your backs and abandon Me. Even if they want to kill you, nevertheless you don't forget Me. Cuz (elaboration) the person/whoever endures following Me until he dies, later I will reciprocate/compensate his/her reward, so that he lives continually together with Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mélleis: you are about to experience"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">mélleis: you are about to experience something. May carry the overtones of the Divine will and plan; but here it is not advisable to explicitly make God the subject bállein: put somebody in jail, or get somebody put in jail. The Devil will engineer it; this isn't a claim that he will physically push you inside and turn the key in the lock<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>peirasthéete: when the Devil does it, it isn't to prove to him or to you what kind of stuff you are made of inside. It's an assault on your personality to force you to give in to him. So "check out" doesn't fit this context stéphanon: this is a head lei of leaves, given as the first place medal in the Olympic games and other athletic contests. It's not the kind of crown a king would wear, in this context<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="11" />Naa! Dengar bae-bae apa yang Tuhan pung Roh ada kasi tau sang Dia pung jama'at dong. Orang yang batahan iko Beta sampe dia mati, nanti dia sonde sangsara di laut api yang manyala sonde pake barenti. Deng bagitu, dia sonde mati kali kadua.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>So! Listen well to what the Lord's Spirit is telling His congregations. The person/whoever endures following Me until he dies, later he will not be tormented in the fire sea (*hell) which has no stopping. In that way, s/he doesn't die a second time.’”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="yang dong bilang tampa mati yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">yang dong bilang tampa mati yang kadua.&gt;&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 20:14, 21:8</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kirim pasán kasi jama'at di Pergamus<bt>The Lord Yesus sends instructions to the congregation at Pergamus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Tarús Manusia Tulen sambung Dia pung omong lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Yohanis, sakarang lu musti tulis surat laen lai. Dia pung bunyi bagini:<bt>Next that Ideal/Original Human (*Son of Man) connected His speach again saying, “Yohanis, now you must written yet another, it's sound is like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Buat jama'at di kota Pergamus:<bt>&lt;To the congregation at Pergamus:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ini surat ni, dari Beta, andia Yesus. Beta yang pegang kalewang mata dua yang tajam. Dengar Beta pung omong ni.<bt>This letter here, is from Me, that is Yesus. I am the one who holds a double edge fighting sword that is sharp. Listen to this speaking of Mine.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Rev 2:1 dístomon: the sword is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Rev 2:1 dístomon: the sword is sharp along both edges. A machete or a cane knife is sharp along only one edge, but it still has two sides<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="13" />Beta su kanál bosong pung kota Pergamus tu. Te yang pegang parenta di situ, andia setan dong pung bos. Biar bagitu ju, ma bosong pegang kuat Beta pung nama, deng parcaya tarús sang Beta. Dolu ada Beta pung orang satu di situ, nama Antipas. Dia salalu ajar batúl so'al Beta pung jalan idop, ma dong bunu bekin mati sang dia. Biar bagitu ju, ma bosong sonde manyangkal sang Beta.<bt>I know that Pergamus city of yours. Cuz (elaboration) the that the one who holds authority there, is the boss of the evil spirits. Even though it's like that, nevertheless you still hold tight to My name/reputation, and continue to believe in Me. Previously there was a person of Mine there, named Antipas. He always taught correctly about My way of life, but they killed him. Even though it's like that, nevertheless you do not deny Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katoikéis ... katoikéi: permanent resident thronos:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">katoikéis ... katoikéi: permanent resident thronos: where Satan is king, where he rules. There was a giant altar to Zeus, the main Greek god, on a cliff above the city, and three temples dedicated to the worship of Roman emperors<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>Satanaa: da Devil ónoma: my name -- you are personally loyal to me, you hang on to what you know about my character<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="14" />Ma beta ada lia, bosong ada jato di satu-dua hal. Ada barapa orang dari bosong yang suka iko Balaam pung ajaran. Dolu Balaam ajar sang Balak ko goda orang Isra'el dong, sampe dong langgar Tuhan pung mau. Dia buju-buju sang dong ko pi iko songgo, deng makan makanan sosonggo, deng pi maen serong deng orang yang bukan dong pung laki ko dong pung bini.<bt>But I am seeing, you are falling/lacking in one or two things. There are several people from among you who like to follow Balaam's teaching. Previously Balaam taught Balak to tempt the Israel people, until they transgressed the Lord's will. He persuaded/cajoled/ enticed/goaded them to go follow traditional.worship (=non-Christian), and to eat traditional.worship objects' food, and to go playing around sexually. [NOTE to daughter translations: Indon /Bileam/ has no basis from either Gk or Heb. (See Kupang Bible dictionary for more details if team balks).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daftar Sensus 22:5, 7, 25:1-3, 31:16, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 23:4</note><v n="15" />Ada ju barapa orang dari bosong yang iko Nikolai pung ajaran.<bt>There are also several people from you who follow Nikolai's teaching.</bt><note reference="2:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 2:6</note><v n="16" />Jadi bosong musti barenti dari bosong pung sala-sala dong. Kalo sonde, tar lama lai, te Beta datang hantam sang bosong pake kata-kata yang tajam, yang potong sama ke kalewang.<bt>So you must stop from those sins of yours. If not, not much longer, (contrary to expectation) I will come attack you using sharp words that cut like a fighting.sword.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="**revised Sep 2005 @@ like CEV"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">**revised Sep 2005 @@ like CEV "my words cut like a sword &gt; CHECK w/team &gt; sharp words like a sword / pake kata-kata yang tajam sama ke kalewang.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="romphaíaai: Deibler suggests &quot;come and judge/punish"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">romphaíaai: Deibler suggests "come and judge/punish those false teachers by the words I speak [explication of metonymy and participant identification]"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="17" />Naa! Dengar bae-bae apa yang Tuhan pung Roh ada kasi tau sang Dia pung jama'at dong. Orang yang batahan iko sang Beta sampe dia mati, nanti Beta kasi dia makan roti <span class="Italic">manna</span> dari sorga yang ada tasimpan bae-bae. Nanti Beta ju kasi sang dia batu puti satu yang ada tatulis dia pung nama baru. Cuma dia sandiri sa yang tau itu nama, ma orang laen sonde tau.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>So! Listen well to what the Lord's Spirit is telling His congregations. The person/whoever endures following Me until he dies, later I will give him to eat the <span class="Italic">manna</span> bread from heaven which is put away well. Later I will also give him a white rock on which is written his new name. Only just he himself knows that name, but other people don't know [it].”&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Rev 2:11 kekrymménou: hidden away --"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Rev 2:11 kekrymménou: hidden away -- a Jewish oral tradition says that when the Jewish temple was about to be destroyed, Jeremiah took the jar of manna that was kept inside the sacred box, and hid it in a cave on Mount Nebo. The idea was that when the Messiah came, God would feed his people with it again. Deibler suggests "I will provide nourishment for their souls which I have hidden/preserved in heaven, like I provided manna for the Israelites [explication of metaphor and OT knowledge]"<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>pséephon: pebble, stone. White symbolizes victory. The stone may be like a pass to get into heaven, or it may carry the judge's "not guilty" verdict, since white and black pebbles were used to tally jury counts</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 16:14-15, 16:33-34, Yohanis 6:48-50, Yesaya 62:2, 65:15</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kirim pasán kasi jama'at di Tiatira<bt>The Lord Yesus sends instructions to the congregation at Tiatira</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ais Manusia Tulen sambung Dia pung omong lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Yohanis, sakarang lu musti tulis surat laen lai. Dia pung bunyi bagini:<bt>Then that Ideal/Original Human (*Son of Man) connected His speaking again saying, “Yohanis, now you must write yet another letter, it's sound is like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Buat jama'at di kota Tiatira:<bt>&lt;To the congregation at Tiatira city:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ini surat ni, dari Beta, Yesus, andia Tuhan Allah pung Ana! Beta pung mata manyala sama ke api, deng Beta pung kaki ju mera manyala sama ke tambaga yang orang bakar dalam api. Dengar Beta pung omong ni.<bt>This letter here, is from Me, Yesus, that is God's Son! My eyes flicker like fire, and My feet shine like copper/bronze that a person burns in fire. Listen to this speaking of Mine.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Rev. 1:15 hoos phlóga pyrós: Deibler"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Rev. 1:15 hoos phlóga pyrós: Deibler suggests that the thought behind the figure is "his eyes penetrating with righteous wrath like a flame of fire [explication of symbols]"<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>chalkolibánooi: here "shining brass" is okay, because the detail "as it looks when it is molten" is omitted</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="19" />Beta su lia bosong pung idop. Bosong sayang batúl sang Beta deng parcaya kuat sang Beta. Bosong iko Beta pung parenta tarús ko layani orang. Biar orang bekin sangsara sang bosong ju, bosong batahan tarús. Beta ju tau bilang, sakarang ni, bosong karjá lebe karás lai kasi Beta.<bt>I have seen your lives. You truly love Me and believe strongly in Me. You always follow my commands to/and serve people. Even if people cause tribulation to you, you continue to endure. I also know that nowadays you are working even harder for Me. [NOTE: implied by grammar “than before” “than at first”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="éschata: not &quot;final&quot;, but &quot;most recent&quot;."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">éschata: not "final", but "most recent". This goes along with taking "proótoon" in a relative sense, not "initial", but "earlier" tóon proótoon: earlier, or possibly initially, when you became Christians, when you first believed in me<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="20" />Ma bosong ada jato dalam satu hal: bosong tarima bae-bae itu parampuan nama Isabel, yang angka-angka diri bilang, dia tu, Tuhan pung jubir. Ais bosong kasi loos sang dia ko ajar sala Beta pung orang dong. Tagal dia pung ajaran pakane'o tu, sampe Beta pung orang dong su iko maen serong deng orang yang bukan dong pung laki ko dong pung bini, deng iko makan makanan sosonggo.<bt>But you have fallen in one thing: you accept well that woman named Isabel, who raises herself up saying she is the Lord's spokesperson (*prophet). Then you give her opportunity to teach incorrectly My people. Because of that twisted teaching of hers, it's gotten to the point that My people have followed in (sexual) off-track/deviation/immoral with people who are not their husband or their wife, and followed eating traditional.worship objects' food. [NOTE to daughter translations: Because of high level issues, for Gk /porneuw/ here, try to find a term that can carry both sexual and moral/loyalty senses, not just a term like ‘adultery’ that is exclusively sexual.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Iezábel: this is not the historical"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Iezábel: this is not the historical Jezebel, the Sidonian princess who married King Ahab and hassled Elijah. This is somebody that has an influence in the Thyatira church that is no better than the influence the first Jezebel had on God's people during her time. The historical Jezebel did not take on the role of a prophetess, nor did she teach. Deibler has "tolerate one who is like wicked queen Jezebel who lived long ago [explication of metaphor and OT knowledge]" planáai: more than telling lies, she influences them to get away from their spiritual identity by getting into promiscuity and idol worship<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Beta su togor itu parampuan ulang kali, ko biar dia kasi tenga itu sala. Ma dia sonde mau.<bt>I have rebuked that woman repeatedly, so that she would leave that sin. But she doesn't want to.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="22" />Jadi lia bae-bae. Te sakarang Beta su putus ko hukum sang dia deng panyaki satu, sampe dia sonde bisa kasi tenga dia pung tampa tidor. Bagitu ju deng samua orang yang maen barsina deng dia. Kalo dong sonde kasi tenga itu parampuan yang jahat tu, sonde lama lai te Beta hukum sang dong ju.<bt>So (consequently) look well. Cuz (elaboration) now I have decided to judge/punish her with a sickness, until she can't leave her bed. Like that also all the people who repeatedly commit adultery with her. If they don't leave that evil woman, not much longer (=soon) I will also judge/punish them. [NOTE to daughter translations: ‘(sexual) adultery’ is OK here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eis klíneen: throw her on a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">eis klíneen: throw her on a bed, probably a sick bed; I will punish her with an illness. He doesn't say he's going to dump all her lovers in the same bed too, which was the orgiastic picture I got as a kid because the grammatical gapping was too heavy. The lovers get punished, but in a different way and a different place. Deibler, "I will cause her to suffer punishment as one on a sickbed suffers along with those who participate in her lifestyle (i.e. unfaithfulness to God/adultery) [explication of genitive, metaphor, and metonymy]" moicheúontas met' autées: committing adultery with her -- this is a figure of speech used a lot in the Old Testament and the New to talk about people who are cheating on God. The people John is talking about were probably cheating on both their wives and on God<span class="Italic">(22)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Nanti Beta bunu itu parampuan jahat pung ana dong. Deng bagitu, bosong samua yang parcaya dong mangarti bilang, Beta tau manusia pung isi hati dong. Deng nanti beta balas kasi sang bosong iko bosong pung bekin-bekin.<bt>Later I will kill her children. In that way, all you believers will understand that I know the contents of humans' livers/hearts. And later I will reciprocate you according to your deeds.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="TRan handbook - inter as bad"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">TRan handbook - inter as bad things; Martens - is 'her children' kept as an an apocalyptic figure or not?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tékna: followers who listened to her"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">tékna: followers who listened to her teaching. The lovers are more like her associates. Deibler has "those who are like her children because they follow her wicked teaching [explication of metaphor]" eraunóon: searching out what is inside, in order to heal or punish<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>doósoo: implies punishment, though the words used are actually neutral -- I will give them whatever reward or punishment they deserve (CHECK PARALLELS).</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 7:10, 62:13, Yeremia 17:10</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="24" />Ma bosong yang laen di Tiatira situ, sonde iko itu parampuan pung ajaran jahat tu. Te bosong su tola itu ajaran rahasia yang dong bilang, &lt;setan pung ilmu galáp&gt;. Tagal itu, Beta sonde parlú togor lai kasi sang bosong,<bt>But the rest of you in Tiatira over there don't follow that teaching of that evil woman. Cuz (elaboration) you have rejected that secret teaching which they call ‘evil spirits' dark/black magic’. Because of that, I don't need to scold you any more,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ajaran-ajaran jahat yang orang ajar itu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Ajaran-ajaran jahat yang orang ajar itu dong parlente la sebut akang par kepala setang pung kata-kata yang masi tasambunyi. Tapi yang tinggal di Tiatira kamong saparu seng iko ajaran jahat itu, jadi Beta mau bilang par kamong bahwa Beta seng kasi tamba beban par kamong.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ouk égnoosan: have never gotten into"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">ouk égnoosan: have never gotten into this stuff. Deibler has "who have not learned/experienced the immoral lifestyle inspired by Satan [explication of `deep things' and genitive]" Satanaa: da Devil<span class="Italic">(24)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="25" />asal bosong pegang karás bosong pung parcaya sampe Beta datang.<bt>as long as you-pl hold firmly to your faith until I come.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="échete: your Christian commitment. Deibler has"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">échete: your Christian commitment. Deibler has "hold fast to the spiritual truth and zeal that you have [concept identification]"</Message></Annotation><v n="26-28" />Orang yang batahan iko sang Beta sampe dia mati, nanti Beta kasi kuasa sang dia. Itu kuasa tu, kuasa bésar, sama ke yang Beta dapa dari Beta pung Bapa, ko parenta samua suku-bangsa di dunya deng tangan bési. Kalo ada yang lawan sang dia, nanti dia bekin ancor sang dong, sama ke orang bekin pica pareu tana.<bt>The person/whoever endures following Me until he dies, later I will give him authority. That aforementioned authority, is big authority, like that which I received from My Father, to command all the nations in the world with a iron hand. If there are those who oppose him, later he will destroy them, like a person breaks a earthern pot. [NOTE to daughter translations: if "tangan besi" doesn't communicate, try "tongkat besi"]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tangan bési = harsh, cruel, heavy-handed,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">tangan bési = harsh, cruel, heavy-handed, kejam</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="The line marked m2 here should"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">The line marked m2 here should come left to be even with the second line in verse 26. en rábdooi sideeráai: with an iron-capped club. Rule them ruthlessly and not let anybody get out of line. We talk about "iron authority". Deibler has "rule over and destroy those opposed to him with severe judgment and destruction as earthen pots are destroyed with a rod of iron [participant identification and explication of metaphor]"<span class="Italic">(26)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="2:26-27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 2:8-9</note>Nanti Beta ju kasi bintang timur sang bosong.<bt>Later I also will give the east star to you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Venus or Mercury when they shine"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Venus or Mercury when they shine early in the morning. Deibler has "my presence which will shine like the morning star (OR, he will receive glory as the shining of the morning star) [explication of metaphor and wider contextual information]"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="29" />Naa! Dengar bae-bae apa yang Tuhan pung Roh ada kasi tau sang Dia pung jama'at dong.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>So! Listen well to what the Lord's Spirit is telling His congregations.”&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kirim pasán kasi jama'at di Sardis<bt>The Lord Yesus sends instructions to the congregation at Sardis</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="3" />
      <v n="1" />Tarús Manusia Tulen sambung Dia pung omong lai deng beta bilang, &lt;&lt;Yohanis, sakarang lu musti tulis surat laen lai. Dia pung bunyi bagini:<bt>Next that Ideal/Original Human (*Son of Man) connected his speaking again with me saying, “Yohanis, now you must write yet another letter, it's sound like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Buat jama'at di kota Sardis:<bt>&lt;To the congregation at Sardis city:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ini surat ni, dari Beta, andia Yesus. Tuhan Allah pung Roh ada di Beta. Deng itu Roh ada tuju sisi. Beta ju yang pegang tuju bintang di Beta pung tangan. Dengar Beta pung omong ni.<bt>This letter here, is from Me, that is Yesus. God's Spirit is upon/exists in Me. And that Spirit has seven facets/manifestations. I also am the one who holds seven stars in my hand. Listen to this speaking of mine. [EXEG: see discussion and ftn at 1:4.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="M. Crofts suggestion: I am the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">M. Crofts suggestion: I am the one who commands/hold the Holy Spirit that is like the seven spirits. ***CHECK out EXEG carefully [Beta yang ada Tuhan Allah pung Roh yang ada pung tuju sisi. // Tuhan Allah pung Roh ada di Beta. Deng itu Roh ada tuju sisi.]</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Beta yang parenta Tuhan Allah pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Beta yang parenta Tuhan Allah pung tuju roh, deng Beta ju yang pegang tuju bintang di Beta pung tangan.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Beta su lia bosong pung karjá samua di Sardis sana. Ada orang yang bilang bosong batúl-batúl idop iko Beta pung mau, padahal bosong sama ke sonde ada pung idop.<bt>I have seen your doings in Sardis over there. There are people who say you really live according to My will, whereas in actual fact you are as if you have no life. [EXEG: life = reputation for spiritual vitality; see Mounce, Hughes]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***alive ~ dead; fixed Sept 2005"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">***alive ~ dead; fixed Sept 2005</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Jadi bangun su! Bekin tamba kuat bosong pung parcaya yang su amper abis. Te Beta su pareksa apa yang bosong su bekin, ma sonde ada yang batúl di Tuhan Allah pung mata.<bt>So get/wake up! Strengthen that faith of yours which is almost gone. Cuz (elaboration) I have examined those deeds of yours, and there are none which are true in God's eyes.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="gínou greegoróon: become alert, get with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">gínou greegoróon: become alert, get with it (not what you would usually say to a dead man) steérison: put a solid support under the other things<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>émellon apothanéin: on the point of death, Christian virtues that were about to disappear from their lives pepleerooména: brought to completion -- you start things and never finish them. Could also mean up to my standards, everything they are supposed to be<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Jadi jang lupa samua ajaran batúl yang bosong su dengar deng tarima dari dolu. Iko batúl-batúl Tuhan pung mau, deng kasi tenga bosong pung sala-sala dong ko bale iko sang Tuhan. Kalo bosong sonde bangun capát ko bekin bagitu, nanti takuju sa Beta datang sama ke pancuri, yang bosong sonde sangka-sangka.<bt>So (consequently), don't forget all that correct teaching which you have heard and accepted from before. Truly follow the Lord's will, and leave your wrongs to turn and follow/obey God2. If you don't get up quickly to do like that, later I will come suddenly like a thief, whom you are not expecting.</bt><note reference="3:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 24:43-44, Lukas 12:39-40, Dunya Model Baru 16:15</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="4" />Ma masi ada saparu dari bosong di Sardis yang idop lurus, sama ke orang yang sonde bekin kotor dia pung pakean. Tagal dong pung idop lurus, jadi dong yang nanti pantas jalan sama-sama deng Beta pake pakean puti.<bt>But there are still some of you in Sardis who live straight, like people who don't make their clothes dirty. Because of their straight/righteous lives, thus later they are the ones who are appropriate/worthy to walk together with Me wearing white clothes. [NOTE to daughter translations: because this is written to people in Sardis, some lgs might do better if the who verse is in 2p.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="olíga: a few people leukà: white,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">olíga: a few people leukà: white, symbolizing purity<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Orang yang batahan iko sang Beta sampe dia mati, nanti dia ju pake pakean puti. Beta sonde hapus dia pung nama dari itu tulisan yang daftar samua orang pung nama yang nanti dapa idop tarús-tarús deng Tuhan. Nanti Beta ju mangaku sang dia di muka Beta pung Bapa, deng Bapa pung ana bua di sorga bilang, dia tu, Beta pung orang.<bt>The person/whoever endures following My way of live until he dies, later he will also wear white clothes like that. I will not erase his name from that writing which lists all the people's names who will live continually with the Lord. Later I will also acknowledge him in front of My Father, and Father angels in heaven, saying he, is my person.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Rev. 2:7"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Rev. 2:7</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 32:32-33, Lagu Puji dong 69:29, Dunya Model Baru 2:7, 20:12, Mateos 10:32, Lukas 12:8</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="6" />Naa! Dengar bae-bae apa yang Tuhan pung Roh ada kasi tau sang Dia pung jama'at dong.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>So! Listen well to what the Lord's Spirit is telling His congregations.”&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kirim pasán kasi jama'at di Filadelfia<bt>The Lord Yesus sends instructions to the congregation at Filadelfia</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ais Manusia Tulen omong tarús lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Yohanis, sakarang lu musti tulis surat laen lai. Dia pung bunyi bagini:<bt>Then that Ideal/Original Human (*Son of Man) spoke on again saying, “Yohanis, now you must write yet another letter, it's sound is like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Buat jama'at di kota Filadelfia:<bt>&lt;To the congregation at Filadelfia city:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ini surat ni, dari Beta, Yesus. Beta ni, yang Barisi deng yang Batúl. Beta yang pegang raja Daud pung konci. Kalo beta buka pintu, sonde ada yang bisa tutu. Kalo beta tutu, sonde ada yang bisa buka.<bt>This letter here, is from Me, Yesus. I here, am the one who is Holy/Clean and True. I am the one who hold's raja Daud's key. If I open a door, there is no one who can close it. If I close [it], there is no one who can open [it].</bt><note reference="3:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 22:22, Ayub 12:14</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="8" />Beta tau samua yang bosong su bekin. Beta ju tau, bosong pung pangaru sadiki sa. Biar bagitu ju, ma bosong sonde manyangkal sang Beta, deng bosong iko tarús Beta pung ajaran. Inga bae-bae, te Beta su buka pintu kasi sang bosong, jadi sonde ada yang bisa tutu.<bt>I know all that which you have done. I also know your influence is small/insignificant. Even though it's like that, but you don't deny Me, and [you] continue to follow My teaching. Remember well, cuz (elaboration) I have opened the door for you, so there is no one who can close [it]. [EXEG: “little strength/power” has a broad range of interpretations (Ex. Summ). Teh meaning of “few people” is a minority possibility with little support, so keep it broader.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thýran eeneooigméneen: a door that has"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">thýran eeneooigméneen: a door that has already been opened and is still open -- symbol of opportunity to serve or to preach the Gospel, or to enter God's kingdom freely mikràn: you have a little power, but not a lot -- still, it's enough that you can do something<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>dýnamin: clout, prestige in the community, good reputation with leverage about getting things done eteéreesas: you have kept what I told you, you've done it and not let it get away from you<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="9" />Dengar bae-bae! Te ada orang yang omong kosong bilang, dong tu, Tuhan pung orang yang batúl. Padahal dong tu, tukang putar-balek yang iko-iko setan dong pung bos. Ma nanti bosong lia sa! Te Beta bekin sampe dong datang tikam lutut di bosong pung muka, deng mangaku bilang, Beta memang sayang sang bosong.<bt>But you be careful! Cuz (elaboration) there are people who lie saying that they are God2's true people. Whereas in actual fact, they are deceivers, who follow along the boss of the evil spirits. But later you will just see (=watch what will happen!). Cuz (elaboration) I will make it happen that they come kneel in front of you, and acknowledge that I truly love you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Satanaa: da Devil See Rev. 2:9|i(9)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Satanaa: da Devil See Rev. 2:9<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 49:23, 60:14, 43:4</note><v n="10" />Tagal bosong su iko Beta pung parenta ko batahan iko sang Beta tarús, andia ko nanti Beta jaga bae-bae sang bosong dari sangsara yang Tuhan mau kirim datang ko uji samua orang di ini dunya.<bt>Because you have followed My command to endure following Me, that's why later I will protect you well from the suffering that God will sent to test everyone in this world.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="11" />Sonde lama lai te Beta su datang. Jadi pegang kuat-kuat Beta pung ajaran yang bosong su tarima dari dolu. Te jang sampe ada yang rampas ame bosong pung upa yang Tuhan mau kasi sang bosong.<bt>Not much longer (contrary to expectation) I will have come. So (consequently) hold tightly to My teaching which you have accepted from before. Cuz (elaboration) may it not be that someone snatches away your reward which God2 wants to give you. [EXEG: crown = reward (for service/faithfulness, not salvation)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** // tanda bae yang Tuhan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** // tanda bae yang Tuhan mau balas kasi sang bosong</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="See Rev. 2:25, 10."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">See Rev. 2:25, 10.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Sonde lama lai te Beta su"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Sonde lama lai te Beta su datang. Jadi bapegang kuat-kuat Beta pung ajaran yang bosong su tarima dari dolu tu. Te kalo bosong iko ajaran laen, nanti ilang buang samua yang Tuhan mau balas kasi sang bosong.</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Orang yang batahan iko sang Beta sampe dia mati, nanti dia tenga tarús-tarús deng Tuhan, sama ke satu tiang bésar yang tatanam mati di Tuhan Allah pung Ruma. Nanti Beta tulis Beta pung Tuhan pung nama, deng Tuhan pung kota pung nama, di itu orang pung diri. Itu kota tu, dong subu bilang, &lt;Yerusalem Baru&gt;, yang nanti Tuhan kasi turun datang dari sorga. Deng nanti Beta ju tulis Beta pung nama baru di itu orang pung diri.<bt>The person/whoever endures following Me to the point of death, later he will live continually with the Lord, like a big pole/pillar that is planted dead (unmovable) in God's House. Later I will write My Lord's name, and the Lord's city's name, on that person's body. That city there, they refer to as ‘New Yerusalem’, which later the Lord will send down from heaven. And later I will also write my new name on that person's body.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NOTE: Gk is 2p, not 3s"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">NOTE: Gk is 2p, not 3s</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="See Rev. 2:7."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">See Rev. 2:7.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 21:2, Yesaya 62:2, 65:15</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="13" />Naa! Dengar bae-bae apa yang Tuhan pung Roh ada kasi tau sang Dia pung jama'at dong.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>So! Listen well to what the Lord's Spirit is telling His congregations.”&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="See Rev. 2:7."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">See Rev. 2:7.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kirim pasán kasi jama'at di Laodikia<bt>The Lord Yesus sends instructions to the congregation at Laodikia</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ais Manusia Tulen sambung Dia pung omong lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Yohanis, sakarang lu musti tulis surat tarahir. Dia pung bunyi bagini:<bt>Then that Ideal/Original Human (*Son of Man) connected His speaking again saying, “Yohanis, now you must write the final letter, it's sound like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Buat jama'at di kota Laodikia:<bt>&lt;To the congregation at Laodikia city:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ini surat ni, dari Beta, Yesus, yang orang pange bilang, &lt;Yang Batúl&gt;. Beta ni, salalu omong batúl-batúl Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata. Deng samua-samua yang Tuhan su bekin, asal dari Beta.<bt>This letter here, is from Me, Yesus, whom people call, saying &lt;True&gt;. I here, always speak truthfully God's Words. And all those things which the Lord has made, they originate from Me.</bt><note reference="3:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kata-kata Mutiara 8:22</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="15" />Beta su lia bosong ada bekin apa di Laodikia sana. Ma bosong ni, karmana?! Panas, sonde; dingin ju sonde. Kalo panas, na, panas batúl-batúl! Kalo dingin, na, dingin batúl-batúl!<bt>I have seen your deeds in Laodikia over there. But how is it with you? Hot, no, not cold either. If [you're going to be] hot, na, be truly hot! If [you're going to be] cold, na, be truly cold!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bekin-bekin has negative overtones"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">bekin-bekin has negative overtones</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="psychròs: cold, indifferent, don't care zestòs:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">psychròs: cold, indifferent, don't care zestòs: hot, enthusiastic, pumping<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Ma tagal bosong pung hati satenga-satenga, Beta mau sumbur buang sang bosong dari Beta pung mulu, sama ke orang sumbur buang luda.<bt>But because your livers are half-hearted, I'm going to spit expel you from My mouth, like a person spits expels saliva. [EXEG: Gk aspect is explicit “I'm about to (spit)”. So try and get it more precise than just ‘later’ or ‘will’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@hati bacabang is uncertain, doubting; is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">@@hati bacabang is uncertain, doubting; is this the same as lukewarm/half-hearted? No. **changed Sep 2005</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="17" />Bosong omong sombong bilang, &lt;Kotong ni, orang kaya. Kotong idop bae-bae, sonde parlú apa-apa lai!&gt; Padahal bosong pung hati su buta, sampe bosong sonde tau mana yang bae. Andia ko bosong su jadi sama ke orang miskin malarat deng talanjang.<bt>You speak proudly/arrogantly [=negative superiority, not justifiable pride] saying, ‘We here, are rich people. We live well, not needing anything else!&gt; While in actual fact, your livers are blind, to the point that you don't know which (of choices) is good. That's why you have become like a destitute poor and naked person. [EXEG: See Ex. Summ. for basis of 3rd sentence--both mental and spiritual blindness. LN, BAGD, HCE]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** sama ke"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** sama ke</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="talaípooros: pathetic, wretched, in bad shape"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">talaípooros: pathetic, wretched, in bad shape eleeinos: pitiable<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Jadi lebe bae bosong datang béli ame mas tulen dari Beta, ko biar bosong jadi orang yang batúl-batúl kaya. Deng béli ame pakean puti ko tutu bosong pung malu. Deng béli ame obat mata ko goso di bosong pung mata, ko biar bosong dapa lia kambali deng taráng.<bt>So (consequently) it's better if you come buy pure/original gold from Me, so that you become people who are truly rich. And buy white clothes to cover that embarressment of yours. And buy eye medicine to rub in your eyes, so that you can see again clearly.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="19" />Kalo orang yang Beta sayang bekin sala, Beta togor deng hukum sang dong, ko biar dong jadi bae. Jadi bosong musti bekin lurus bosong pung hati, ko bosong batúl-batúl samangat iko sang Beta.<bt>If people whom I love do wrong, I scold and punish them, so that they become good. So you must straighten your livers, so that you are truly enthusiastic to follow Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="zeéleue: the opposite of lukewarm --"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">zeéleue: the opposite of lukewarm -- get enthusiastic, charged up</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kata-kata Mutiara 3:12, Ibrani 12:6</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="20" />Dengar bae-bae, te Beta su badiri di muka pintu, deng Beta ada pange-pange ko mau maso. Kalo ada orang dengar Beta pung suara, ais dia datang buka pintu, nanti Beta maso pi dalam, ko botong dudu makan sama-sama.<bt>Listen well, cuz (elaboration) I am already standing in the front of the door, and I am repeatedly calling in order to enter. If there is a person who hears my voice, then he comes open the door, later I will go inside, so that the two of us eat together. [EXEG: verbal aspect changed to better reflect the Gk. In this region, people call out to enter, rather than knock.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="deipneésoo: have a meal, regardless of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">deipneésoo: have a meal, regardless of the time of day kroúoo: knock, asking but not demanding to be let inside<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>anoíxeei: open and invite somebody inside the house</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Orang yang batahan iko sang Beta sampe dia mati, nanti Beta kasi hak sang dia, ko dudu parenta sama-sama deng Beta. Te Beta ju su batahan iko sang Beta pung Bapa, andia ko sakarang Beta dudu parenta sama-sama deng Dia.<bt>The person/whoever endures following My way of life to the point of death, later I will give him the authority, to rule together with Me. Cuz (elaboration) I also have endured following My Father, that's why now I sit ruling together with Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="22" />Naa! Dengar bae-bae apa yang Tuhan pung Roh ada kasi tau sang Dia pung jama'at dong.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>So! Listen well to what the Lord's Spirit is telling His congregations.”&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong sémba sang Tuhan Allah di sorga<bt>They worship God in heaven</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="4" />
      <v n="1" />Manusia Tulen omong abis Dia pung pasán kasi sang itu tuju jama'at dong, ais Tuhan buka kasi lia sang beta hal laen lai. Takuju sa, beta lia satu pintu tabuka di sorga. Ais beta dengar lai itu orang yang pung suara karás sama ke tarompet tu bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari! Nae datang di sini su, ko beta mau kasi lia sang lu samua yang nanti jadi.&gt;&gt;<bt>That Ideal/Original Human (*Son of Man) finished speaking his requests to those seven congregations, then the Lord reveal yet another thing/s to me. Suddenly, I saw a door open in heaven. Then I heard again that person's whose voice was loud like a trumpet saying, “Come! Come up here, so that I can show you all that will happen later.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) removed “door (facing) heaven”"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** (2009) removed “door (facing) heaven”</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="voice like a trumpet Rev. 1:10."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">voice like a trumpet Rev. 1:10. "Trumpet" OK; "horn" would be like a car horn. éidon: I saw, referring to a vision as in 1:12. Like a dream, but seen when the person is awake<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>deíxoo: "goin show" sounds like a more distant future than "like show"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Itu waktu ju Tuhan pung Roh angka bawa sang beta pi sorga. Takuju beta lia ada satu korsi parenta deng ada yang dudu di atas.<bt>At that time then the Lord's Spirit lifted took me to heaven. Suddenly I saw a ruling chair which had someone sitting on it.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="maybe not angka bawa because in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">maybe not angka bawa because in spirit only; takuju te = behold</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Dia bacaya warna ijo deng mera, sama ke batu mangkilat yang mahal yang dong subu bilang, <span class="Italic">yaspis</span> deng <span class="Italic">sardius.</span> Ada ju palangi satu kuliling Dia pung korsi parenta. Dia pung cahaya, warna ijo sama ke batu mangkilat <span class="Italic">samrud.</span><bt>He radiated green and red colours, like jewel stones that are expensive which they refer to as <span class="Italic">yaspis</span> and <span class="Italic">sardius.</span> There was also a rainbow surrounding that ruling chair. It's radiance, was a green colour like the <span class="Italic">samrud</span> jewel. [NOTE: colours, etc. relating to precious stones from Loewen, TH, Martins article.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="homoios horasie: had a visual effect"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">homoios horasie: had a visual effect like that of a ... (two times)</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:2-3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 1:26-28, 10:1</note><v n="4" />Di situ ju ada 24 korsi parenta kici kuliling itu korsi parenta yang ada di teng-tenga. Ada 24 katua yang dudu di itu korsi dong. Dong samua pake pakean puti, deng pake topi parenta dari mas.<bt>There there were also 24 other ruling chairs surrounding that ruling chair in the middle. There were 24 elders who sat in those chairs. They all wore white clothes, and wore ruling hats from gold.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@changed topi juara &gt; topi parenta**"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">@@changed topi juara &gt; topi parenta** BASED on what? Context? (Gk is /stefanos/)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="presbytérous: though tradition adds up the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">presbytérous: though tradition adds up the twelve apostles and the twelve tribe leaders to get 24, these act more like heavenly citizens than like people with an earthly connection, or like ordinary church "elders" leukóis: white may suggest purity, or victory, or immortality<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>crown made from gold, not solid gold</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ada kilat yang basambar dari itu korsi parenta yang ada di teng-tenga, deng guntur dong babunyi bésar basambung. Ada ju tuju obor yang manyala di itu korsi parenta pung muka. Dong tu, sama ke Tuhan pung Roh yang ada pung tuju sisi.<bt>There was lightning that struck out from the midst of those ruling chairs, and thunder that rumbled on loudly. There were also seven torches that burned/shone in front of that ruling chair. Those were like Gld2's Spirit which seven facets/ manifestations. [EXEG: see discussion and ftn at 1:4. Make parallel with 3:1.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***take parallel solution to 3:1 on"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">***take parallel solution to 3:1 on 7 spirits</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ada ju tuju obor yang manyala"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Ada ju tuju obor yang manyala di itu korsi parenta pung muka, andia Tuhan Allah pung tuju roh.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pneúmata: not ghosts, but unseen beings"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">pneúmata: not ghosts, but unseen beings with personalities that can influence people. It may be a symbolic way of talking about the Holy Spirit. Attach "good", because people are acquainted with other spirits that are not good. [But P&amp;S say only good spirits would come from God, so do not need to say 'good'.] lampádes pyròs: fixed torches that burn with a visible flame. Not lamps that burn oil, but torches that themselves burn on top.<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="4:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 19:16, Dunya Model Baru 1:4, 8:5, 11:19, 16:18, Yeskial 1:13, Sakaria 4:2</note><v n="6" />Di muka itu korsi parenta tu, beta lia tingka ke ada laut yang jarní sama ke kaca.<bt>In front of that ruling chair, I saw as if there was a sea that was clear like glass.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="A pool like the reflecting pool"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">A pool like the reflecting pool in front of the State Capitol building, part of the architecture. King Solomon had one at his palace.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais beta lia 4 binatang luar biasa kuliling itu korsi. Dong pung badan muka-balakang ponu deng mata. Dong tu, Tuhan pung binatang yang layani sang Dia.<bt>Then I saw there were four extra-ordinary animals around that chair. Their bodies front-back were full of eyes. They were the Lord's animals who served/attended Him. [EXEG: “in the midst” made implicit; although vs. 6 isn't clear, the info in vs. 8 gives fuller info allowing us to say here that the eyes are on their bodies, not just on their heads. “Served” from higher level context (vs.8-11, etc) signals that these fearsome creatures were not a threat. Required here as part of background intro to them.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** restructured from earlier versions Sept"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** restructured from earlier versions Sept 2005 / Oct 2007</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kyklóoi: next to the throne, one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">kyklóoi: next to the throne, one on each of its four sides</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Itu korsi parenta ada di laut"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Itu korsi parenta ada di laut pung teng-tenga.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 1:22</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Binatang partama pung muka tu, sama ke singa. Nomer dua pung muka, sama ke sapi laki. Nomer tiga pung muka, sama ke manusia. Deng nomer ampa pung muka, sama ke burung garuda tarbáng.<bt>That first animal's face, was like a lion. Number two's face, was like a bull. Number three's face, was like a human. And number four's face, was like a flying garuda bird.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="moschóoi: young bull, calf"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">moschóoi: young bull, calf</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:7" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Iko orang yang pintar so'al Alkitab, dong bilang ini binatang 4 dong pung arti, andia: Singa tu, yang paling kuasa. Sapi laki tu, yang paling kuat. Manusia tu, yang paling pintar. Deng garuda tu, yang paling capát.<bt>According to experts on the Bible, they say these four animals meaning is: The lion, is the one who is most powerful. The cow, is the one who is the strongest. Humans, are the ones who are the smartest. And the garuda bird, is the one who is the fastest.</bt></note><note reference="4:6-7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 1:5-10, 10:14</note><v n="8" />Itu 4 binatang dong, satu-satu ada pung anam sayap. Di itu sayap dong pung bagian luar deng bagian dalam, ju ponu deng mata. Siang-malam dong manyanyi sonde putus-putus bilang,<bt>Those four animals, each one had six wings. On those wings inside part and outside part, were also full of eyes. Day-night they sang without stopping saying, [EXEG: NLT has wings covered with eyes; CEV has bodies covered with eyes; NRSV is vague. Gk “they are full of eyes” could refer grammatically to the wings or the creatures as a whole. KM has both covered, saying ‘bodies’ in vs. 6 and ‘wings’ in vs. 8.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Botong puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah!<bt>“We keep praising God!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Botong angka tinggi-tinggi Tuhan pung nama!<bt>We lift up high God's name!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan tu, yang talalu barisi!<bt>God is the one, who is extremely holy/clean!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan tu, yang pung kuasa paling hebat.<bt>God is the one, whose authority is extremely amazing.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan yang ada dari dolu.<bt>God is the one who existed from long ago.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan yang ada sakarang.<bt>God is the one who exists now.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Deng Tuhan yang ada tarús sampe salamanya!&gt;&gt;<bt>God is the one who will continue forever!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="légontes: the Greek word is nonspecific"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">légontes: the Greek word is nonspecific about the mode of utterance, but it isn't conversation. Chanting is a part of all ethnic Hawaiian rituals, which other people are familiar with from television, and it is also part of the Buddhist heritage Rev. 1:4, 1:8.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="4:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 1:18, 10:12, Yesaya 6:2-3</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Deng manyanyi bagitu, dong puji deng kasi hormat sang Tuhan Allah, deng minta tarima kasi sang Dia, tagal Dia yang dudu di atas itu korsi parenta, deng Dia yang ada tarús-tarús sampe salamanya. Waktu dong ada manyanyi,<bt>By singing like that, they praised and gave respect to God, and requested/reciprocated thankyou to Him, because He was who sat on that ruling chair, and who lives continually. When they were singing, [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><v n="10" />itu 24 katua dong ju jato tikam lutut di muka Tuhan Allah yang ada dudu di itu korsi parenta. Dong buka dong pung topi parenta, ais taro di muka Dia pung korsi parenta, ko sémba sang Dia yang ada sampe salamanya. Ais dong angka puji sang Dia bilang,<bt>those 24 elders also fell kneeling in front of God who was sitting in that ruling chair. They took off their champion hats, then put them in front of that ruling chair of His, in order to worship Him who lives continually. They raise/lift praises to Him saying, [EXEG: Gk is /stefanos/ here, not /diadema/; but apparently from the higher-level context, a consultant felt “topi parenta” (usually matches /diadema/) fit better than “topi juara” (usually matches /stefanos/)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="balóusin: throw, implying that the honor"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">balóusin: throw, implying that the honor they have is no big deal compared to God. But in Pidgin throwing them on the ground would imply that they are disgusted with God, so it sounds better to say that they place them there carefully, which allows for respect légontes: as in v 8, they aren't just talking. But 24 people together don't chant in this culture (four can, if it's antiphonal), so with the rhythm of the words it has to be taken to be more like singing<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="11" />&lt;&lt;Oo, Tuhan Allah!<bt>“O Lord God!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Botong puji-puji sang Tuhan!<bt>We praise God!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Botong angka tinggi-tinggi Tuhan pung nama.<bt>We lift up high God's name.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tuhan ni, yang hak parenta sang botong.<bt>This God2, the one with say-so/ordering rights over us-exc.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tuhan ni, botong pung Allah!<bt>This God2, is our God1!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan yang pantas tarima botong pung puji.<bt>God2 is the one who is appropriate to receive our praise.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan yang memang musti tarima botong pung hormat.<bt>God2 is the one who certainly must receive our respect/honour.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tagal Tuhan yang paling kuasa.<bt>Because God2 is the one who is the most powerful.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng Tuhan yang paling hebat.<bt>And God2 is the one who is the most amazing. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan yang bekin samua.<bt>God2 is the one who made everything.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan yang kasi idop samua.<bt>God2 is the one who cause everything to live.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Samua yang ada,<bt>Everything that exists,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">su jadi tagal Tuhan yang bekin.<bt>has happened because it's God who created it.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Samua yang idop,<bt>Everything that lives,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">su ada napas tagal Tuhan yang kasi.&gt;&gt;<bt>has breath because it's God who gave it.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="to receive glory, and honor, and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">to receive glory, and honor, and power: people giving God these things Exist: This needs to include both living and inanimate things. In Acts 17:28: "live and move and have our being": "...stay an move an do everyting."<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tuhan or you?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Tuhan or you?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tulisan tagulung yang tasegel mati<bt>The rolled writing that is sealed closed</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="5" />
      <v n="1" />Ais beta lia kambali sang Dia yang dudu di itu korsi parenta tu. Dia ada pegang satu gulungan di tangan kanan. Itu gulungan tu, ponu deng tulisan muka-balakang. Deng dong su segel mati di tuju tampa.<bt>Then I saw again at He who sat in that ruling chair. He held a *scroll (Indo: rolled up thing) in His right hand. That scroll was full of writing front-back. And they had sealed it shut in seven places.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katesphragisménon: it had wax seals along"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">katesphragisménon: it had wax seals along the edge and on the strings so that the only way to see what it said would be to break the seals. But the seals were not broken yet. Still, no need to mention the string, which isn't in the text.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dia ada pegang satu tulisan di"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Dia ada pegang satu tulisan di tangan kanan. Itu tulisan ada tagulung, deng ada tatulis muka-balakang.</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 2:9-10, Yesaya 29:11</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Ais beta dapa lia satu ana bua dari sorga yang hebat batúl. Dia tanya deng suara karás bilang, &lt;&lt;Sapa yang ada pung hak ko bisa buka itu segel deng baca itu tulisan?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then I saw an angel from heaven who was truly amazing. He asked in a loud voice saying, “Who has the right to open those seals and read that writing?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="iskhyròn: not just physically strong, but"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">iskhyròn: not just physically strong, but having a lot of clout, an important angel áxios: qualified, has the right, he deserves to get it<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Dia tanya bagitu, ma dong sonde dapa satu orang ju yang ada pung hak ko bisa buka itu gulungan, deng baca dia pung isi. Bae di sorga, bae di bumi, sonde satu ju yang ada pung hak. Di orang mati pung tampa, sonde ada ju.<bt>He asked like that, but they did not find even one person who had the right to open that writing and read its contents. Not in heaven, nor on earth, there was no one who had the right. In the dead people's place, there was not anyone either.</bt><v n="4" />Lia bagitu ju, beta manangis makarereu, tagal sonde ada satu orang ju yang ada pung hak ko bisa buka itu gulungan, deng baca dia pung isi.<bt>Seeing like that, then I cried sobbing loudly, because there was not even one who had the right to open that writing and read its contents.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="heuréthee: does not imply a search,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">heuréthee: does not imply a search, but just that there was nobody qualified</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ais satu dari itu 24 katua tu, omong deng beta bilang, &lt;&lt;He, bu! Jang manangis. Te raja Daud ada pung turunan satu yang hebat, yang dong pange sang Dia bilang, &lt;Singa dari suku Yahuda&gt;. Dia su banting kasi ancor samua yang jahat. Jadi Dia yang ada pung hak ko bisa buka itu segel, deng baca itu tulisan pung isi.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then one of those 24 elders, spoke with me saying, “He, [+objection] elder brother! Don't cry. Cuz (elaboration) raja Daud has a descendant who is amazing, whom they call saying, ‘Lion from Yahuda clan/tribe&gt;. He has smashed destroyed all that is evil. So (consequently), He has the right to open that seal and read that writing's contents.”</bt><note reference="5:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 49:9, Yesaya 11:1, 10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Dengar bagitu, ju beta dapa lia satu Domba Ana badiri di teng-tenga itu 4 binatang luar biasa tu, deng itu 24 katua yang dudu kuliling itu korsi parenta. Itu Domba Ana tu, tingka ke su parná kaná bunu. Dia pung tandok ada tuju, deng Dia pung mata ada tuju. Dia pung tuju mata biji tu, sama ke Dia pung Roh yang ada pung tuju sisi, yang Dia su kirim pi anteru dunya.<bt>Hearing like that, then I saw a Sheep Offspring standing in the middle of those four extra-ordinary animals, and those 24 elders who sat around that ruling chair. That Sheep Offspring there, it was as if it had once been murdered/killed. His horns were seven, and his eyes were seven. Those seven eyes of his, were like His Spirit which has seven facets/manifestations, whom He had sent to the whole world. [NOTE to daughter translations: review note at 1:4; follow solution consistent with 1:4, 3:1 &amp; 4:6 re: 7 spirits, but remember here they are sent to 7 locations, so has to make sense.] [NOTE to daughter translations: yg parná kaná bunu (implication: and was brought back to life). For most groups this is clear from the grammar plus the activities that it does, but just CHECK.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** follow solution used in 1:4,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** follow solution used in 1:4, 3:1 &amp; 4:6 re: 7 spirits ; tandok = horn ; tandu = stretcher *** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dia pung tuju mata biji tu,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Dia pung tuju mata biji tu, andia Tuhan pung tuju roh yang Dia su kirim pi dalam dunya.</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 53:7, Sakaria 4:10</note><v n="7" />Ais beta lia itu Domba Ana pi di Dia yang ada dudu di itu korsi parenta, ko ame itu tulisan tagulung dari Dia pung tangan kanan.<bt>Then I saw that Sheep Offspring go to the one who was sitting in that ruling chair, and take that rolled writing from His right hand.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eíleephen: he took it -- not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">eíleephen: he took it -- not snatching it away, but receiving it because he was qualified to take it</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Waktu itu Domba Ana ame ju, itu 4 binatang luar biasa, deng itu 24 katua tu, jato tikam lutut ko sémba di Dia pung muka. Dong satu-satu ada pegang alat musik sama ke sasando, deng satu mangko mas, yang ta'isi deng kamanyán yang dong bakar ko bekin asap wangi. Itu dara kayu wangi tu, andia Tuhan pung orang dong pung sambayang.<bt>When He took it, then those four extra-ordinary animals there, and those 24 elders there, fell kneeling in front of Him. They each one held a musical instrument like a sasando, and a golden bowl, which was filled with resin which they burned to make sweet smelling smoke. That sweet smelling resin there, it was the Lord's people's prayers. [EXEG: Is it incense = prayers? or bowls = prayers? Ex. Summ. #2 grammatical agreement favours “bowls” here. But NIGTC points out 8:3-4 equates prayers = incense, and Ex.Summ #1 goes there for this verse. None of the sources discuss the possibility of the higher level “golden bowls full of incense” = prayers (but then they rarely get above the microscopic level); I think (CEG) the incense is burning by implication, and the smoke rising is symbolically the prayers going up to God -- evoking other passages of scripture, but without explicit textual support here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="why use kemenyan?? dara kayu wangi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">why use kemenyan?? dara kayu wangi</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 141:2</note><v n="9" />Ais dong samua manyanyi satu lagu baru bilang:<bt>Then they all sang a new song, saying:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Domba Ana ni, yang pantas tarima ini tulisan.<bt>“The Sheep Offspring here, is the one who is appropriate to receive this writing.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Domba Ana ni, yang pung hak ko buka dia pung segel.<bt>The Sheep Offspring here, is the one who has right to open its seals.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Te Dia su kaná horo.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) He has been (ritually) slaughtered.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ais Tuhan Allah pake Dia pung dara,<bt>Then God used His blood,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko tabús ame manusia dari samua suku deng bangsa,<bt>to redeem human from every tribe and ethnic group,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ko hapus manusia pung sala. Deng"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">ko hapus manusia pung sala. Deng bagitu, manusia dari samua suku deng bangsa</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko biar dong saparu bisa jadi Tuhan pung orang.<bt>so that some of them can become God2's people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Deng bagitu, manusia dari samua bahasa deng negara,<bt>Because of that, humans from every language and country,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">bisa jadi Tuhan pung kelu.<bt>can become the Lord's family.</bt><note reference="5:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 33:3, 98:1, Yesaya 42:10</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="10" />Domba Ana ni, su kumpul sang dong samua,<bt>The Sheep Offspring here, has gathered them all together,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">jadi satu karaja'an.<bt>to become a kingdom.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Domba Ana ni, su pili sang dong,<bt>The Sheep Offspring here, has chosen them,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">jadi Tuhan pung orang karjá dong.<bt>to become the Lord's workers.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nanti dong pegang parenta di dunya.<bt>Later they will rule in the world.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nanti dong karjá kasi Tuhan di bumi.&gt;&gt;<bt>Later they will serve God on the earth.” [NOTE to daughter translations: this is a recurring phrase “kingdom of priests”; KM is undertranslated here, but to bring it out skews the focus. See if you can bring it out a little better in your translation.]</bt><note reference="5:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 19:6, 1 Petrus 2:5,9, Dunya Model Baru 1:6</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ais itu, beta angka muka, ju beta dengar satu suara bésar. Deng beta lia itu 4 binatang luar biasa, deng itu 24 katua tu, tamba deng Tuhan pung ana bua bam-banya dari sorga. Itu ana bua dong pung banya tu, sampe juta-juta.<bt>After that, I lifted my face and I heard a loud voice. And I saw those four extra-ordinary animals there, and those 24 elders there, added together with many of God's angels from heaven. Those angel's amount there, was up to millions and millions.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="myriádes myriádoon, kaì khiliádes khiliádoon: ten"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">myriádes myriádoon, kaì khiliádes khiliádoon: ten thousands of ten thousands, and thousands of thousands -- super big number, too many to even try to count</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 7:10</note><v n="12" />Dong samua manyanyi deng suara karás bilang,<bt>They all sang with a loud voice saying, [NOTE: TB /nyaring/ ‘piercing, shrieking, high pitched’, is incorrect here.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Botong angka tinggi-tinggi itu Domba Ana yang kaná horo,<bt>“We lift up high that Sheep Offspring who (ritually) slaughtered there,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">tagal Dia yang pantas tarima botong pung puji!<bt>Because He is appropriate to receive our praise!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia pung kuasa tu, paling bésar.<bt>That power/authority of his, is exceedingly big.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia pung harta tu, talalu banya.<bt>That wealth of his, is very much.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia pung akal tu, jitu talalu.<bt>That thinking of his, extremely hits the mark.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia pung kuat tu, hebat batúl.<bt>That strength of his, is truly amazing. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Botong angka tinggi-tinggi Dia pung nama.<bt>We lift up high His name/reputation.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Botong kasi hormat sang Dia.<bt>We give honor to Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Botong puji-puji sang Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>We praise Him.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ais itu, beta dengar satu lagu laen lai. Dari samua-samua yang idop, mau di sorga, di langit, di bumi, deng di dalam laut, dong samua angka suara ko manyanyi. Dari orang mati pung tampa ju, dong iko manyanyi. Dong samua rame-rame manyanyi bilang,<bt>After that, I heard yet another song. Everything that live, in heaven, in the sky, on the earth, and in the sea, they all lifted up their voices to sing. From the dead people's place also, they followed along singing. They all sang with great enthusiasm saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Botong puji sang Tuhan Allah yang ada dudu di ini korsi parenta ni.<bt>“We praise God who sits on this ruling chair here.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Botong ju angka tinggi-tinggi sang ini Domba Ana ni.<bt>We also lift up high this Sheep Offspring here.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Botong kasi hormat sang Dong.<bt>We give respect to Them. [EXEG: Gk: glory here, undertranslated because of the inadequacies of Kupang.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Botong sémba sang Dong,<bt>We worship Them,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal Dong yang pegang parenta tarús-tarús,<bt>because They are the Ones who rule forever,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng Dong pung kuasa sonde tau abis-abis na!&gt;&gt;<bt>and Their power/authority never run out!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tà en autóis pánta: all the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">tà en autóis pánta: all the things in all these places</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ais, itu 4 binatang luar biasa tu, manyao tarús-tarús bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl tu! Su batúl tu!&gt;&gt; Ju itu 24 katua dong jato tikam lutut lai ko sémba sang Tuhan Allah deng itu Domba Ana.<bt>Then those four extra-ordinary animals there, replied over and over saying, “That's true! It's true!” And those 24 elders fell kneeling again to worship God and that Sheep Offspring.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Domba Ana buka itu segel dong satu-satu [\s2] Segel nomer satu -- kapala paráng kaluar datang<bt>The Sheep Offspring opens each of those seals [\bts2] Seal number one -- a war leader comes out</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="6" />
      <v n="1" />Ais itu, beta dapa lia itu Domba Ana buka itu tulisan tagulung pung segel yang partama. Ju beta dengar satu dari itu 4 binatang luar biasa batarea deng suara karás sama ke guntur. Dia parenta bilang, &lt;&lt;Pi su!&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, I saw that Sheep Offspring open that rolled writing's first seal. Then I heard one of those four extra-ordinary animals there yell with a loud voice like thunder. He commanded saying, “Go!” [EXEG: Trans Handbook: the ‘go’ is to the horseman. See note on Gk /érkhou/ not “come up to the sky” but “come on the scene”, “start to do your thing”, “get going”, “Go”, which in the Timor region is best expressed as “go!”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="érkhou: not &quot;come up to the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">érkhou: not "come up to the sky" but "come on the scene", "start to do your thing", "get going", "Go".</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Takuju sa beta dapa lia satu kuda puti. Ada satu orang dudu di atas pake topi kapala paráng, tagal dia manáng tarús dalam paráng. Sakarang dia su pegang pana, deng kaluar ko pi kasi kala lai dia pung musu di bumi.<bt>Suddenly/unexpectedly I saw a white horse. There was a person sitting on top wearing a war captain's hat, because He continually conquered in war. Now He was holding a bow, and going out to go defeat again his enemies on earth. [EXEG: none of the sources discuss “going out (from where)?” It is assumed to be a generic “going forth to battle”.] [NOTE to daughter translations: if bow-arrow is not known or is not used, or is only used for hunting, but not a symbol of war, then use “sharp weapons” /sanjata (tajam)/.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nikoon: not &quot;fighta&quot;, because that's a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">nikoon: not "fighta", because that's a boxer. "Military person" conveys a better image.</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Sakaria 1:8, 6:3, 6</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Segel nomer dua -- kaco di bumi [\s2]<bt>Seal number two -- chaos on earth [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ais, itu Domba Ana buka segel nomer dua. Ju beta dengar binatang luar biasa yang nomer dua parenta bilang, &lt;&lt;Pi su!&gt;&gt;<bt>Afterwards, that Sheep Offspring opened seal number two. And I heard the number two extra-ordinary animal command saying, “Go!”</bt><v n="4" />Ais ju satu kuda mera manyala kaluar datang. Orang yang dudu di atas, ada tarima satu kalewang bésar. Dong kasi kuasa sang dia ko pi bekin kaco di bumi, ko biar manusia dong babunu satu deng satu.<bt>And then a shiny/flaming red horse came out. The person who sat on top accepted a big fighting sword. They gave him power/authority to go make chaos on earth, so that humans would kill each other.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="exéelthen: doesn't imply that the horses"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">exéelthen: doesn't imply that the horses were inside some enclosure and then came outside, but more like they each sallied forth to do their thing pyrrós: flame red, fiery red<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="6:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Sakaria 1:8, 6:2</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Segel nomer tiga -- musim lapar yang hebat [\s2]<bt>Seal number three -- an extreme famine [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Tarús, itu Domba Ana buka segel nomer tiga. Ju beta dengar binatang luar biasa yang nomer tiga parenta bilang, &lt;&lt;Pi su!&gt;&gt; Takuju sa beta dapa lia satu kuda itam. Orang yang dudu di atas itu kuda, ada pegang satu timbangan di dia pung tangan, ko mau timbang makanan yang su mulai bakurang.<bt>Next, that Sheep Offspring opened seal number three. And I heard the extra-ordinary animal number three command saying, “Go!” Suddenly/unexpectedly I saw a black horse. The person who was sitting on that horse, was holding a scale in his hand, to weigh food which had started to be lacking.</bt><note reference="6:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Sakaria 6:2, 6</note><v n="6" />Ais ju beta dengar tingka ke ada satu suara yang datang dari itu 4 binatang luar biasa pung teng-tenga. Itu suara kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Nanti ada musim lapar yang hebat di bumi. Orang pung gaji satu hari, cuma mampu béli barás tiga mok; barás bagus, na, cuma dapa satu mok sa. Ma nanti kalo itu musim lapar su sampe, orang sonde bole bekin rusak pohon saitun deng pohon anggor di kabón dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>And then I heard as if there was a voice that came from the middle of those extra-ordinary animals. The voice explained saying, “Later there will be an intense hunger season on earth. A person's one day wage, will only be enough to buy three measuring tins of rice; and as for good rice, na, only enough for just one measuring tin. But later when that famine arrives, people are not allowed to destroy the olive trees and the grape trees/bushes in the gardens.” [EXEG: how do oil &amp; wine become olive trees and vines? Ex.Summ. has fairly widespread agreement that it is metonymy for the source here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ Rethink translation of barley; jagong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">@@ Rethink translation of barley; jagong rote would be better to convey status difference *** added ftn 2007</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="khóinix: a quart of flour, about"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">khóinix: a quart of flour, about two pounds. This is is ten times the ordinary price deenaríou: a Roman coin that was the regular pay for working all day at field labor. Like a dollar a day in the cane field<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>meè adikeéseeis: don't wrong the oil and the wine, don't ruin the supply of oil or wine; don't adulterate the oil or the wine (less probable in the money context - it sounds more like famine conditions for supply and demand at outrageous prices)</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:6" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Di itu da'era orang dong idop dari itu dua pohon. Jadi biar musim lapar talalu hebat, asal itu dua pohon masi ada, orang dong masi bisa idop tarús.<bt>In that region people live(d) from those two types of trees [NOTE: =important part of life and culture, like lontar tree for Rote and Sabu people; similar phrasing used to talk about it]. So (consequently), even if the famine is severe, as long as they still have those two trees, people can still continue to live.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Segel nomer ampa -- banya orang mati [\s2]<bt>Seal number four -- many people die [\s2]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** title adjusted Sept 2005"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** title adjusted Sept 2005</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ais, itu Domba Ana buka segel nomer ampa. Ju beta dengar binatang luar biasa yang nomer ampa parenta bilang, &lt;&lt;Pi su!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then that Sheep Offspring opened seal number four. And I hear extra-ordinary animal number four command saying, “Go!”</bt><v n="8" />Takuju, beta dapa lia satu kuda warna kuning pucat. Orang yang dudu di atas itu kuda, dia pung nama &lt;Mati&gt;. Ada ju yang iko dia pung balakang, dia pung nama &lt;Tampa Orang Mati Dong&gt;. Ais dong dua dapa kuasa ko pi bunu bekin mati orang di bumi pake kalewang, musim lapar, panyaki, deng pake binatang buas. Kalo itong dong samua yang mati tu, dia pung banya sama deng satu bagian dari ampa bagian samua manusia di bumi.<bt>Suddenly, I saw a pale yellow horse. The person sitting on top of that horse, his name was &lt;Death&gt;. There was also one who went behind him, his name &lt;Place of Dead People&gt;. Then the two of them were given authority to go kill people on earth using swords, famine, sickness, and wild animals. If we count all those who died, the sum is the same as one part from four parts of all the humans on earth. [NOTE to daughter translations: Gk here tends toward ‘light green’ ‘pale greenish gray’, so do your colour research, not just blindly going with an equivalent of /kuning pucat/. Colour systems in the Timor region vary widely.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="khloorós: ghastly greenish, like the mummy"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">khloorós: ghastly greenish, like the mummy in the monster movie. Sickly pale, corpse color. Careful that "no mo color" doesn't get confused with "no mo kala!" R</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 14:21</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Segel nomer lima -- Tuhan pung orang dong tunggu ko Dia putus dong pung parkara [\s2]<bt>Seal number five -- God's people wait for Him to decide their cases [\s2]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***suggestion from Helong check &gt; orang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">***suggestion from Helong check &gt; orang &gt; saksi??</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ais, itu Domba Ana buka segel nomer lima. Ju beta dapa lia orang-orang yang dolu su kaná bunu. Dong pung jiwa ada di kolong meja korban. Dong kaná bunu tagal dong parcaya sang Tuhan Allah, deng carita pi mana-mana Dia pung Kata-kata.<bt>Then, that Sheep Offspring opened seal number five. And I saw the people who had previously been murdered. Thier sould were under the sacrificing table. They were murdered because they believed God, and told His Words everywhere.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hypokátoo: underneath, or at the base"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">hypokátoo: underneath, or at the base in this case psychàs: souls or spirits of the departed. Not ghosts or obake spirits; this is positive -- the living personalities of many Christians who had been killed for their faith, and now are with God, but without the new body God plans to give them yet<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Dong batarea bilang, &lt;&lt;Oo, Tuhan! Botong pung Bos yang paling hebat! Bos yang barisi! Apa yang Tuhan omong, botong parcaya. Ma botong musti tunggu sampe kapan lai, baru Tuhan putus parkara ko hukum itu orang dong yang bunu sang botong di bumi?&gt;&gt;<bt>They yelled out saying, “O God2! Our-exc Boss who is exceedingly amazing! Boss who is holy! What ever the Lord (=you) say, we believe. [NOTE: =faithful, we know you will do it.] But how long must we wait, until the Lord decides the litigation in order to punish those people who murdered us on earth?”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added on “faithful”"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** (2009) note added on “faithful”</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ho despótees: slave owner, master, in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">ho despótees: slave owner, master, in this case very much like Almighty God héoos póte: not a request for a timetable, but a demand for action - "Please don't wait any longer!"<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>ekdikéis: get even, settle accounts, right the wrong</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Dong tanya abis bagitu, ju dong satu-satu tarima baju puti panjang. Ada yang kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Tunggu sadiki lai, sampe bosong pung jumla su langkáp. Te masi ada bosong pung sodara dong yang nanti kaná bunu sama ke bosong.&gt;&gt;<bt>They finished asking like that, then they each one received a white robe/dress/shirt. There was someone who told them saying, “Wait a bit longer, until your total is complete. Cuz (elaboration) there are still your siblings who will later be murdered the same as you.” [NOTE to daughter translations: if /langkáp/ causes difficulties, try alternate /Tunggu sadiki lai, te masi ada bosong pung sodara dong yang nanti kaná bunu sama ke bosong. Tunggu sampe dong samua su kaná bunu, baru beta kasi hukum itu orang dong yang bunu sang bosong./]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="leukeé: white clothes (Rev 3:4-5 &quot;dat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">leukeé: white clothes (Rev 3:4-5 "dat no ack pilau, jalike dey get clean clotheses. Dey da guys dat goin walk wit me an wear white kine clotheses, cuz dey get da right fo do dat. Everybody dat fight an win ova da bad kine stuff, dey goin wear white kine clotheses lidat.") to show purity and victory</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Segel nomer anam -- calaka di langit deng di bumi [\s2]<bt>Seal number six -- disaster in the sky and on earth [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ais, itu Domba Ana buka segel nomer anam. Takuju sa, beta dapa lia tana goyang yang bésar. Ju matahari jadi galáp sama ke kaen itam, deng bulan jadi mera sama ke dara.<bt>Then, that Sheep Offspring opened seal number six. Suddenly, I saw a big earthquake. And the sun became dark like a black cloth and the moon became red like blood.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sákkos tríkhinos: sacking cloth made from"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">sákkos tríkhinos: sacking cloth made from black goat hair, worn to show extreme grief or dismay, similar to knocking out one's own teeth or cutting off one's own finger joints in parts of the Pacific. But the goats here are brown, and mourning is shown in some of the ethnic groups by white, and is not symbolized in others. Change the figure to something sinister.<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="6:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 11:13, 16:18, Yesaya 13:10, Yoel 2:10, 31, 3:15, Mateos 24:29, Markus 13:24-25, Lukas 21:25</note><v n="13" />Bintang-bintang di langit dong jato turun di bumi, sama ke bua manta yang jato dari pohon tagal angin karás.<bt>The stars in the sky fell down to the earth, like unripe fruit that falls from a tree because of hard/strong wind. [EXEG: Gk <span class="Italic">olunthous </span>‘late fig, winter fig, unripe fruit’ that often falls before ripening. LN, TH, NLT; note CEV is undertranslated. (LJ)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** manta &gt; masak"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** manta &gt; masak</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anémou megálou: this would be about"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">anémou megálou: this would be about a gale force wind, not quite a hurricane but plenty dangerous on land or sea. Not a local wind like a whistling wind or Lahainaluna wind or one of the others that have special names</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-10-23 01:00:39Z">Gk</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Ju beta dapa lia langit tapica bagi dua, ko tagulung sama ke tikar sampe ilang. Ju gunung-gunung deng pulo-pulo dong samua tagoyang sampe ilang buang dari dong pung tampa.<bt>And I saw the sky split divide in two, to roll up like a mat until it disappeared. And the mountains and the islands all shook until they disappeared completely from their place.</bt><note reference="6:13-14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 34:4; Dunya Model Baru 16:20</note><v n="15" />Lia bagitu, ju samua orang di bumi, mulai dari raja-raja, kapala pamarenta, komandán tantara, orang kaya, sampe budak dong, dong samua jadi taku. Ais dong lari sambunyi di lobang-lobang goa deng di calá-calá batu di gunung.<bt>Seeing like that, then all the people on earth from the rajas to the government heads, military commanders, rich people, until even slaves, they all become afraid. Then they all ran to hide in holes in caves and in gaps in the rocks in the mountains.</bt><note reference="6:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 2:19, 21</note><v n="16" />Dong suru sang gunung-gunung deng batu bésar dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Biar jato ko tutu ame sang botong su! Sambunyi sang botong ko Dia yang dudu di atas itu korsi parenta bésar tu, sonde bisa dapa lia sang botong lai. Deng itu Domba Ana sonde bisa hukum sang botong lai.<bt>They commanded the mountains and the big rocks saying, “(Go ahead and) fall to cover over us! Hide us so that He who sits on that big ruling chair there, can't see us anymore. And that Sheep Offspring can't judge us anymore. [EXEG: they are so terrified of God's wrath that they would prefer to be crushed. See Ex. Summ.]</bt><note reference="6:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Hosea 10:8, Lukas 23:30</note><v n="17" />Aduu! Botong su para-para ni, te hari calaka su datang! Tuhan Allah deng itu Domba Ana su mau po'a dong pung mara sang botong. Ma sonde ada yang bisa sili lai!&gt;&gt;<bt>Aduu! (remorse/regret) We-exc are in big trouble here, cuz (elaboration) the calamity day/s has arrived! God and that Sheep Offspring are wanting to pour out their anger on us. And there is no one who can avoid/survive it anymore.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NOTE to daughter translations: sili in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">NOTE to daughter translations: sili in sense of endure/survive ; sili = survive</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yoel 2:11, Maleaki 3:2</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Allah cap ame 144.000 orang<bt>God stamps 144.000 people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="7" />
      <v n="1" />Ais itu, beta dapa lia Tuhan pung ana bua ampa dari sorga ada badiri di bumi pung ampa mata angin ko tahan angin. Ais ju angin sonde bisa fuu di laut, di darat, deng fuu pi pohon-pohon dong.<bt>After that, I saw four angels from heaven standing on the earth's four sources of wind in order to constrain the wind. And so the wind could not blow on the sea, on the land and blow on the trees.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="meta touto: after that episode. This"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">meta touto: after that episode. This is a different vision</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeremia 49:36, Daniel 7:2, Sakaria 6:5</note><v n="2" />Tuhan su kasi kuasa sang dong ko bekin ancor darat deng laut. Ais beta dapa lia satu ana bua laen dari sorga, datang dari tampa matahari nae. Dia ada bawa cap dari Tuhan Allah yang idop tarús. Ju dia batarea kasi tau sang itu ampa ana bua bilang,<bt>God had given power to them to destroy the land and sea. Then I saw another angel from heaven, come from the place the sun comes up (=east). He was bring the stamp/seal from God who live continually. Then he shouted out telling those four angels saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sphragíida: not a seal on a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">sphragíida: not a seal on a document, as in the preceding chapter. This was a signet ring or chop, used to put an identifying mark on God's people. Nowadays they stamp your hand at Aloha Stadium or Waikiki Shell. A carved stone was usually used in those days to make an impression on a blob of wax, or in this case, to put ink on somebody's skin ékraxen phoonéei megáleei: he shouted with a loud voice<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>thálassan: any large body of water, salt or fresh</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />&lt;&lt;Tunggu dolo! Jang bekin rusak darat ko, laut ko, pohon-pohon dong. Tunggu sampe botong su taro cap di Tuhan pung orang suru-suru dong pung testa.&gt;&gt;<bt>“Wait! Don't destroy the land or sea or trees. Wait until we-exc have put a stamp on God's servants' foreheads.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sphragísoomen: the angel who is talking"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">sphragísoomen: the angel who is talking and his associates, but not the four angels in charge of controlling the winds</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 9:4, 6</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ais dong kasi tau sang beta bilang, itu ana bua su cap ame Tuhan pung orang. Dong pung banya tu, ada 144.000 orang, yang datang dari samua suku Isra'el. Andia:<bt>Then they told me that angel had stamped God's people. Their amount/total were 144.000 people, who came from all the clans of Israel. They were:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="5" />dari suku Yahuda, ada 12.000 orang;<bt>from clan Yahuda, there were 12.000 people;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">suku Ruben, 12.000 orang;<bt>clan Ruben, 12.000 people;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">suku Gad, 12.000 orang;<bt>clan Gad, 12.000 people;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="6" />suku Aser, 12.000 orang;<bt>clan Aser, 12.000 people;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">suku Naftali, 12.000 orang;<bt>clan Naftali, 12.000 people;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">suku Manase, 12.000 orang;<bt>clan Manase, 12.000 people;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="7" />suku Simeon, 12.000 orang;<bt>clan Simeon, 12.000 people;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">suku Lewi, 12.000 orang;<bt>clan Lewi, 12.000 people;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">suku Isaskar, 12.000 orang;<bt>clan Isaskar, 12.000 people;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="8" />suku Sebulon, 12.000 orang;<bt>clan Sebulon, 12.000 people;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">suku Yusuf, 12.000 orang;<bt>clan Yusuf, 12.000 people;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng dari suku Benyamin, 12.000 orang.<bt>and from clan Benyamin, 12,000 people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang barisi dong puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah deng Domba Ana<bt>The holy/clean people praise God and the Sheep Offspring</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ais ju beta dapa lia manusia bam-banya, sampe sonde bisa itong sang dong samua. Dong datang dari samua suku, samua bangsa, samua bahasa, deng samua negara di bumi. Dong samua bakumpul mangada itu korsi parenta deng itu Domba Ana. Dong pake baju puti deng ada pegang daon palam di dong pung tangan.<bt>After that, I saw many people, to the point that they all could not be counted. They came from every clan/tribe, every ethnic group/race, and every language/speech community, and every country on earth. They all gathered facing that ruling chair and that Sheep Offspring. They all wore white clothes and were holding palm leaves in their hands.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="éidon: another separate vision phoínikes: palm"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">éidon: another separate vision phoínikes: palm branches. A sign of celebration and happiness, like when Jesus went into Jerusalem. Sounds like a victory parade<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dong datang dari samua bangsa, samua"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Dong datang dari samua bangsa, samua suku, samua kaum, deng samua bahasa di bumi.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Ais dong angka puji rame-rame bilang,<bt>Then they all enthusiastically lifted up praises saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Botong puji-puji sang botong pung Tuhan Allah,<bt>“We praise1 and praise2 our God,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">yang ada dudu di korsi parenta ni.<bt>who is sitting on this ruling chair here.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Botong ju angka tinggi-tinggi ini Domba Ana ni!<bt>We also lift up high this Sheep Offspring here!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dong ni, yang kasi salamat sang botong.<bt>They here, are who give salvation to us.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dong ni, yang buka jalan idop kasi sang botong.&gt;&gt;<bt>They here, are who open the path of life for us.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hee sooteería tóoi theóoi: victory? salvation?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">hee sooteería tóoi theóoi: victory? salvation? but why the dative case? "associated with"? Check B-D grammar. Nothing in Blass-Debrunner under Dative, unless it is "Salvation has to do with our God" as a loose associative, but there are no good parallels. Might it be a calque on "hosanna"?<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Dong omong abis bagitu, ju Tuhan pung ana bua dari sorga yang badiri kuliling itu korsi parenta dong, jato tikam lutut sampe dong pung muka kaná di tana mangada pi itu korsi parenta bésar. Itu katua dong, deng itu 4 binatang luar biasa dong, bekin bagitu ju. Dong samua sémba sang Tuhan Allah,<bt>They finished speaking like that, then the angels who stood around those ruling chairs, knelt until their faces hit the ground in front of that big/main ruling chair. Those elders, and those four extra-ordinary animals, also did like that. They all worship God</bt><v n="12" />deng manyanyi bilang,<bt>and singing saying, [EXEG: NRSV]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Batúl! Batúl tu!<bt>“Correct! That's correct!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Botong ju puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah!<bt>We also praise and praise the Lord God!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Botong ju angka tinggi-tinggi Tuhan pung nama!<bt>We also lift up high the Lord's name/reputation!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tuhan pung akal tu, jitu talalu.<bt>That idea/s of God's, hit the mark/ are extremely perceptive.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tuhan pung kuasa tu, bésar talalu.<bt>That power/authority of God's, is very big.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tuhan pung kuat tu, hebat talalu.<bt>That strength of God's, is exceeding amazing. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Botong minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan tarús-tarús.<bt>We reciprocate thankyou to God continually.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Botong kasi hormat sang Tuhan sonde putus-putus.<bt>We give honour to God without ever ending.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Batúl! Andia tu!&gt;&gt;<bt>That's right! That's how it is!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="datives: again, this appears to be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">datives: again, this appears to be something people are giving to God, not a statement about his attributes. OR, they are recognizing his attributes, like "bless God" is recognizing and thanking him for the blessings he gives.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Dong puji-puji abis bagitu, ju dari itu 24 katua dong, ada satu yang tanya sang beta bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini orang banya yang ada pake baju puti ni, lu kanál sang dong, ko? Dong tu, dari mana?&gt;&gt;<bt>They finished praising like that, then from those 24 elders there was one who asked me saying, “These many people here who are wearing white clothes, you know them, [+tag question, expecting yes answer]? Where are they from?”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ma beta manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde, pak. Beta sonde kanál dong tu, sapa. Pak yang lebe tau.&gt;&gt;<bt>But I replied saying, “No, Father/Mr. I don't know/recognise who they are. Mr. would know better.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju dia kasi tau sang beta bilang, &lt;&lt;Dong tu, orang yang su kaluar datang dari sangsara bésar.<bt>Then he told me saying, “They there, are the people who have come out of the big suffering.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lolos?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">lolos?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dong tu, orang yang su pake itu Domba Ana pung dara,<bt>They there, are the people who used that Sheep Offspring's blood,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko cuci dong pung pakean,<bt>to wash their clothes,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng bekin puti barisi dong pung baju.<bt>to make clean white their shirts/robes.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thlípseoos: they lived through a time"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">thlípseoos: they lived through a time of extraordinary distress; they are the survivors. Probably not just any big trouble, but the Tribulation or, the whole church age.</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 12:1, Mateos 24:21, Markus 13:19</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="15" />Tagal itu, dong badiri di muka Tuhan Allah pung korsi parenta.<bt>Because of that, they stand in front of God's ruling chair.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dong layani sang Tuhan siang-malam di Dia pung Ruma Sambayang.<bt>They serve God day-night in His Worship House. [EXEG: NLT]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tuhan ada deng dong tarús-tarús.<bt>God is continually with them.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tuhan jaga sang dong tarús-tarús.<bt>God continually protects them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="skeenoósei: spread his tent over them"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">skeenoósei: spread his tent over them [and protect them], shelter them with his presence</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="16" />Nanti dong sonde rasa lapar lai.<bt>In the future they will not feel hungry anymore.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nanti dong sonde rasa aus lai.<bt>In the future they will not feel thirsty anymore.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Nanti dong sonde kaná tabakar dari matahari lai.<bt>In the future they will not be burnt by the sun anymore.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Nanti dong pung kulit sonde takupas kaná panas lai.<bt>In the future their skin will not peel being adversely affected by heat anymore.</bt><note reference="7:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 49:10</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="17" />Itu Domba Ana yang badeka deng itu korsi parenta,<bt>That Sheep Offspring who is close to that ruling chair there,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">nanti Dia yang jadi dong pung gambala.<bt>In the future He will become their shepherd.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nanti Dia foo bawa sang dong,<bt>In the future He will herd lead them,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">pi minum di mata aer yang bawa idop.<bt>to go drink at the source of water that brings life. [NOTE: this phrasing is what we use in other Yohannine writings. NLT, CEV]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nanti Tuhan ju hapus buang dong pung susa,<bt>In the future God will also wipe away their difficulties,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko dong sonde manangis lai.&gt;&gt;<bt>so that they do not cry anymore.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="poimanéi: used of the shepherd; but"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">poimanéi: used of the shepherd; but here the Lamb is the shepherd</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 23:1-2, Yeskial 34:23, Yesaya 49:10, Yesaya 25:8</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Segel nomer tuju -- Tuhan pung ana bua dong tarima ame tuju tarompet<bt>Seal number seven -- angels receive seven trumpets</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="8" />
      <v n="1" />Ais, itu Domba Ana buka segel nomer tuju. Takuju sa, samua yang ada di sorga diam tapaku. Sonde ada yang basuara sampe kira-kira satenga jam.<bt>Then, that Sheep Offspring opened seal number seven. Suddenly, everything in heaven was dead quiet. There was nothing that voiced/made.a.noise for approximately half an hour.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="diam tapaku = dead quiet"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">diam tapaku = dead quiet</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="seventh seal: the last seal. silence"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">seventh seal: the last seal. silence for half hour: emphasizes the importance of what was happening.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Ais beta dapa lia tuju ana bua dari sorga yang ada badiri tarús-tarús di Tuhan Allah pung muka, ko dong siap layani sang Dia. Dong satu-satu tarima dia pung tarompet.<bt>Then I saw seven angels continually standing in front of God so that they are ready to serve Him. They each one receive a trumpet.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Luke 1:9"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Luke 1:9</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="horn or trumpet: The Biblical trumpet"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">horn or trumpet: The Biblical trumpet could be a ram's horn. Modern trumpets are brass wind instruments. There is no way to know which the writer meant. But "horn" nowadays is "car horn," so they'd better be trumpets.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ais satu ana bua dari sorga yang laen pi badiri di muka itu meja yang dong pake bakar dara kayu wangi. Dia ada pegang satu mangko mas, yang dong biasa pake ko taro dara kayu wangi. Ais dong kasi sang dia dara kayu wangi bam-banya, ko dia campor deng Tuhan Allah pung orang dong pung sambayang. Ais dia bawa itu mangko mas sama ke korban yang baboo wangi, ko taro di atas itu meja mas di itu korsi parenta pung muka.<bt>Then one of the other angels went to stand in front of that table which they use to burn resin. He was holding a golden bowl, which they usually used to put resin. They gave him lots of resin, to mix with God's people's prayers. Then he took that golden bowl as a sacrifice which smelled fragrant to place it on top of the gold table in front of that ruling chair.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="censer: small golden bowl or pan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">censer: small golden bowl or pan in which incense was burned. It had a handle so the priest could hold it and carry it to the altar (1 Kings 7:50). He was given much incense: God, an angel, or somebody gave him, or he received.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="8:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Amos 9:1, Kaluar dari Masir 30:1, 3</note><v n="4" />Tarús dia bakar itu dara kayu wangi. Ju dia pung bau wangi nae pi Tuhan Allah pung muka, sama-sama deng samua do'a dari Tuhan pung orang dong.<bt>Next he burned that resin. And it's fragrant smell went up in front of God, together with all of the prayers from God's people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ais, itu ana bua ame api dari itu meja, ko taro bekin ponu itu mangko mas. Tarús dia lempar buang itu mangko pi bumi. Takuju sa, beta lia ada kilat yang basambar kiri-kanan di bumi. Tarús ada guntur yang babunyi bésar basambung, deng ada tana tagoyang bésar.<bt>Then, that angel took fire from that table, in order to fill up that gold bowl. Next he threw that bowl away on to the earth. Unexpectedly/immediately, I saw lightening striking out left-right on the earth. And loud sounding thunder followed, and there was a big earthquake. [NOTE to daughter translations: #1 check “take fire” (like getting fire sticks from the neighbours), #2 does “fire” collocate with “fill up”.]</bt><note reference="8:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 16:12, Yeskial 10:2, Kaluar dari Masir 19:16, Dunya Model Baru 11:19, 16:18</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ais, itu tuju ana bua dari sorga dong siap-siap ko mau tiop dong pung tarompet.<bt>Then, those seven angels got ready to blow their trumpets.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tiop tarompet nomer satu -- tanaman tabakar [\s2]<bt>Trumpet number one -- plants are burned [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Waktu ana bua nomer satu tiop dia pung tarompet, ju ujan es deng api yang bacampor deng dara, jato tapo'a pi bumi. Samua rumput ijo tabakar abis di mana-mana. Kalo kotong bagi bumi jadi tiga bagian, na, yang tabakar tu, satu bagian. Deng kalo kotong bagi samua pohon di bumi jadi tiga bagian, na, yang tabakar tu, satu bagian.<bt>When the first angel blew his trumpet, then ice rain and fire mixed with blood, fell pouring down on the earth. All the green grass was burned up everywhere. If we-inc divide the earth into three parts, na, what was burned up, was one part. If we-inc divide all the trees on the earth into three parts, na, what was burned up, was one part. [DISCOURSE: reordered for info flow: all grass, 1/3 of earth, 1/3 of trees/plants.] [EXEG: TH]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="1/3 world destroyed, completely destroying tree"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">1/3 world destroyed, completely destroying tree etc on that part = THandbook ***revised 2007</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hail: extremely rare in Hawaii; most"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">hail: extremely rare in Hawaii; most people have never seen it. Ice is common, sold by the bag triteen: "one third" is homophonous with an expression that would be unacceptable in church. It has to be "thirty-three percent" in order to not offend or amuse or be totally misunderstood. Percentages and round numbers are a fact of life in a society where people pay taxes and look for discounts.<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Waktu ana bua nomer satu tiop"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Waktu ana bua nomer satu tiop dia pung tarompet, ju ujan es deng api yang bacampor deng dara, jato tapo'a pi di bumi, sampe pohon-pohon deng tanaman-tanaman dong tabakar. Rumput ju tabakar. Kalo kotong bagi samua pohon deng tanaman di bumi jadi tiga bagian, na, yang tabakar tu, satu bagian.</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 9:23-25, Yeskial 38:22</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tiop tarompet nomer dua -- laut pung isi mati [\s2]<bt>Trumpet number two -- the contents of the sea die [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Waktu ana bua nomer dua tiop dia pung tarompet, ju ada satu barang sama ke gunung bésar yang manyala, talempar maso pi dalam laut, sampe satu dari tiga bagian di laut jadi dara.<bt>When angel number two blew his trumpet, then a thing like a big mountain that was burning, was thrown into the sea, until one of three parts in the sea became blood. [NOTE: versification in NRSV off from Gk here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="**fixed Sep 2005 one-third of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">**fixed Sep 2005 one-third of the sea became blood; changed bits in which verse to reflect Greek</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Ais satu dari tiga bagian dari samua binatang yang idop di laut, mati abis. Deng satu dari tiga bagian dari samua kapal yang balayar di laut, ju ancor buang.<bt>Then one of three parts of all the animals that live in the sea, died off. And one of three parts of all the ships that were sailing in the sea also were completely destroyed.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="jumla ; **fixed Sep 2005; 1/3"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">jumla ; **fixed Sep 2005; 1/3 creatures destroyed, 1/3 ships destroyed<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais samua binatang laut yang ada"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Ais samua binatang laut yang ada di situ, mati abis. Deng samua kapal yang balayar di situ ju, ancor abis. Kalo kotong bagi samua laut di bumi jadi tiga bagian, na, yang jadi dara tu, satu bagian.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tarompet nomer tiga -- aer jadi pait [\s2]<bt>Trumpet number three -- water becomes bitter [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10-11" />Waktu ana bua nomer tiga tiop dia pung tarompet, ju ada satu bintang bésar jato dari langit, sama ke satu obor bésar yang manyala. Itu bintang pung nama &lt;Pait&gt;. Waktu dia jato, ju aer di kali deng mata aer jadi pait. Ais orang yang minum itu aer, ada banya yang mati. Kalo kotong bagi samua kali deng mata aer di bumi jadi tiga bagian, na, yang jadi pait tu, satu bagian.<bt>When angel number three blew his trumpet, then a big star fell from the sky, like a big torch that was burning. That star's name was ‘Bitter’. When it fell, then rivers and springs became bitter. Then of the people who drank that water, there were many who died. If we divide all the rivers and springs in the world into three parts, na, those who became bitter, were one part.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Wormwood: named after a bitter drug"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Wormwood: named after a bitter drug made from a plant with a certain smell. The drug is not poisonous, but it was considered poisonous. Harsh tasting.</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:10-11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 14:12, Yeremia 9:15</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tarompet nomer ampa -- matahari, bulan, deng bintang jadi galáp [\s2]<bt>Trumpet number four -- sun, moon, and stars become dark [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ais, itu ana bua nomer ampa tiop dia pung tarompet. Takuju matahari, bulan, deng bintang dong kaná pukul, ju dong jadi galáp. Jadi pas siang hari, satu bagian dari tiga bagian waktu siang jadi galáp, tagal matahari su sonde basinar batúl lai. Deng pas malam hari, satu bagian dari tiga bagian waktu malam jadi galáp buta, tagal bulan deng bintang dong su sonde bacaya batúl lai.<bt>Then, that angel number four blew his trumpet. Unexpectedly the sun and moon and stars were stricken, and they become dark. So (consequently) in the daytime, one part from three parts of the day time became dark, because the sun was not shining correctly/fully anymore. And at nighttime, one part from three parts of night time became pitch dark, because the moon and the stars did not shine correctly/fully anymore.</bt><note reference="8:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 13:10, Yeskial 32:7, Yoel 2:10, 31, 3:15</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ais beta angka muka, ju dapa lia satu burung garuda tarbáng tinggi-tinggi di langit. Dia batarea bilang, &lt;&lt;Awas, ó! Calaka bésar nanti jato kaná samua orang yang idop di bumi. Te masi ada tiga ana bua di sorga laen yang balóm tiop dong pung tarompet.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then I lifted up my face, and I saw a garuda bird flying high in the sky. He yelled out saying, “Watch out, ó! A big catastrophe will fall on all the people who live on earth. Cuz (elaboration) there are still three angels who have not yet blown their trumpets.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tiop tarompet nomer lima -- kalamak bekin sangsara manusia [\s2]<bt>Trumpet number five -- grasshoppers cause people to suffer [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="9" />
      <v n="1" />Ais, itu ana bua nomer lima tiop dia pung tarompet. Ju beta dapa lia satu bintang yang su jato pi bumi. Dong kasi satu konci sang itu bintang ko dia buka pintu lobang sangsara yang sonde ada pung dasar.<bt>Then, that angel number five blew his trumpet. And I saw a star that had fallen to the earth. They gave a key to that star in order that s/he open the door to the hole of torment which has no foundation/bottom. [EXEG: implicature: CEV note and Ex. Summ (unanimous) in ancient world, stars were thought to be personal beings of some kind. Consider FTN, if necessary, if the star being given the key doesn't make sense.] [NOTE to daughter translations: Make sure the “endless/bottomless” modifies “hole”, not “suffering” (that goes on and on). ALT: pintu lobang yang sonde ada pung dasar. Itu tampa tu, ponu deng sangsara.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added |i(1) |rplace"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** (2009) note added <span class="Italic">(1) </span>place of evil spirits, fallen angels??</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Dia buka itu lobang pung pintu, ju asap itam tabal kaluar sama ke asap utan tabakar. Itu asap nae kaluar kabuak-kabuak, sampe langit deng matahari jadi galáp.<bt>S/he opened that hole's door, and thick black smoke came out like the smoke of burning forest. That smoke came out went up in clumps, until the sky and the sun were black.</bt><note reference="9:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 19:28</note><v n="3" />Tarús ada kalamak banya mau mati tarbáng kaluar dari itu asap, ko turun datang pi bumi. Tuhan Allah su kasi sang dong kuasa sama ke kalajingking.<bt>Next an incredible large number of grasshoppers flew out of that smoke, to come down/swoop down to the earth. God had given them power like scorpions.</bt><note reference="9:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 10:12-15</note><v n="4" />Ma Dia parenta sang dong ko sonde bole bekin rusak bumi pung rumput, pohon, deng tanaman laen dong. Ma dong musti bekin sangsara samua orang yang sonde ada Tuhan pung cap di dong pung testa.<bt>But He ordered them to not destroy the earth's grass, and trees, and other plants. But they were to cause torment to all the people who did not have God's stamp/brand/identifying mark on their forehead.</bt><note reference="9:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 9:4</note><v n="5" />Tuhan kasi loos itu kalamak dong ko bekin sangsara sang itu orang dong sampe lima bulan, ma sonde bole bekin mati sang dong. Cuma bekin saki sang dong sama ke kalajingking dedek.<bt>God allowed those grasshoppers to cause torment to those people for five months, but they could not kill them. Only cause them pain like a scorpion sting.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dedek"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">dedek</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Dalam lima bulan tu, nanti orang sangsara tar bisa-bisa lai, sampe dong minta mati sa. Biar bagitu ju, ma dong sonde mati.<bt>During those five months, the suffering people would not be able to stand it anymore, to the point that they just request to die. Even that being the case, nevertheless they do not die.</bt><note reference="9:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Ayub 3:21, Yeremia 8:3</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Beta lia itu kalamak dong pung rupa, sama ke kuda paráng. Dong ada pake topi kapala paráng yang bekin dari mas. Dong pung muka sama ke manusia.<bt>I saw those grasshoppers' form, like war horses. They were wearing war chief hats which were made out of gold. Their faces were like humans. [NOTE to daughter translations: be careful that “form” and “faces” come out differently. For the first, you can just say “like”.]</bt><note reference="9:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yoel 2:4</note><v n="8" />Dong pung rambu panjang sama ke parampuan pung rambu. Deng dong pung gigi tajam sama ke singa pung gigi.<bt>Their hair was long like a woman's hair. And their teeth were sharp like lion's teeth.</bt><note reference="9:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yoel 1:6</note><v n="9" />Tingka ke dong ada pake pele dada dari bési, tingka ke ikan pung sisik. Dong pung sayap babunyi bésar sama ke satu batalyon tantara pung kuda hela bawa lari kareta paráng.<bt>It was as if they were wearing chest protectors out of metal, like fish scales. Their wings sounded loudly, like an army batalion's horses running pulling war carts. [NOTE to daughter translation: compare phrasing for “breastplate” in 1 Thess. 5:8 &amp; Eph. 6:14]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Miriam prefers &quot;chariots&quot;. In Exodus we"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Miriam prefers "chariots". In Exodus we have used "wagons fo war" and "war wagons", so we need to see how generally "chariots" is understood.</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yoel 2:5</note><v n="10" />Dong pung ekor talalu hebat, deng baracon sama ke kalajingking pung racon. Dong dapa kuasa ko bekin sangsara orang pake dong pung racon, sampe lima bulan.<bt>Their tails were truly amazing with poison like scorpion poison. They were given power to torment people with that poison of theirs, for five months.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sengat BI?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">sengat BI?</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Itu kalamak dong pung raja, andia bos dari samua ana bua yang kaná usir di itu lobang sangsara yang sonde ada pung dasar. Dia pung nama dalam bahasa Ibrani, <span class="Italic">Abadon,</span> deng dalam bahasa Yunani, <span class="Italic">Apolyon.</span> Dia pung arti bilang, &lt;&lt;Tukang Bekin Rusak&gt;&gt;.<bt>Those grasshopper's raja, was the boss of all the underlings who had been evicted to that suffering hole which did not have a foundation. His name in Hebrew language, <span class="Italic">Abadon,</span> and in Greek language, <span class="Italic">Apolyon.</span> It's meaning says, “The Habitual Destroyer.” [EXEG: See Ex.Summ., TH, Hughes, Mounce, for merely a glimpse of the complex issues in this verse. We take the king/angel in this vs as the same as 9:1. The ‘lobang sengsara’ spews forth various kinds of destructive creatures in ch.9, 11, 17, 20. So at a high level we take “a king, the angel of the abyss” as being boss of all the groups associated with the abyss, including the locusts here. Note: some MTTs have gotten confused with the rendering of the Kupang, so discuss carefully. (LJ)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ should who are in the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">@@ should who are in the pit &gt; who came out of the pit?? (see v.2)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Deng bagitu, calaka partama tu, su lewat. Ma awas, ó! Te masi ada dua calaka lai nanti datang.<bt>In that way, that first catastrophe, had passed. But be careful, ó! Cuz (elaboration) there are still two more catastrophes to come later.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tiop tarompet nomer anam -- tiga macam sangsara di bumi [\s2]<bt>Trumpet number six -- three kinds of suffering on earth [\s2]</bt></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\HK00260C.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left">Meja mas deng dia pung tandok<bt>Gold table and its horns</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ais, itu ana bua nomer anam tiop dia pung tarompet. Ju beta lia itu meja mas yang dong pake ko bakar dara kayu wangi, yang bamangada deng Tuhan. Ada suara kaluar datang dari itu meja pung tandok ampa-ampa.<bt>Then, that number six angel blew his trumpet. And I saw that gold table which they used to burn resin, which was facing God. There was a voice coming out of that table's four horns.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="corners [CEV] *** pix added 2007"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">corners [CEV] *** pix added 2007</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 30:1-3</note><v n="14" />Itu suara kasi tau itu ana bua yang baru tiop dia pung tarompet tu bilang, &lt;&lt;Ada ana bua ampa yang su ta'ika lama di kali bésar satu, nama kali Efrat. Pi kasi lapás sang dong su!&gt;&gt;<bt>That voice told that angel who had just blown that trumpet saying, “There are four underlings who have been tied up for a long time at a big river, named Efrat river. Go free them!”</bt><v n="15" />Ju dia pi kasi lapás sang dong, ko dong pi bunu bekin mati manusia pas deng dia pung taon, dia pung bulan, dia pung hari deng dia pung jam, yang Tuhan su putus memang. Kalo kotong bagi samua manusia di bumi jadi tiga bagian, na, yang mati tu, satu bagian.<bt>Then he went to free them, in order for them to go murder kill humans exactly at the year, on the month, on the day, and on the hour which God had decided ahead of time. If we divide all the humans on earth into three parts, na, those who died, were one part.</bt><v n="16" />Dong kasi tau sang beta bilang, itu ana bua dong pung tantara yang nae kuda paráng tu, ada dua ratus juta.<bt>They told me saying those underling's soldiers which rode war horses, were two hundred million.</bt><v n="17" />Ais beta dapa lia itu tantara deng dong pung kuda-kuda dong. Itu tantara dong pake pele dada tiga warna, andia mera manyala, biru mangkilat, deng kuning balerang. Itu kuda-kuda dong pung kapala sama ke singa pung kapala. Ada ju api, asap, deng balerang yang tasumbur dari itu kuda dong pung mulu,<bt>Then I saw those soldiers and their horses. Those soldiers wore three colour chest protectors, that is shiny red, flashing blue, and sulfur yellow. Those horse's head were like lion's heads. There was also smoke and sulfur that sprayed/spit out of those horses mouths,</bt><v n="18" />ko kasi tiga macam sangsara di bumi. Itu sangsara yang kaluar dari kuda dong pung mulu tu, bekin mati satu dari tiga bagian, dari samua manusia yang ada di bumi.<bt>in order to give three kinds of suffering on earth. Those sufferings that came out of the horses mouths, caused death to one of three parts of all the humans who are on the earth.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="one-third is missing; undertranslated; **fixed Sep"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">one-third is missing; undertranslated; **fixed Sep 2005</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Ais, itu kuda dong pi bekin sangsara manusia pake dong pung mulu deng dong pung ekor. Di dong pung ekor tu, ada kapala sama ke ular pung kapala.<bt>Then, those horses went to cause suffering to humans using their mouths and their tails. On those tails of theirs, there was a head like snake head.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ma masi ada manusia laen dong di bumi, yang sonde kaná bunu deng itu calaka dong. Biar bagitu ju, ma dong sonde mau kasi tenga dong pung jahat. Dong songgo setan tarús-tarús, deng songgo barang yang dong bekin dari mas, perak, tambaga, batu deng kayu. Biar itu barang dong sonde bisa lia, sonde bisa dengar, deng sonde bisa jalan, ma dong songgo tar pake barenti!<bt>But there were still other people on earth, who were not killed with those sufferings. Even that being the case, nevertheless they did not want to abandon their evil. They continued (non-Christian) worshipping evil spirits and worship things which they made from gold, silver, copper, stone and wood. Even though those things could not see, could not hear, and could not walk, but they just kept on worshipping them.</bt><note reference="9:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 115:4-7, 135:15-17, Daniel 5:23</note><v n="21" />Dong ju sonde mau barenti dari dong pung sala-sala laen dong, sama ke bunu orang, pake ilmu galáp, maen serong deng orang yang bukan dia pung laki ko dia pung bini, deng mancuri.<bt>They also did not want to stop from their others sins, such as killing people, using black magic, (sexual) transgression with someone who is not their husband or wife, and stealing.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="porneia is broader than just adultery"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">porneia is broader than just adultery **fixed Sep 2005</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ana bua dari sorga deng tulisan kici yang tagulung<bt>The angel with the small writing that is rolled up</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="10" />
      <v n="1" />Ais beta dapa lia Tuhan pung ana bua satu yang hebat, turun datang dari sorga. Dia pung badan tabungkus deng awan. Ada palangi kuliling dia pung kapala ju. Dia pung muka bacaya sama ke matahari, deng dia pung kaki manyala sama ke api.<bt>Then I saw an angel who was amazing, coming down from heaven. His body was wrapped with cloud. There was also a rainbow surrounding his head. His face shone like the sun, and his leg/feet blazed like fire.</bt><v n="2" />Dia ada pegang satu tulisan kici tagulung yang su tabuka. Dia badiri deng kaki kanan di laut, kaki kiri di darat.<bt>He was holding a small rolled up writing which was opened. He stood right foot in the sea, left foot on the land.</bt><v n="3" />Ais dia batarea deng suara karás sama ke singa mangaum. Dia batarea abis, ju guntur manyao basambung tuju kali.<bt>Then he yelled with a loud voice, like a lion roaring. He finished yelling, then thunder answered in sequence seven times.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Seven: indicates completion in the Bible."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Seven: indicates completion in the Bible. Thunder: sometimes indicates God's judgment, or people think God is speaking.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Waktu guntur dong manyao abis, ju beta su mau tulis dong pung omong. Ma beta dengar satu suara dari sorga bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Lu jang kasi tau orang itu tuju guntur pung omong, ó! Sonde bole tulis apa-apa.&gt;&gt;<bt>When the thunders had answered/responded, then I was wanting to write what they said. But I heard a voice from heaven saying, “Wee! You don't tell anyone the talking of those seven thunders, ó. Don't write anything.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ais, itu ana bua yang badiri deng satu kaki di laut, satu kaki di darat tu, angka dia pung tangan kanan pi langit,<bt>Then, that angel there who stood with one foot in the sea, one foot on the land, lifted up his right hand to the sky,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="The gesture of one who makes"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">The gesture of one who makes a promise to God</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />ko sumpa bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta pung omong ni, memang batúl! Beta sumpa pake Tuhan Allah pung nama, tagal Dia yang ada tarús sampe salamanya! Dia yang su bekin ame langit deng bumi, deng dong pung isi samua. Naa, dengar bae-bae! Itu hari yang kotong tunggu-tunggu tu, su deka-deka datang.<bt>to swear (oath) saying, “This speaking of mine, is true! I swear with God's name, because it is He, who continues on forever! It is he who has made the sky and land, and all their contents. Now! Listen well! That day which we all have waited for, it is nearly here. [EXEG: lgs in this region don't tend to have a lexical item that matches “delay”; Sense of “wait no longer” from NLT, CEV; immediately, without delay, see Ex. Summ.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="say first then swear that it's"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">say first then swear that it's true</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Te kalo Tuhan pung ana bua nomer tuju su mau tiop dia pung tarompet, nanti Tuhan bekin iko dia pung rancana yang dolu-dolu orang balóm tau. Ma itu rancana Dia su kasi tau sang Dia pung jubir dong yang layani sang Dia. Jadi dengar bae-bae, te Beta pung omong ni, batúl.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if God's number seven angel is about to blow his trumpet, then God will carry out his plan which long ago people did not know. But that plan, He has told using His spokespersons who serve Him. So (consequently), listen carefully, cuz (elaboration) this speaking of mine here, is true.” [EXEG: TAM “is to blow” NRSV, “is about to sound trumpet” AGNT] [DISCOURSE: last sentence closing off oath.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="TERM: &quot;Serious promise&quot; or &quot;strong promise&quot;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">TERM: "Serious promise" or "strong promise" elsewhere too - check for 'oath'.</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:5-7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 20:11, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 32:40, Daniel 12:7, Amos 3:7</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ais, itu suara yang beta dengar dari langit tu, omong ulang lai deng beta bilang, &lt;&lt;Yohanis, lu pi su di itu ana bua dari sorga yang ada badiri deng satu kaki di laut, satu kaki di darat tu. Ame itu gulungan kici yang ada tabuka di dia pung tangan tu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then, that voice which I heard earlier from the sky, it spoke again with me saying, “Yohanis, you go to that angel there, who is standing with one foot in the sea, one foot on the land. Take that small rolled up writing which is open in that hand of his.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ais beta pi itu ana bua, ko minta itu gulungan kici tu. Ju dia kasi tau sang beta bilang, &lt;&lt;Ame ko makan su! Di lu pung mulu rasa manis sama ke madu, ma nanti dia bekin lu pung parú rasa pait.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then I went to that angel, to request that aforementioned small writing. Then he told me saying, “Take it to eat it (imp)! In your mouth it will taste sweet like honey, but later it will make your stomach feel bitter.” [EXEG: reverse order for chronology: mouth, then stomach. Compare vs. 10.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Nanti dia bekin lu pung parú"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Nanti dia bekin lu pung parú rasa pait, ma di lu pung mulu nanti rasa manis sama ke madu.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Dia omong abis bagitu, ju beta tarima itu gulungan kici dari dia pung tangan. Tarús beta makan. Dalam beta pung mulu ada rasa manis sama ke madu. Ma waktu beta su kodo sang dia, beta rasa pait di beta pung parú.<bt>He finished speaking like that, then I accepted that small writing from his hand. Next I ate it. In my mouth it tasted sweet like honey. But when I swallowed it, I felt bitter in my stomach.</bt><note reference="10:8-10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 2:8--3:3</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ais ada yang suru sang beta bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu musti pi ulang lai ko kasi tau memang apa yang Tuhan mau bekin di bumi. Kasi tau so'al apa yang nanti jadi deng samua raja di bumi deng orang dari samua suku, samua bangsa, deng samua bahasa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then there was one who ordered me saying, “You must go again to tell ahead of time that which God wants to do on earth. Tell about what will latter happen with all the kings on earth and the people from every nation, every clan, and every language.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Allah pung jubir dua orang yang hebat<bt>God's two amazing spokespersons</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="11" />
      <v n="1" />Ais dong sorong kasi sang beta satu kayu ukur yang panjang sama ke tongkat. Ju Tuhan Allah parenta sang beta bilang, &lt;&lt;Yohanis, lu bangun su ko pi ukur Beta pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat deng dia pung meja korban di kota Yerusalem. Deng itong samua orang yang ada sambayang di situ.<bt>They they handed me a measuring stick that was long like a staff. And God commanded me saying, “Yohanis, you get up to go measure My Main Worship House with it's sacrifice table in Yerusalem city. And count all the people who are worshiping/praying there. [EXEG: ‘My’ from TH] [NOTE to daughter translations: careful with the tongkat measure (following the Gk). The middle eastern ones seem to be about a fathom (arm-span) in length. Some of the ones around this region only average a little over a meter. If so, say /kayu ukur yang panjang satu depa/.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tuhan is in later verse 'my'"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Tuhan is in later verse 'my' Thandbook.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 40:3, Sakaria 2:1-2</note><v n="2" />Ma sonde usa ukur itu Ruma Sambayang pung kintal, te itu tampa su sarakan kasi suku-bangsa laen yang sonde kanál sang Beta. Nanti dong datang inja-inja bekin kamomos Beta pung kota tu, sampe 42 bulan (andia 1.260 hari).<bt>But it's not necessary to measure the Worship House's yard, cuz (elaboration) that place already has been handed/turned over to the other nations who do not know Me. Later they will come step all over making dirty that city of Mine, for 42 months (that is 1260 days). [EXEG: Yakan BT for ‘my city’] [NOTE to daughter translations: try “three and a half years” if that's more natural to give sense of times, but remember, precision of info is what is in focus, so sometimes saying 3.5 yrs is being more vague.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="su bagi kasi bangsa-bangsa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">su bagi kasi bangsa-bangsa</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 21:24</note><v n="3" />Nanti Beta utus Beta pung orang dua di situ, ko dong jadi Beta pung jubir. Nanti dong pake pakean duka deng kasi tau pasán dari Beta, sampe itu 1.260 hari su abis.&gt;&gt;<bt>Later I will commission two of My people there so that they become My spokesperson. Later they will wear mourning clothes and tell messages/instructions from Me until those 1260 days are finished.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Nanti dong pake pakean duka deng"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Nanti dong pake pakean duka deng omong so'al Beta, sampe itu 1.260 hari su abis.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Tuhan Allah pung jubir Sakaria su tulis memang dari dolu, so'al ini dua jubir ni. Dia pake gambar dua pohon saitun deng dua tampa taro lampu yang badiri mangada pi Tuhan Allah, yang hak parenta sang samua orang di dunya.<bt>God's spokesperson Sakaria wrote ahead of time from before, about these two aforementioned spokespersons, using a picture of two olive trees and two wick lamps that stand facing God, who has the say-so/ordering rights over all people in the world.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tabadiri mangada"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">tabadiri mangada</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Sakaria 4:3, 11-14</note><v n="5" />Kalo ada orang yang mau bekin calaka sang Tuhan Allah pung jubir dua ni, nanti api kaluar dari dong pung mulu ko bekin angus dong pung musu samua. Deng bagitu, samua orang yang mau bekin susa sang dong, pasti mati.<bt>If there is/are a person/people who wants to cause torment to this two spokesperson's of God, later fire will come out of their mouths to burn all their enemies. In that way, all people who want to cause them difficulty, will surely die.</bt><v n="6" />Waktu dong dua jadi Tuhan pung jubir di bumi, Dia kasi kuasa sang dong ko tutu ujan. Dia ju kasi kuasa ko bekin mata aer jadi dara, deng kuasa ko bawa macam-macam calaka di ini bumi, iko dong pung mau-mau sa.<bt>When the two of them become God's spokespersons on earth, He will give power to them to close the rain (make it not rain). He will also give power to make water springs become blood, and power to bring all kinds of catastrophies on this earth, according to whatever they want.</bt><note reference="11:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Raja-raja dong 17:1, Kaluar dari Masir 7:17-19, 1 Samuel 4:8</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Kalo dong pung waktu ko kasi tau Tuhan pung pasán dong su abis, nanti satu binatang buas kaluar dari lobang sangsara yang sonde ada pung dasar. Dia baparáng lawan dong dua, sampe dia kasi kala deng bunu bekin mati sang dong.<bt>When their time of telling God2's messages/ instructions is over, later a vicious animal will come out of that torment hole that does not have a foundation. He will war against the two of them, until he defeats them and kills them.</bt><note reference="11:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 7:7, Dunya Model Baru 13:5-7, 17:8, Daniel 7:21</note><v n="8-9" />Deng bagitu, dong dua mati di itu kota bésar yang dolu orang bunu dong pung Tuhan di kayu palang. Te itu kota tu, su jadi kota jahat sama ke Sodom deng Masir tempo dolu. Nanti orang dong lempar buang itu jubir dong pung mayat di jalan, sampe tiga hari satenga. Ais orang dari samua suku, samua bangsa, samua bahasa, deng samua negara datang manonton itu dua mayat. Dong ju sonde kasi isin ko kubur,<bt>In that way, they two will die in that big city in which previously people killed their Lord on a cross. Cuz (elaboration) that aforementioned city, has become an evil city like Sodom and Masir in previous times. Later people will throw away those spokesperson's corpses in the street, for three and half days. Then people from every nation, every clan, every language, and every country will come watch those two aforementioned corpses. They also will not give permission to bury them,</bt><note reference="11:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 1:9-10</note><v n="10" />tagal dong sanáng lia itu dua orang su mati. Te dong dua yang maen ganggu samua orang di bumi pung pikiran. Jadi dong rame-rame bekin pesta, deng bakirim hadia kasi satu deng satu.<bt>because they are happy seeing those two people have died. Cuz (elaboration) the two of them are the ones who kept disturbing the thoughts of all people on earth. So they will enthusiastically make a feast, and send presents to each other. [NOTE to daughter translations: what the prophets say upsets everybody's consciences, so avoid the impression of wreaking physical havoc.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bekin sangsara"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">bekin sangsara</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ma tiga hari satenga abis, nanti Tuhan Allah kasi napas sang dong, ko dong idop kambali. Ais samua orang yang dapa lia sang dong, gamatar dingin.<bt>But after three and half days then God will give breath to them, so that they live again. Then all people who see them, will tremble exceedingly.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** new paragraph 30/9/05 M.Crofts"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** new paragraph 30/9/05 M.Crofts</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 37:10</note><v n="12" />Ais, itu jubir dua nanti dengar satu suara karás dari langit, yang suru sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Woi! Bosong dua mari nae datang di sini su!&gt;&gt; Ju dong dua ta'angka nae pi langit deng awan tutu bungkus sang dong. Lia bagitu ju, dong pung musu dong tanganga bodo.<bt>Then, those two spokesperson later will hear a loud voice from heaven, which tells them saying, “Woi! [+challenge] You two come up here!” Then they two will be taken up to the sky with a cloud covering wrapping them. Seeing that, then their enemies will be stunned (open mouth speechless).</bt><note reference="11:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Raja-raja dong 2:11</note><v n="13" />Takuju sa ju, ada tana tagoyang yang hebat. Kalo kotong itong samua ruma di kota, dari sapulu ruma, ada satu yang rubu. Deng ada tuju ribu orang yang mati. Orang laen yang sonde mati dong, jadi taku mau mati. Ma nanti dong ju kasi hormat sang Tuhan Allah, tagal Dia yang pegang parenta di sorga.<bt>Suddenly there will be a big earthquake. If we count all the houses in the city, from ten houses, there will be one that falls. And there will be seven thousand people who die. The other people who don't die, will become exceedingly afraid, But they will also give honour to God, because He is the one who holds ruling power in heaven. [EXEG: Gk: glory here, undertranslated because of the inadequacies of Kupang resulting in skewing the focus.]</bt><note reference="11:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 6:12, 16:18</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Deng bagitu, calaka nomer dua su lewat. Ma awas, ó! Te calaka nomer tiga su mau datang na.<bt>In that way, catastrophe number two will pass. But be careful, ó! Cuz (elaboration) catastrophe number there is coming [+obviously].</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tiop tarompet nomer tuju -- Tuhan Allah deng Yesus Kristus pegang parenta di bumi [\s2]<bt>Trumpet number seven -- God and Yesus Kristus rule on earth [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ais itu, Tuhan pung ana bua dari sorga nomer tuju tiop dia pung tarompet. Takuju sa, beta dengar banya suara rame-rame datang dari sorga bilang,<bt>After that, angel number seven blew his trumpet. Unexpectedly/suddenly, I heard many voices enthusiastically come from heaven saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Sakarang yang pegang parenta di bumi,<bt>“Now the ones who rule on earth,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">cuma Tuhan Allah deng Kristus,<bt>are only God and Kristus,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">andia Tuhan pung Orang yang Dia su pili ame dari dolu.<bt>that Person whom He has chosen from long ago.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Nanti Tuhan Allah pegang parenta tarús sama ke Raja, sampe salamanya.&gt;&gt;<bt>Later God will rule like a King forever.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tran handbook final dia = Tuhan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Tran handbook final dia = Tuhan Allah ; @@ sometimes /tiop/ sometimes /tiup/ ??</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 15:18, Daniel 2:44, 7:14, 27</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Itu 24 katua yang ada dudu di korsi parenta di Tuhan Allah pung muka tu, dong ju dengar itu suara dong. Ais dong jato tikam lutut deng muka sampe di tana, ko puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah,<bt>Those 24 elders who were sitting on those aforementioned ruling chairs in front of God, they also heard those voices. Then they fell kneeling with face to the ground, to praise and praise God,</bt><v n="17" />deng manyanyi bilang,<bt>and sing saying, [EXEG: NRSV] [NOTE to daughter translations: some lgs do this direct praise respectfully in 3rd person, but some do it better in 2s as in Gk. CHECK yours.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Oo, Tuhan Allah!<bt>“O Lord God!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Botong pung Bos!<bt>Our Bos!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Botong pung Allah!<bt>Our God!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tuhan yang parenta samua.<bt>Lord  (=you) is the one who rules everything</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tuhan yang kuasa samua.<bt>Lord  (=you) is the one who has power/authority over everything</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan yang ada dari dolu-kala.<bt>Lord  (=you) is the one who lives from long ago.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan yang ada sakarang.<bt>Lord  (=you) is the one who lives now.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Botong minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan,<bt>We request(=give) thanks to the Lord  (=you),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal Tuhan su pake Tuhan pung kuasa yang bésar,<bt>because the Lord  (=you) has used the Lord's (=your) power which is big,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko pegang parenta di bumi.<bt>to rule on earth.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="18" />Ma suku-bangsa dong mara,<bt>But the other nations are angry,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">te dong sonde mau iko sang Tuhan.<bt>cuz (elaboration) they don't want to follow the Lord.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ma sakarang Tuhan ju mara,<bt>And now the Lord is also angry,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal dong sonde mau kanál sang Dia.<bt>because they don't want to know Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Sakarang dia pung waktu su sampe,<bt>Now the time has come for</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko Tuhan hukum sang orang yang sonde mau toe sang Dia.<bt>The Lord to punish people who don't want to know anything about Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Sakarang dia pung waktu su sampe,<bt>Now the time has come for</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko Tuhan kasi ancor orang yang bekin ancor orang laen.<bt>the Lord to destroy people who destroy other people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Sakarang dia pung waktu su sampe,<bt>Now the time has come for</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko Tuhan pareksa orang mati dong pung parkara.<bt>the Lord to examine the dead people's affairs/cases.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Sakarang dia pung waktu su sampe,<bt>Now the time has come for</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko Tuhan balas Tuhan pung orang suru-suru dong pung karingat.<bt>the Lord to reciprocate the Lord's servant's sweat (=effort):</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Andia Tuhan pung jubir dong,<bt>That is the Lord's spokespersons,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng Tuhan pung orang dong,<bt>and the Lord's people,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">kici-bésar, tua-muda.<bt>Small big, old young.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan balas kasi samua orang,<bt>The Lord reciprocates all people</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">yang kasi hormat sang Tuhan pung nama.&gt;&gt;<bt>who give honour to the Lord's name.”</bt><note reference="11:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 2:5, 110:5, 115:13</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ais itu, beta dapa lia di sorga, Tuhan pung Ruma Sambayang pung pintu ada tabuka. Tarús beta dapa lia itu peti yang dolu dong pake simpan Tuhan Allah pung parenta yang ada tatulis di batu. Ju kilat basambar pi-datang, guntur babunyi bésar basambung, bumi tagoyang-goyang, deng ujan es batu yang barát jato turun dari langit.<bt>After that, I saw in heaven the Lord's Worship House's door was open. Next I saw that box which previously they used to store God's commands that were written on stone. Then lightning struck all around, loud sounding thunder followed, the earth shook and shook, and rock ice rain that was heavy fell down from the sky.</bt><note reference="11:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 8:5, 16:18, 16:21</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ular naga baparáng lawan parampuan deng dia pung ana<bt>The dragon snake wars against the woman with her child</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="12" />
      <v n="1" />Ais itu, takuju sa beta lia ada satu tanda luar biasa yang muncul di langit, yang manusia balóm parná lia: ada satu parampuan yang dia pung badan ada tabungkus deng matahari. Dia alas dia pung kaki di atas bulan. Dia pake topi raja yang ada 12 bintang.<bt>After that, unexpectedly/suddenly I saw an extra-ordinary sign which appeared in the sky, which humans have not yet ever seen: there was a woman whose body was wrapped with the sun. She put her feet on top of the moon. She wore a raja hat that had 12 stars.</bt><v n="2" />Dia ada dudu parú, deng ada manangis, te dia su dapa saki mau barana.<bt>She was pregnant, and was crying, cuz (elaboration) she was having birth pains.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Takuju sa, beta dapa lia lai satu tanda luar biasa laen yang muncul di langit. Ada satu ular naga mera yang bésar. Dia pung kapala ada tuju, deng dia pung tandok ada sapulu. Dia ada pake tuju topi raja di dia pung kapala dong.<bt>Unexpectedly, I saw again another extra-ordinary sign which appeared in the sky. There was a red dragon snake that was big. It's heads were seven, and it's horns were ten. It wore seven king hats on its heads.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="diadeemata: fillet, blue band trimmed with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">diadeemata: fillet, blue band trimmed with white, from Persia</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 7:7</note><v n="4" />Dia pake dia pung ekor ko sapu barisi kasi ilang satu bagian dari bintang-bintang di langit. Yang sisa, cuma dua bagian sa. Ais dia lempar buang itu bintang dong pi bumi. Tarús dia pi badiri mangada itu parampuan, ko tunggu-tunggu sampe dia barana. Te dia mau kodo memang itu ana.<bt>It used its tail to sweep clean one part of the stars in the sky. Those that were left, were only just two parts. Then it threw those stars to the earth. Next it went ot stand facing that woman, to wait until she gave birth. Cuz (elaboration) it wanted to right away swallow that child.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="triteen: one third, one out of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">triteen: one third, one out of every three stars. Alternate, more appropriate in some contexts, "30%". The English term "third" is known and used, but it is also homophonous with a coprology.</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 8:10</note><v n="5" />Ais, itu parampuan barana ame satu Ana laki-laki. Ma Tuhan Allah pung ana bua satu dari sorga datang rampas ame itu Ana, ju bawa pi Tuhan ko itu Ana parenta sama-sama deng Tuhan Allah di sorga. Te itu Ana tu, nanti parenta samua suku-bangsa di bumi deng kuasa yang paling hebat.<bt>Then, that woman gave birth to a male Child. But an angel came and snatched that Child, and brought him to the Lord so that that child ruled together with God in heaven. Cuz (elaboration) that aforementioned Child, later would rule all the nations on earth with extremely amazing authority/power.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="poimainei: firmness, not force"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">poimainei: firmness, not force</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 66:7, Lagu Puji dong 2:9</note><v n="6" />Ma itu parampuan lari pi satu tampa sunyi yang Tuhan su siap memang kasi sang dia. Nanti dong urus sang dia di situ sampe tiga taon satenga (andia, 1.260 hari).<bt>But that woman ran to a quiet/desolate place which the Lord had prepared for her. Later they took care of her there for three and half years (that is 1260 days).</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Mikael baparáng lawan ular naga di sorga [\s2]<bt>Mikael wars against the dragon snake in heaven [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ais itu ju jadi paráng bésar di sorga. Tuhan Allah pung ana bua dari sorga deng dong pung panglima Mikael, baparáng lawan itu ular naga deng dia pung ana bua dong.<bt>After that then there was a big war in heaven. The angels with their commander-in-chief Mikael warred against that snake dragon and its underlings.</bt><note reference="12:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 10:13, 21, 12:1, Yudas 9</note><v n="8" />Ju Mikael dong kasi kala itu ular naga deng dia pung ana bua dong. Ais itu dong larang itu ular naga deng dia pung ana bua dong, ko sonde bole tenga di sorga lai.<bt>And Mikael (collective) defeated that snake dragon and its underlings. Then they forbade that snake dragon and its underlings, so that they could not stay in heaven anymore.</bt><v n="9" />Tagal itu, dong usir buang sang dong dari sorga, ais lempar buang pi bumi. Itu ular naga tu, andia setan dong pung bos, yang dong bilang, &lt;Iblis&gt;. Dari mula-mula dia yang maen putar-balek manusia ko dong bekin sala.<bt>Because of that, they expelled threw them out of heaven, then threw them away on to the earth. That aforementioned dragon snake, that is the evil spirit's boss, whom they call ‘Iblis (Indo for ‘devil’)’. From long ago, he habitually lied to people so that they would do wrong.</bt><note reference="12:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 3:1, Lukas 10:18</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ais beta dapa dengar lai satu suara karás dari langit bilang,<bt>Then I heard again a loud voice from the sky saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Dolu itu ular naga badiri tarús di Tuhan pung muka.<bt>“Previously that dragon snake kept standing before God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia tu, tukang bawa mulu yang maen lempar sala kasi kotong pung sodara yang parcaya dong.<bt>He is a tattle-tale who keeps accusing our siblings who believe.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Dia maen tudu sang dong siang-malam.<bt>He accuses them daytime-nighttime.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ma sakarang dia su talempar buang dari sorga.<bt>But now he/it is thrown out of heaven.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Jadi sakarang samua langkáp.<bt>So (consequently) everything is complete. [EXEG: Teams queried theology implying “salvation” etc. hadn't happened before. NLT gives sense of completeness or final step for everything to be complete. More support in Ex.Summ. and LN of Gk on /arti egeneto/.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ added to reduce theological noise"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">@@ added to reduce theological noise</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te sakarang dia pung waktu su sampe ko Tuhan kasi salamat sang manusia.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) now the time has come for God to save humans.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Sakarang Tuhan su pegang parenta deng Dia pung kuasa yang hebat.<bt>Now God rules with His amazing power/authority.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng Dia su angka Kristus,<bt>And He has raised up Kristus,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">andia Orang yang Dia su pili ko jadi Raja kasi samua suku-bangsa.<bt>that Person whom He chose to become King of all nations.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***12:10-12 formatted as poetry 30/9/05 M.Crofts"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">***12:10-12 formatted as poetry 30/9/05 M.Crofts</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Ayub 1:9-11, Sakaria 3:1</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="11" />Kotong pung sodara orang parcaya dong su kasi kala itu ular naga yang dolu lempar sala kasi sang dong,<bt>Our fellow believers have defeated that snake dragon who previously kept accusing them,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal Domba Ana pung dara su tumpa ko hapus dong pung sala-sala.<bt>because the Sheep Offspring's blood has spilled to erase their wrongs.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dong ju kasi kala sang dia,<bt>They also defeated him,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal dong barani kasi tau orang so'al Domba Ana pung hati bae kasi sang dong.<bt>because they dared to tell people about the Sheep Offspring's good liver (goodness/grace/kindness) for them. [NOTE: should track back to 1st 2 lines of vs.11.] [EXEG: “by the word of their testimony”, Uma BackTrans.; CEV seems to have missed it here.] [EXEG: recurring phrase in Rev. “the testimony of Jesus”. 1:2; 1:9; 12:11; 12:17; 19:10; 20:4. Much discussion (and disagreement) in the commentaries.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) fixed “by the word"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** (2009) fixed “by the word of their testimony”; note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tagal dong barani kasi tau Tuhan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">tagal dong barani kasi tau Tuhan pung Kata-kata.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Biar orang mara ko mau bunu sang dong ju,<bt>Even though people got angry and even wanted to kill them,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma dong sonde ondor.<bt>nevertheless they were not retreat/withdraw/shrink back.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="12" />Jadi samua yang idop di sorga, musti sanáng!<bt>So (consequently), all who live in heaven, [you] must be happy!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ma samua yang idop di bumi musti bajaga,<bt>But all who live on earth must watch out,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal calaka su mau jato kaná sang bosong.<bt>because misfortune/calamity is about to befall you-pl.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Setan dong pung bos su turun datang di bosong.<bt>The evil spirit's boss has come down to you-pl.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia su mara mau mati,<bt>He is very angry,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal dia tau bilang, dia pung waktu bekin jahat tu, su mau abis!&gt;&gt;<bt>because he knows, that time of this for doing evil, is about to finish!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eufrainete: more than &quot;be happy&quot; or"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">eufrainete: more than "be happy" or "feel good" hoi ... skeenountes: those who live temporarily<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ular naga cari-cari sang itu parampuan di bumi [\s2]<bt>The snake dragon keeps looking for the woman on earth [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Waktu itu ular naga dapa tau bilang, dia su tabuang di bumi, ju dia pi cari ko mau bekin susa sang itu parampuan yang su barana ame itu Ana.<bt>When that snake dragon knew that he was cast off to the earth, then he went to find and to cause difficulty to that woman who had given birth to that Child. [EXEG: troubled/pursued the woman, or the Child (who was already taken to heaven)? vs. 14 and all versions imply it is the woman. Referent needs to be clear. CHECK.]</bt><v n="14" />Ma dong kasi itu parampuan dua sayap, sama ke burung garuda pung sayap, ko biar dia tarbáng pi sambunyi di itu tampa sunyi yang jao dari itu ular naga. Di situ dong urus sang dia sampe tiga taon satenga.<bt>But they gave that woman two wings, like garuda bird wings, so that she could fly go hide in that desolate place that was far from that snake dragon. They they took care of her for three and half years. [EXEG: TH, HCE, Uma, Mounce, Hughes]</bt><note reference="12:14" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani asli tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;satu waktu, dua waktu, deng satenga waktu&gt;&gt;. Itu kata dong sama deng yang ada di <span class="Italic">Daniel</span> 7:25, 12:7. Dia pung waktu, sama deng 42 bulan, ko, 1.260 hari di fasal 11:2-3 di atas.<bt>The original Yunani language Bible writes saying, “one time, two times, and half (a) time”. Those words are the same as what is in <span class="Italic">Daniel</span> 7:25, 12:7. The time is the same as 42 months, or, 1,260 days in chapter 11:2-3 above.</bt></note><v n="15" />Lia bagitu, itu ular naga sumbur kasi kaluar aer sama ke banjer, ko mau sapu bawa itu parampuan.<bt>Seeing that, that snake dragon spit out water like a flood, to sweep take away that woman.</bt><v n="16" />Ma bumi tolong itu parampuan deng buka dia pung tana ko kodo abis itu aer yang malele kaluar dari itu ular naga pung mulu, ko biar itu aer jang sampe di itu parampuan.<bt>But the earth helped that woman by opening its land to swallow up that water that flowed coming out of that snake dragon's mouth, so that that water didn't get to that woman.</bt><v n="17" />Ais ju itu ular naga mara mau mati sang itu parampuan. Jadi dia kaluar ko pi baparáng lawan itu parampuan pung ana-ana laen dong, andia orang yang idop iko Tuhan Allah pung parenta, deng mangaku bilang, dong tu Yesus pung orang.<bt>Then that snake dragon was extremely angry at that woman. So (consequently), it went out to fight against that woman's other children, that is the people who live following/obeying God's commands, and acknowledge that they are Yesus' people. [EXEG: “having the testimony of Jesus”. NLT “confess that they belong to Jesus”; Uma “acknowledge that Jesus is their Lord”; CEV “faithful to what Jesus did and taught”; TEV “faithful to the truth revealed by Jesus”; NCV “have the message Jesus taught”; Mounce sees it as an objective genitive “is not their witness to him, but the testimony that he bore” (about them?); Hughes “bear testimony to Jesus” (also TH) or “witness in the face of all opposition (as in verse 11)”; BUT in Rev. 1:2 “testimony of Jesus Christ” is taken as “everything JC had said and done” (CEV); we follow NLT, as this makes sense in context. What/who makes the dragon angry? Those who obey God and say they belong to JC.] [EXEG: recurring phrase in Rev. “the testimony of Jesus”. 1:2; 1:9; 12:11; 12:17; 19:10; 20:4. Much discussion (and disagreement) in the commentaries.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) revised last clause and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** (2009) revised last clause and added note</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="andia orang yang idop iko Tuhan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">andia orang yang idop iko Tuhan Allah pung parenta, deng kasi tasiar tarús-tarús Yesus pung Kabar Bae.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Ais ju itu ular naga pi badiri di laut pung pinggir, deng makan gigi.<bt>And then that snake dragon went to stand on the edge of the sea, and ground his teeth (=furious frustration). [NOTE: last clause added (context: implicit &gt; explicit) Sept 2005 M. Crofts]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***last clause added (context: implicit &gt;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">***last clause added (context: implicit &gt; explicit) Sept 2005 M. Crofts</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Binatang buas yang kaluar dari laut<bt>The ferocious animal that comes out of the sea</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="13" />
      <v n="1" />Ais itu, beta dapa lia satu binatang buas kaluar dari laut. Dia pung kapala, tuju, deng dia pung tandok, sapulu. Dia pake topi raja satu-satu di dia pung tandok dong. Di itu kapala dong ada tulis kata-kata yang bekin hina sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>After that, I saw a ferocious animal come out of the sea. His heads, seven, and his horns, ten. He wore king hats on top of each of his horns. On those heads were written words which are offensive to God.</bt><note reference="13:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 7:3, Dunya Model Baru 17:3, 7-12</note><v n="2" />Dia pung badan, sama ke harimau. Dia pung kaki, sama ke baruang pung kaki. Deng dia pung mulu, sama ke singa pung mulu. Itu ular naga ofer kasi dia pung hak sang itu binatang buas ko dudu di korsi parenta, deng pake dia pung kuasa samua.<bt>His body, was like a tiger. His feet/legs, were like bear's feet. And his mouth, like lion's mouth. That snake dragon handed over his authority to that wild animal, so that he sat in that ruling chair, and he used all of his power/authority. [NOTE to daughter translations: Check animals if known, or at least assumed to be fearsome.] [EXEG: Does this animal have 7 mouths (logical from the 7 heads in vs.1) like a lion, or only one? Gk is grammatically singular, but that is vague since each head would have only one mouth. The Gk /autou/ “of it” or “its” is also singular, apparently referring to the whole beast. None of 11 sources consulted address this question. Therefore our protocols say go the safe route of the singular followed by all versions (including TB). This preserves the vagueness of the Gk.)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 7:4-6</note><v n="3" />Di itu binatang buas pung kapala satu ada bakás luka bésar, tingka ke dia parná kaná potong sampe amper mati, ma sonde jadi mati. Samua orang di bumi heran lia itu binatang buas pung hebat, ju dong iko sang dia.<bt>On one of that wild animal's heads was a big former wound, as if he had once been cut until he almost died, but he didn't die. All the people on earth were amazed looking at that wild animal's incredibleness, and they followed/obeyed it/him.</bt><v n="4" />Ais dong ju kasi hormat sang itu ular naga, deng angka tinggi-tinggi sang dia sama ke Tuhan, tagal itu ular su kasi kuasa sang itu binatang buas tu. Itu orang dong ju puji-puji itu binatang buas bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia tu, talalu hebat! Sonde ada yang bisa kasi kala sang dia!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they also gave honour to that dragon snake and lifted him up high like God, because that snake had given authority to that ferocious animal. Those people also kept praising that ferocious animal saying, “He there, is incredibly amazing! There is no one who can defeat him!” [NOTE to daughter translations: check that kasi hormat is equal to puji-puji, not weaker or lesser.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Tuhan Allah kasi loos itu binatang buas ko dia omong sombong deng omong bekin hina sang Tuhan. Dia dapa isin ko pegang parenta, sampe tiga taon satenga (andia 42 bulan).<bt>God permitted that ferocious animal to speak arrogantly and speak offensively to God. He was given permission to hold ruling authority, for three and a half years (that is 42 months). [EXEG: “was permitted” by whom? TH (followed by Uma) says by God, but in vs. 2 and 4 it is the dragon who is giving authority of different kinds to the beast. Mounce says John's readers would have understood the 4 occurrences in 5-7 to be “by divine permission” of God.]</bt><v n="6" />Andia ko, dia omong kasi jato Tuhan Allah pung nama. Deng dia ju omong bekin hina Tuhan Allah pung orang dong samua yang tenga di sorga.<bt>That's why he spoke making fall (slander2) God's name/ reputation. And he also slandered1 all of God's people who live in heaven. [EXEG: don't force “tabernacling” as does the TB.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="skeeneen: the portability is not in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">skeeneen: the portability is not in focus; it's the Old Testament allusion</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:5-6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 7:8, 25, 11:36</note><v n="7" />Tuhan ju kasi isin sang dia, ko baparáng lawan Tuhan pung orang dong, sampe bekin kala sang dong. Dia ju dapa kuasa ko parenta orang dari samua suku, samua bangsa, samua bahasa, deng samua negara di bumi.<bt>God also gave permission to him, to war against God's people, until he defeated them. He also was given authority/power to rule people of all the clans, all the nations, all the languages, and all the countries on earth.</bt><note reference="13:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 7:21</note><v n="8" />Tagal itu, samua orang di bumi songgo itu binatang buas. Dong tu, andia samua orang yang dong pung nama sonde tatulis di dalam Domba Ana pung Tulisan. Dolu orang su bunu bekin mati itu Domba Ana, ma Tuhan kasi idop kambali sang Dia. Waktu Tuhan balóm bekin ini dunya, Dia su tulis memang samua orang parcaya pung nama di itu tulisan bilang, dong tu, yang nanti dapa idop yang batúl yang sonde putus-putus.<bt>Because of that, all the people on earth (traditional/non-Christian) worshipped that aforementioned ferocious animal. They were all the people who names were not written in that Book of the Sheep Offspring. Previously people had killed that Sheep Offspring, but God made him live again. When God had still not yet made this world, He had already written ahead of time all the believer's names in that writing, saying they are the ones who would later get true/real life that never ends.</bt><note reference="13:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 69:29</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="9" />&lt;&lt;Dengar bae-bae!<bt>“Listen well!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***13:9-10 formatted as poetry 30/9/05 M.Crofts"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">***13:9-10 formatted as poetry 30/9/05 M.Crofts</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="10" />Kalo Tuhan su putus bilang, ada orang yang musti kaná tangkap,<bt>If God decides that there is someone who must be captured/arrested,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nanti dia kaná tangkap.<bt>later he will be captured.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Kalo Tuhan su putus bilang, ada orang yang musti kaná bunu deng kalewang,<bt>If God decides that there is someone who must be murdered with a fighting sword,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nanti dia kaná bunu deng kalewang.&gt;&gt;<bt>later he will be murdered with a fighting sword.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Andia, Tuhan pung orang dong jang ondor, te itu jadi sampát ko dong batahan iko tarús deng parcaya tarús sang Dia na!<bt>So God's people shouldn't retreat/pull back, cuz (elaboration) that is an opportunity to endure following and believing in Him continually [+obviously]!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** last two stanzas adjusted Sept"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** last two stanzas adjusted Sept 2005 M. Crofts / NLT</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Rev. 14:2."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Rev. 14:2.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Andia, Tuhan pung orang dong musti"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Andia, Tuhan pung orang dong musti batahan iko tarús sang Dia,</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeremia 15:2, 43:11</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Binatang buas yang kaluar dari bumi<bt>The ferocious animal that comes out of the earth</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ais itu, beta dapa lia binatang buas yang laen, nae kaluar dari bumi. Dia pung tandok dua, sama ke domba pung tandok. Deng dia pung suara, sama ke ular naga pung suara.<bt>After that, I saw another ferocious animal come up out of the earth. He had two horns, like a sheep's horn/s. And his voice, was like the dragon snake's voice.</bt><v n="12" />Dia jadi jubir kasi dia pung bos, andia itu binatang buas yang partama tu, yang dolu kaná potong amper mati. Dia tarima kuasa dari dia pung bos, ko paksa samua orang di bumi songgo dia pung bos.<bt>He became a spokesperson for his boss, who was that aforementioned first ferocious animal, who previously was inflicted with a cut almost dying. He received power/authority from that boss of his, in order to force all people on earth to [trad.] worship his boss.</bt><v n="13" />Dia ju bekin tanda-tanda heran yang hebat, sampe-sampe dia bisa kasi turun api dari langit di orang banya dong pung muka.<bt>He also did amazing signs that were incredible, to the point that he could bring down fire from heaven in front of many people. [EXEG: Gk just says “before (the) men/people”, so don't get caught up in noise from translations that say “all” or “everyone”, since it is contextually driven, not driven by the Gk text.]</bt><v n="14" />Deng bagitu, itu binatang buas nomer dua, pake dia pung bos pung kuasa ko putar-balek orang di bumi. Dia ju parenta orang dong ko bekin satu patong, sama ke dia pung bos pung rupa, ko dong kasi hormat sang dia pung bos yang dolu kaná potong amper mati tu.<bt>In that way, that aforementioned ferocious animal number two, used his boss' power to deceive people on earth. He also ordered people to make a statue, like his boss' appearance, so they could give honor to that aforementioned boss of his who previously was inflicted with a cut almost dying. [EXEG: “with a sword” explicit - implicit, since “cut” here evokes the earlier reference.]</bt><v n="15" />Tuhan ju kasi loos sang itu binatang tukang putar-balek tu, ko kasi napas bekin idop itu patong. Deng bagitu, itu patong bisa omong, deng kasi parenta ko bunu orang yang sonde mau songgo sang dia.<bt>God also allowed that aforementioned animal habitual deceiver, to give breath making that statue live. In that way, that statue could talk, and give orders to kill people who did not want to worship him. [EXEG: see note at vs. 5 on God as agent.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Itu binatang tukang putar-balek tu, ju paksa samua orang ko tarima cap di dong pung tangan kanan, ko, di dong pung testa. Samua orang, kici-bésar, kaya-miskin, mardeka ko, budak ko, dong samua musti tarima itu cap.<bt>That aforementioned animal habitual deceiver, also forced all people to receive a stamp on their right hands, or, on their foreheads. All people, small-big, rich-poor, freed or slave, they all must receive that stamp.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Rev. 11:18; 3:17; 6:15."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Rev. 11:18; 3:17; 6:15.</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Te kalo sonde, na, dong sonde bisa bajual, ko, balanja apa-apa. Di itu cap tu, ada tatulis itu binatang buas nomer satu pung nama, deng dia pung nomer.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if they didn't, na, they could not sell or buy anything. On that stamp was written that first wild animal's name and his number.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Di sini parlú pake otak, ó! Orang yang pintar, bisa mangarti itu nomer pung arti. Itu nomer yang kasi tunju ame sang manusia satu, andia &lt;&lt;666&gt;&gt;.<bt>Here you need to use your brains! The person/ whoever is smart can understand that number's meaning. That number which designates a certain human is “666”.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ rethink, /kana/ is too vague;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">@@ rethink, /kana/ is too vague; perhaps /kasi tunju/; **fixed Sep 2005</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Rev. 13:10."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Rev. 13:10.</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:18" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Iko orang yang pintar so'al Alkitab, jaman dolu di sana, nomer &lt;&lt;6&gt;&gt; pung arti, andia satu hal yang sonde bae, yang sonde sampurna, ko, yang jahat. Jadi nomer &lt;&lt;666&gt;&gt; ni pung arti bilang, &lt;&lt;yang paling jahat&gt;&gt;.<bt>According to people who are knowledgable about the Bible, long ago in that place, the number “6” meant something that was not good, not complete, or evil. So (consequently), this number “666” here means “most evil”. [EXEG: UBS Study Notes.]</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Domba Ana deng Dia pung 144.000 orang<bt>The Sheep Offspring with His 144.000 people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="14" />
      <v n="1" />Ais beta angka muka, ju takuju sa, beta dapa lia itu Domba Ana ada badiri di atas satu gunung kici, nama gunung Sion. Dia badiri sama-sama deng 144.000 orang. Di dong samua pung testa, ada tatulis itu Domba Ana deng Dia pung Bapa pung nama.<bt>Then I lifted my face, and unexpectedly I saw that Sheep Offspring standing on top of a small mountain, named Sion mountain. He stood together with 144.000 people. On all their foreheads, were written that Sheep Offspring and His Father's names.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Mt. Zion: here represents the seat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Mt. Zion: here represents the seat of the Messianic Kingdom on earth The Lamb: Rev. 5:6.<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>144,000: Rev. 7:4.</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 9:4, Dunya Model Baru 7:3</note><v n="2" />Ais beta dengar satu suara dari langit. Dia pung bunyi tu, bésar sama ke aer tarjún deng karás sama ke guntur. Ma itu suara talalu bagus, sama ke ada banya orang maen sasando.<bt>Then I heard a voice from the sky. It's sound, was big like a waterfall, and loud like thunder. But that aforementioned voice, was also very good like there were many people playing sasandos [NOTE: traditional Rotinese/Timorese stringed instrument].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="I hear a voice: see Rev."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">I hear a voice: see Rev. 10:4. Like the sound of many waters: see Rev. 1:15.<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>Loud thunder: see Rev. 6:1.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ju beta lia itu 144.000 orang tu ada badiri mangada sang Tuhan Allah, deng itu 4 binatang luar biasa yang kuliling Tuhan pung korsi parenta tu, deng itu 24 katua dong. Itu orang banya dong ada manyanyi satu lagu baru. Cuma dong sandiri sa yang tau itu lagu, ma orang laen sonde. Te dong ni yang su babae deng Tuhan, tagal Tuhan su pake Dia pung Ana pung dara ko tabús ame sang dong.<bt>And I saw those aforementioned 144.000 people were standing facing God, and those four extra-ordinary animals who surround that aforementioned chair of God's, and those elders. Those many people were singing a new song. Only they themselves knew that song, but other people didn't know it. Cuz (elaboration) it was they who were in a reciprocally good relationship with God, because God had used His Child's blood to fully *redeem them. [NOTE: “from the earth” undertranslated so as not to skew the information load.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bayar kontan ganti dong pung sala."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">bayar kontan ganti dong pung sala.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="They sing: Rev 13:12. Before the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">They sing: Rev 13:12. Before the throne...four living creatures...elders: Rev. 4.<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>TERM: eegorasmenoi 'redeemed' 5:9 fo buy back peopo fo bring um to God</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Dong pung idop barisi, sama ke orang bujang yang sonde parná tidor bakumpul deng parampuan. Dong iko-iko itu Domba Ana pi mana sa, te Tuhan su bayar ame sang dong pake Dia pung Ana pung dara, ko biar dong jadi Dia pung milik. Tagal itu, dong ni sama ke hasil partama yang orang bawa dari kabón ko sarakan kasi sang Tuhan deng itu Domba Ana.<bt>Their lives were clean/holy, like bachelors who have never slept together with a woman/women. They followed that Sheep Offspring, where it went, cuz (elaboration) God had paid (fully) for them using His Child's blood, so that they would become His possessions. Because of that, they here were like the first harvest which people bring from the garden to give to God and the Sheep Offspring.</bt><v n="5" />Dong ju sonde tau omong putar-balek, tagal dong pung hati barisi.<bt>They also did not speak deceptively, because their livers were clean/holy.</bt><note reference="14:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Sefanya 3:13</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tiga ana bua dari sorga bawa kabar<bt>Three angels bring news</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ais beta dapa lia Tuhan Allah pung ana bua satu lai dari sorga. Dia ada tarbáng tinggi-tinggi di langit, ko kasi tasiar Tuhan pung Kabar Bae yang sonde putus-putus. Dia tarbáng kuliling kasi tau samua orang di bumi, dari samua suku, samua bangsa, samua bahasa, deng samua negara.<bt>Then I saw another angel. He was flying high in the sky, in order to spread/scatter the Lord's Good News that never ends. He flew around telling all the people on the earth, from every nation, every clan, every language, and every country.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Another angel: angels have appeared already"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Another angel: angels have appeared already in Rev. 5:2, 10:1. Flying in midair: see Rev. 8:13.<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>TERM: Nation, tribe, language, people: see Rev. 5:9 "ohana, an language, an peopo, an country". The order differs from place to place, but probably could be regularized; it is the terms themselves that should be regularized more than their order. Check especially "language," which as inanimate does not need to be pluralized to be plural.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Dia batarea karás-karás bilang,<bt>He yelled loudly saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Bosong musti kasi hormat sang Tuhan Allah!<bt>“You(pl) must give honour to God!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Bosong musti angka tinggi-tinggi Dia pung nama yang hebat!<bt>You must lift up high His name which is tremendous/amazing! [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tagal dia pung waktu su sampe,<bt>Because the time has come for</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko Tuhan pareksa samua orang pung bekin-bekin.<bt>God to examine all people's deeds. [EXEG: LN, NLT, CEV]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Puji sang Dia!<bt>Praise Him!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Angka tinggi-tinggi Dia pung nama!<bt>Lift up high His name!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tagal Dia yang bekin ame langit deng bumi.<bt>Because He is the one who made the sky and the land.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Deng Dia yang parenta ko laut deng mata aer dong jadi samua.&gt;&gt;<bt>And He is the one who commanded that all the seas and the water springs come into being.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Omong abis bagitu, tarús beta dapa lia satu ana bua laen dari sorga, yang datang iko sang dia. Dia kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Su ancor! Su ancor! Kota Babel yang hebat tu, su ancor! Itu kota yang jahat tu, su rubu rata tana. Dolu itu kota sama ke palacor yang paksa-paksa samua bangsa di bumi minum mabo deng iko-iko dia pung basundal. Ma sakarang itu kota su rasa Tuhan pung mara!&gt;&gt;<bt>Finished speaking like that, next I saw another angel, who came with him. He told saying, “It's destroyed! It's destroyed! Babel city is destroyed! That aforementioned evil city, has fallen down to the ground. Previously that city was like a prostitute who forced people to drink until drunk and to follow her prostitution. But now that city has tasted/felt God's anger [+obviously]!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Babylon is fallen: see Rev. 18:2-3."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Babylon is fallen: see Rev. 18:2-3.</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 21:9, Yeremia 51:8, Dunya Model Baru 18:2</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ais beta dapa lia ana bua dari sorga yang laen lai, yang datang iko sang itu ana bua yang nomer dua tu. Dia batarea karás-karás bilang, &lt;&lt;Awas, ó! Samua orang yang songgo itu binatang buas deng dia pung patong, ko, tarima dia pung cap di testa, ko, di tangan, nanti dong ju rasa Tuhan pung mara!<bt>Then I saw yet another angel, who came following that number two angel. He shouted loudly saying, “Be careful, ó! All people who [traditional/non-Christian] worship that ferocious animal and his statue, or receive his stamp on their forehead, or arm, later they will also taste/feel God's anger!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="The First Beast: Rev. 13:1, 14-15."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">The First Beast: Rev. 13:1, 14-15. Mark: Rev. 13:16.<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Nanti Tuhan sandiri po'a datang Dia pung mara kasi sang dong, sama ke Dia kasi minum sang dong anggor kapala yang pait. Nanti Dia lempar buang sang dong pi api balerang yang manyala sonde abis-abis. Dia pung ana bua dari sorga dong, deng itu Domba Ana ju lia itu hal.<bt>Later God himself will pour out His anger on them, as if He is making them drink full strength wine that is bitter. Later He will throw expel them into the sulfur fire that burns without ending. His angels, and that Sheep Offspring also saw that matter.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***adjusted Sept 2005; problem: who is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">***adjusted Sept 2005; problem: who is where? in front of &gt; they saw it happen</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="TERM: the wine = wrath metaphor,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">TERM: the wine = wrath metaphor, this time</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dia lempar sang dong tu, di"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Dia lempar sang dong tu, di muka Dia pung ana bua dari sorga dong, deng di muka itu Domba Ana.</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 51:17, Carita Mula-mula 19:24, Yeskial 38:22</note><v n="11" />Pokonya, samua orang yang songgo itu binatang deng dia pung patong, ko, tarima ame dia pung cap, nanti dong dapa siksa bagitu deng sonde tau abis-abis. Asap dari dong pung sangsara nae kaluar siang-malam sonde tau barenti.&gt;&gt;<bt>The important thing is, all people who traditionally worships that animal and his statue, or, accept his stamp/brand/ identifying mark, later they will be endlessly tortured like that. And smoke from their suffering/torment rises day-night unceasingly.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***omission corrected Sept 2005"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">***omission corrected Sept 2005</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 34:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12-13" />Jadi itu samua pung maksud bilang, Tuhan Allah pung orang dong musti dengar bae-bae Dia pung parenta, parcaya tarús-tarús sang Yesus, deng jang ondor.<bt>So (consequently), all that means, God's people must listen carefully to His commands, and continually believe in Yesus, and not retreat. [EXEG: LN and Ex. Summ. #1 Gk “endure” here is about persevering in persecution and difficulties (part c below), not just about faithfulness (part a above)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***12-13 combined 2007"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">***12-13 combined 2007</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais beta dengar satu suara dari langit yang kasi tau sang beta bilang, &lt;&lt;Yohanis! Lu musti tulis bagini: mulai sakarang, kalo orang yang parcaya sang Tuhan Yesus dong mati, na, dong dapa ontong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then I heard a voice from the sky that told me saying, “Yohanis! You must write like this: from now on, if people who believe in the Lord Yesus die, na, they will obtain an advantage/benefit.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais Tuhan Allah pung Roh yang Barisi manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl! Nanti dong ontong batúl! Te dong su dapa susa sangsara di dunya, ma dong batahan ko iko Tuhan tarús. Jadi nanti Tuhan balas dong pung cape, deng dong sonde idop sangsara lai di sorga.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then God's Holy Spirit replied saying, “True! Later they will be truly advantaged! Cuz (elaboration) they have obtain suffering difficulty on earth, but they endured following God. So (consequently), later God will reciprocate their tiredness (=effort) and they live with out any more suffering in heaven.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ta erga autoon akolouthei met' autoon:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">ta erga autoon akolouthei met' autoon: information only, or skills? Erga probably includes the latter.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan pung hukuman di bumi sama ke pake sabit ko panen<bt>God2's punishment on earth is like using a sickle to harvest</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***title made more vivid Sept 2005"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">***title made more vivid Sept 2005</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ais itu, beta angka muka. Takuju sa, beta dapa lia satu awan puti bacaya, deng ada satu orang dudu di atas itu awan. Itu orang tu, tingka ke Manusia Tulen. Dia ada pake topi juara dari mas, deng ada pegang satu sabit tajam.<bt>After that, I lifted my head. Unexpectedly, I saw a shiny white cloud, and there was a person who sat on that cloud. That aforementioned person, was like the Ideal/Original Human (*Son of Man). He was wearing a champion hat from gold, and was holding a sharp sickle.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Son of Man: Rev. 1:13."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Son of Man: Rev. 1:13.</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 7:13</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ais beta dapa lia lai satu ana bua yang laen dari sorga, kaluar dari Tuhan pung Ruma Sambayang. Dia batarea kasi tau sang itu Orang di awan bilang, &lt;&lt;Pake itu sabit ko mulai panen su! Te dia pung waktu kumpul ame bumi pung hasil dong, su sampe.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then I saw again an angel, come out from God's Worship House. He yelled telling that person on the cloud saying, “Use that sickle to go harvest (imp)! Cuz (elaboration) the time to gather the earth's harvests, has come.”</bt><note reference="14:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yoel 3:13</note><v n="16" />Ais, itu Orang yang dudu di awan tu, ayun Dia pung sabit ko panen, deng kumpul ame bumi pung hasil dong.<bt>Then that Person who sat on that aforementioned cloud, wielded his sickle to harvest, and gathered up the earth's harvests.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ayun = wield, flash"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">ayun = wield, flash</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ju ada satu ana bua yang laen lai kaluar dari Ruma Sambayang di sorga. Dia ju ada pegang satu sabit ko mau ketu bua.<bt>Then there was another angel came out of the Worship House in heaven. He was also holding a sickle to go pick fruit. [NOTE: this is also a sickle, not just a knife. Same Gk word as in 14-16.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***17-19 changed to sickle 2007"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">***17-19 changed to sickle 2007</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ais, ada satu ana bua yang laen kaluar datang dari itu tampa bakar dara kayu wangi di Ruma Sambayang di sorga. Ana bua ni pung tugas, andia jaga api di itu tampa bakar dara kayu wangi. Dia batarea suru itu ana bua yang pegang itu sabit bilang, &lt;&lt;Pake lu pung sabit tu, ko pi ketu bua di bumi su! Te di sana pohon anggor pung bua dong su masak-masak.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then there was another angel came out from that place of burning resin in the Worship House in heaven. This angel's job, was to guard that place of burning resin. He yelled ordering that angel who held that sickle saying, “Use that sickle of yours, to go pick fruit on the earth (imp)! Cuz (elaboration) the grape trees/bushes' fruits there are ripe.”</bt><v n="19" />Ais, itu ana bua ayun dia pung sabit pi bumi, ko potong ame anggor pung rangke dong. Ju dia kasi maso itu bua anggor dong pi dalam bak parés. Tarús dong inja-inja ko mau ame dia pung aer. Inja-inja bua anggor di bak parés tu, andia Tuhan pung mara.<bt>Then that angel wielded his sickle went to the earth, to cut those grapes' bunches. And He put those grapes into a pressing tank. Next they step all over [the grapes] to get their liquid/juice. Stepping on grapes in that pressing tanks, is God's anger.</bt><v n="20" />Itu bak parés ada di luar kota. Waktu dong inja itu anggor pung bua dong, ju dara malele kaluar bam-banya. Itu dara malele sama ke kali satu, dia pung panjang 300 kilo, deng dia pung dalam satu meter satenga.<bt>That pressing tank was outside the city. When they stepped on those grapes, then lots of blood flowed out. That blood flowed like a river, it's length 300 kilometers, and it's depth one and half meters.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Carolyn Dyk illustrations?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Carolyn Dyk illustrations?</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:20" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani tulis itu kali pung panjang bilang, &lt;&lt;1.600 <span class="Italic">stadia&gt;&gt;,</span> andia 296-300 kilometer. Deng itu kali pung dalam dong tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;sama tinggi deng kuda pung tali kekáng&gt;&gt;, andia satu meter satenga. Dong pung kuda lebe bésar dari kuda Rote.<bt>The Yunani language Bible writes that river's length saying, “1,600 <span class="Italic">stadia</span>”, that is 296-300 kilometers. And that river's depth they write saying, “as high as a horse bit”, that is one and a half metres. Their horses are taller than Rote horses.</bt></note><note reference="14:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 63:3, Manangis Makarereu 1:15, Dunya Model Baru 19:15</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuju ana bua dari sorga bawa tuju calaka bésar pi bumi<bt>Seven angels from heaven bring seven great calamities to earth [NOTE to daughter translations: NRSV, NIV; every English translation seems to have a different title for this section, so just go with what's here -- it's as good/bad as any]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Yohanis lia sorga pung isi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Yohanis lia sorga pung isi</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="15" />
      <v n="1" />Ais itu, beta dapa lia satu hal di langit yang luar biasa, sampe beta heran mau mati. Ada tuju ana bua dari sorga, satu-satu pegang kuasa ko kirim calaka bésar pi bumi. Ini tuju calaka ni, andia calaka tarahir. Kalo dong samua su jadi, na, dia pung arti bilang, Tuhan Allah pung hati su dingin, sampe Dia su sonde mara lai sang manusia.<bt>After that, I saw extra-ordinary thing in the sky to the point that I was totally amazed. There were seven angels, whom each one had the authority to send big catastrophes to earth. These seven aforementioned catastrophes, were the final catastrophes. If they all had happened, na, it meant that God's liver was cool to the point that He was no longer angry with humans.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="plague: Rev. 9:18, great disaster that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">plague: Rev. 9:18, great disaster that injures and kills, often seen as God's punishment; a blow, calamity, terrible trouble</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Ais beta dapa lia laut yang manyala sama ke kaca yang tacampor deng api. Beta ju dapa lia banya orang yang badiri di itu laut pung pinggir. Dong tu, orang yang sonde iko itu binatang buas, sonde songgo dia pung patong, deng sonde tarima dia pung cap. Dong samua ada pegang alat musik sama ke sasando yang dong tarima dari Tuhan Allah.<bt>Then I saw a sea that shone/burned like glass which was mixed with fire. I also saw many people who were standing at that sea's edge. They were the ones, the people who did not follow that aforementioned ferocious animal, did not worship his statute, and did not accept his stamp. They all held musical instruments like sasandos which they had received from God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Pool of glass: See Rev. 4:6"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Pool of glass: See Rev. 4:6 same Conquered: Rev. 2:7, 6:2.<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>Beast: Rev. 13:1, 14-15, 16-17. Harps: Rev. 5:8.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ais dong manyanyi satu lagu dari ba'i Musa, andia Tuhan Allah pung orang suru-suru dolu-dolu. Itu orang dong ju manyanyi satu lagu ko puji-puji sang Yesus. Te dolu orang bunu bekin mati sang Dia, sama ke orang bunu domba ana di Tuhan Allah pung Ruma Sambayang ko bekin dingin Dia pung hati. Dong manyanyi bilang,<bt>Then they sang a song from Gf/Ff Musa, that is God's servant long ago. Those people also sang a song to praise Yesus. Cuz (elaboration) previously people had killed Him, like people kill a sheep offspring in God's Worship House to cool His liver. (=ask forgiveness; make things right with God). They sang saying, [NOTE to daughter translations: UNS's couldn't connect the dots about the Lamb without this explication.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="[NOTE to daughter translations: consultants have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">[NOTE to daughter translations: consultants have differing opinions on whether explicating context of song of Moses above is 1) adding, 2) overtranslating, or 3) implicit &gt; explicit from context of song making the song more powerful. We've compromised here and put it in a footnote.]</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais dong manyanyi satu lagu yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Ais dong manyanyi satu lagu yang dolu Tuhan Allah pung orang suru-suru Musa manyanyi waktu Tuhan bawa Dia pung orang dong kaluar dari Masir, dong pung tampa sangsara tu.</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:3" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Musa karang itu lagu waktu Tuhan bawa orang Isra'el dong kaluar dari Masir, andia dong pung tampa sangsara.<bt>Musa composed that song when God took the Isra'el people out of Masir, that suffering place of theirs.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Botong puji-puji Tuhan Allah!<bt>“We praise God!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Botong angka tinggi-tinggi Dia pung nama!<bt>We lift up high His name!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tagal Tuhan pung kuasa, luar biasa.<bt>Because God's power, is extra-ordinary.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng Tuhan pung hebat, talalu heran.<bt>And God's greatness, is sooo amazing.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan su pegang parenta sang samua suku-bangsa di bumi.<bt>God rules all the nations on earth.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan su jadi Raja kasi samua suku di dunya.<bt>God has become King for all the clans in the world.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Samua yang Tuhan bekin, luar biasa!<bt>God's deeds, are extra-ordinary!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tuhan pung karjá, talalu bagus!<bt>God's work, is truly good!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tuhan pung jalan, lurus mau mati!<bt>God's road/path, is very, very straight (=righteous)!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tuhan pung idop, paling batúl!<bt>God's life, is very correct!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Moses song: Exodus 15:1-18, Deuteronomy 32:1-44,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Moses song: Exodus 15:1-18, Deuteronomy 32:1-44, the song Moses sang or composed.</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 15:1-18</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="4" />Samua orang angka tinggi-tinggi Tuhan pung nama,<bt>All the people lift up high God's name,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">samua orang puji-puji Tuhan pung bae.<bt>all the people praise God's goodness.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tagal cuma Tuhan sandiri yang barisi.<bt>Because only God himself is the one who is clean/holy.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Cuma Dia sandiri sa yang sonde ada pung sala.<bt>Only just He himself is the one who doesn't have sin.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nanti samua suku-bangsa datang sémba sang Tuhan.<bt>Later all people will come to worship God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nanti samua suku datang minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan.<bt>Later all clans will come to request thankyou to God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tagal samua orang su lia Tuhan pung karjá yang bae.<bt>Because all people have seen God's deeds which are good.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng samua orang su tau Tuhan pung hati yang lurus.&gt;&gt;<bt>And all people have known God's liver which is straight/righteous.” [EXEG: Gk. /dikaiwmata/ for last two lines as “righteous acts/deeds” (NLT, LN) rather than “judgements” (NRSV) -- fits context better.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Respeck your name: Rev. 11:18. Glorify"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Respeck your name: Rev. 11:18. Glorify your name: Rev. 11:13, 4:7.<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>Holy: Rev. 16:5. Separate, God, different from people.</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeremia 10:7, Lagu Puji dong 86:9</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Waktu itu orang dong manyanyi abis, ju beta dapa lia itu Kamar yang Paling Barisi di Tuhan pung Ruma Sambayang di sorga, deng dia pung kaen pele ada tabuka lebar.<bt>When those people finished singing, then I saw that that Room that is Very Holy in God's Worship House in heaven, and it's blocking cloth was wide open. [NOTE: many lgs/UNS cannot have an open room (NLT actually sounds funny in English), but the cloth is wide open.] [EXEG: for “tent of witness” see summary discussion in TH. We follow their recommended solution, which seems to make the best sense in context.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***adjusted Sept 2005;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">***adjusted Sept 2005;</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 38:21</note><v n="6" />Ais beta lia itu tuju ana bua dari sorga yang bawa itu tuju calaka tu. Dong ada jalan kaluar dari Tuhan pung Ruma Sambayang. Dong pake pakean yang bacaya puti barisi, deng pake salempang dari mas tulen.<bt>Then I saw those seven angels who brought those seven aforementioned catastrophes. They were walking out of God's Worship House. They wore clothes that were shiny clean white, and they wore sashes of original/pure gold.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Gold bands: Rev. 1:13."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Gold bands: Rev. 1:13.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Tarús beta lia satu dari itu 4 binatang luar biasa yang ada di sablá Tuhan pung korsi parenta, bagi tuju bokor mas kasi sang itu tuju ana bua dong. Itu tuju bokor dong, satu-satu ta'isi deng hukuman dari Tuhan Allah. Dia yang ada tarús sampe salamanya. Te Dia su siap ko po'a Dia pung mara pi di bumi.<bt>Then2 I saw those four extra-ordinary animals who were at the side of God's aforementioned ruling chair, divide out seven (wide rimmed) gold bowls to those seven angels. Each one of those seven bowls were filled with judgements from God. He is the one who exists continually forever. He was ready to pour out His anger on the world.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bokor = basin, large bowl"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">bokor = basin, large bowl</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Sonde lama lai ju, itu Ruma Sambayang su ponu deng asap yang kaluar dari Tuhan Allah pung hebat deng Dia pung kuasa. Sonde ada satu orang ju yang bisa maso pi situ. Itu tuju ana bua dong musti po'a bekin abis itu tuju calaka di bumi, baru orang bisa maso pi situ.<bt>Not much longer (=soon), then that Worship House was full of smoke, which came out of God's greatness and His power. There was not a single person who could enter in there. Those seven angels had to finish pouring out those seven catastrophes on the earth, before a person could go in there. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><note reference="15:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 40:34, 1 Raja-raja dong 8:10-11, 2 Sajara Isra'el deng Yahuda 5:13-14, Yesaya 6:4</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Allah pung mara tapo'a pi bumi<bt>God's anger poured out on the earth</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="16" />
      <v n="1" />Ais beta dengar ada satu suara karás kaluar dari Ruma Sambayang ko parenta sang itu tuju ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Pi su! Angka bawa itu bokor dong ko po'a buang Tuhan pung mara pi bumi su.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then I heard a loud voice come out of the Worship House to order those seven angels saying, “Go! Pick up and take those bowls in order to pour out God's anger on the earth (imp).”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Dengar bagitu, ju ana bua yang partama po'a buang dia pung bokor pung isi pi bumi. Takuju sa, calaka kaná samua orang yang parná tarima itu binatang buas pung cap, deng orang yang songgo dia pung patong. Dong kaná luka puruk yang saki mau mati.<bt>Hearing like that, then the first angel poured out his bowl's contents on the earth. Suddenly, calamity struck all the people who had ever received that wild animal's stamp, and the people who traditional worshipped that statue of his. They were afflicted with rotten sores that were terribly painful.</bt><note reference="16:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 9:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ais ana bua nomer dua po'a buang dia pung bokor pung isi pi laut. Takuju sa, aer di laut jadi dara baboo busuk, sama ke orang mati pung dara. Ju samua yang idop di laut, mati abis.<bt>Then angel number two poured out his bowl's content on the sea. Unexpectedly, the water in the sea became rotten smelling blood, like a dead person's blood. And everything that lived in the sea, completely died.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Exodus 7:20-21."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Exodus 7:20-21.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ais ana bua nomer tiga po'a buang dia pung bokor pung isi pi kali deng mata aer dong. Ju itu aer samua jadi dara.<bt>Then angel number three poured out his bowl's contents on the rivers and water springs. And all those waters became blood.</bt><note reference="16:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 7:17-21, Lagu Puji dong 78:44</note><v n="5" />Ais beta dengar ana bua satu dari sorga, yang urus samua aer di bumi. Dia puji sang Tuhan Allah bilang,<bt>Then I heard an angel, who was (in charge of) managing all the water on earth. He praised God saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Oo, Tuhan!<bt>“O Lord!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan yang barisi!<bt>Lord  (=you) is the one who is holy!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan yang sonde parná sala!<bt>Lord  (=you) is the one who is never wrong/sinful!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tuhan su ada dari mula-mula,<bt>Lord  (=you) has lived from the beginning,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng Tuhan nanti ada sampe salamanya.<bt>and Lord (=you) will (surely) live forever.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan su putus parkara deng batúl.<bt>Lord  (=you) have judged cases correctly.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan su kasi jato hukuman yang pas.<bt>Lord  (=you) has given judgements/punishments that are appropriate.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="6" />Orang dong su kasi tumpa<bt>People have spilled</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tuhan pung orang pung dara.<bt>the Lord's people's blood.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Orang dong su bunu bekin mati<bt>People have killed</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tuhan pung jubir dong.<bt>the Lord's spokesperson.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Andia ko, Tuhan su paksa ko dong ju minum dara.<bt>That's why, the Lord  (=you) has forced them to also drink blood ( = suffer).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Andia ko, Tuhan su balas deng kasi hukuman yang batúl.&gt;&gt;<bt>That's why, the Lord  (=you) has reciprocaed with a correct punishment.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ais itu, beta dengar satu suara kaluar dari meja korban, yang manyao bilang,<bt>After that, I heard a voice come out from the sacrifice table which replied saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Batúl! Tuhan Allah yang paling kuasa.<bt>“True! God is the one who is most powerful.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Batúl! Tuhan Allah yang paling hebat.<bt>True! God is the one who is most great.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tuhan yang putus parkara deng batúl.<bt>God is the one who judges correctly.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tuhan yang kasi jato hukuman yang pas.&gt;&gt;<bt>God is the one who gives punishments that are appropriate.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ais ju ana bua nomer ampa po'a buang dia pung bokor pung isi pi matahari. Takuju sa matahari jadi panas talalu, sampe manusia dong tabakar.<bt>Then angel number four poured out the contents of his bowl on the sun. Unexpectedly/suddenly the sun became exceedingly hot, to the point that humans were burned.</bt><v n="9" />Samua manusia yang kaná bakar tu, dong kutuk Tuhan Allah pung nama, tagal Dia yang suru kirim itu calaka kasi sang dong. Biar bagitu, ma sonde ada satu orang ju yang tobat, ais bale kambali pi Tuhan, ko, angka puji sang Dia.<bt>All those humans who were burned, they cursed God's name, because He was the one who ordered that calamity to be sent to them. Even that being the case, nevertheless there was not a single person who *repented, then changed returning to God to praised Him. [EXEG: Gk: giving him glory here; CEV]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ais, itu ana bua nomer lima po'a buang dia pung bokor pung isi pi itu binatang buas pung korsi parenta. Takuju sa ju, galáp gulita tutu ame samua orang yang songgo sang dia, sampe dong makan gigi, ko biar dong bisa tahan sangsara.<bt>Then, that angel number five poured out his bowls contents on that wild animal's ruling chair. Unexpectedly, then pitch darkness covered all the people who worshipped him, until they ground their teeth, so that they could endure that suffering.</bt><note reference="16:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 10:21</note><v n="11" />Dong ju kutuk sang Tuhan Allah di sorga, tagal dong pung luka dong saki mau mati. Biar bagitu, ma sonde ada satu ju yang barenti bekin jahat, ais bale ko iko sang Tuhan.<bt>They also cursed God in heaven because those sores of theirs, were extremely painful. Even though it was like that, nevertheless there was not even one who stopped doing evil, and turned to follow/obey God2.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ais ana bua nomer anam po'a buang dia pung bokor pung isi pi itu kali bésar, nama Efrat. Ju itu kali pung aer karíng memang. Ais dong bekin jalan di situ kasi raja-raja deng tantara dong yang nanti datang dari sablá timur.<bt>Then angel number six poured out his bowl's contents on that big river, named Efrat. Then that river's water dried up right away. Then they made a road there for kings and armies that would later come from the east. [DISCOURSE/EXEG: Gk only mentions kings here, but context is major battle (e.g. vs.14). NLT mentions armies in this verse. Regional lg patterns for background-foreground info require it to be placed here.]</bt><note reference="16:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 11:15</note><v n="13" />Ju beta dapa lia tiga setan yang jahat. Dong pung model sama ke katak. Satu kaluar dari itu ular naga pung mulu. Satu kaluar dari itu binatang buas pung mulu. Deng satu lai kaluar dari itu ular naga pung jubir tukang putar-balek pung mulu.<bt>Then I saw three evil spirits. Their shape/forms were like frogs. One came out of that dragon snake's mouth. One came out of that wild animal's mouth. And one more came out of that dragon snake's deceptive spokesperson's mouth.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="jubir pakane'o - da guy dat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">jubir pakane'o - da guy dat say he fo God but he bulai ; katak = frog</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Itu tiga setan dong ada pung kuasa ko bekin tanda heran macam-macam. Dong kaluar ko pi katumu samua raja di dunya, ais dong bajanji satu waktu ko mau pi baparáng lawan Tuhan Allah yang paling kuasa. Ma itu waktu yang dong su bajanji tu, andia Tuhan Allah pung waktu yang Dia su pili ame ko kasi kala Dia pung musu samua.<bt>Those three evil spirits had power to do all sorts of miracles. They came out to go meet all the kings in the world, then they promised each other a time to go war against God who is most powerful. But that time which they promised, is God's time which He had already chosen to defeat all his enemies.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Great Day of God Almighty: Rev."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Great Day of God Almighty: Rev. 19:11-15.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15-16" />Itu tampa yang nanti dong bakumpul ko baparáng tu, bahasa Ibrani bilang, <span class="Italic">Armagedon.</span><bt>That aforementioned place where they will gather to go to war, Hebrew language says <span class="Italic">Armagedon.</span> [NOTE: some MTT's want to know what ‘Armadegon’ means. The scholars have wide ranging views on what it means and where it is, and whether or not it is symbolic, cryptic, or geographical. Best discussion in Mounce (on TW4). Info not clear enough to make a coherent ftn.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Yesus Kristus ju omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Inga bae-bae! Takuju sa, te Beta datang sama ke pancuri yang orang sonde sangka-sangka. Orang yang mete jaga deng pake pakean langkáp dong, paling ontong. Te nanti kalo Beta datang, dia sonde dapa malu, tagal orang sonde dapa lia dia pung talanjang.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus Kristus also speaks/spoke saying, “Listen well! Unexpectedly I will come like a thief which people do not expect. The person who stays awake watches/guards with all his/her clothes on are most fortunate. Cuz (elaboration:grounds) when I come, s/he will not be embarrassed, because people will not see his/her nakedness.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Orang yang barontong, andia orang yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Orang yang barontong, andia orang yang bajaga deng pake pakean langkáp.</Message></Annotation><note reference="16:15-16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 24:43-44, Lukas 12:39-40, Dunya Model Baru 3:3; 2 Raja-raja dong 23:29, Sakaria 12:11</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ais ana bua nomer tuju po'a buang dia pung bokor pung isi pi di angin. Ju Tuhan Allah omong deng suara bésar dari Dia pung korsi parenta di Ruma Sambayang bilang, &lt;&lt;Su abis! Beta pung mara su tapo'a abis samua!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then angel number seven poured out his bowl's contents on the wind. And God spoke with a loud voice from His ruling chair in the Worship House saying, “It's finished! My anger is all poured out now!”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phoonee megalee ek tou naou apo"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">phoonee megalee ek tou naou apo tou thronou legousa: What is the relationship between the sanctuary and the throne?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Tarús ada kilat yang basambar, deng guntur yang babunyi bésar basambung. Deng tana tagoyang yang paling bésar yang balóm parná jadi di bumi, ju datang.<bt>Next there was lightning that struck out and thunder that connected sounding loud. And a very big earthquake, which has never yet happened before on earth, also came. [EXEG: “since people were on the earth” undertranslated so as not to skew the information load.]</bt><note reference="16:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 8:5, 11:13, 19</note><v n="19" />Itu waktu, Tuhan Allah sonde lupa kota Babel pung jahat. Dia pake itu tana tagoyang luar biasa, sampe itu kota hebat tabalá bagi tiga. Dia bekin bagitu, ko biar orang Babel dong rasa Dia pung mara. Kota-kota laen di dunya ju rubu buang.<bt>At that time, God did not forget Babel city's evil. He used that extra-ordinary earthquake so that that great city was divided in three. He did like that, so that the Babel people would taste His anger. Other cities in the world also were destroyed. [EXEG: second use of wine-cup = anger/destruction. Since the image is confusing, we've just kept the grounds for comparison here to avoid over-translation.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="TERM: Second use of the wine"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">TERM: Second use of the wine = wrath metaphor "God come real huhu an no take da bad kine stuff dose peopo stay doing. He goin make dose peopo suffa real bad from da burning sulfur, in front da spesho angel guys an God's Baby Sheep. Dass jalike wen one guy make anodda guy drink too much real strong wine, fo make um come real drunk."</Message></Annotation><note reference="16:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 51:17</note><v n="20" />Itu waktu pulo-pulo dong tanggalám bagitu sa, deng gunung-gunung dong ju ilang buang samua.<bt>At that time the islands submerged just like that (=without explanation), and the mountains also completely disappeared gone.</bt><note reference="16:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 6:14</note><v n="21" />Ada ju ujan es batu yang bésar-bésar jato dari langit ko tendes ame manusia. Itu es batu dong pung barát, ada yang sampe ampa pulu kilo.<bt>There were also rain ice rocks that was very big falling from the sky to mash/press down on/crush humans. Those rocks' heaviness, there were those that were up to forty kilos.</bt><note reference="16:21" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;sama barát deng satu <span class="Italic">talenta</span>&gt;&gt;. Satu <span class="Italic">talenta</span> pung barát tu, andia 34-40 kilogram.<bt>The Yunani language Bible writes saying, “as heavy as one <span class="Italic">talenta”. </span>The weight of one talenta is 34-40 kilograms. [EXEG: see NLT note and LN. TH is all over the map.]</bt></note>Tagal itu ujan es yang bekin sangsara sang dong, andia ko manusia dong kutuk sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>Because of that ice rain which made them suffer, that's why humans cursed God.</bt><note reference="16:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 9:23, Dunya Model Baru 11:19</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Allah pung ana bua banding kota Babel deng parampuan nakal<bt>God's angel compares the city of Babel with a whore/ prostitute</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tuhan Allah pung ana bua kasi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Tuhan Allah pung ana bua kasi tau orang di kota Babel pung jahat</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="17" />
      <v n="1" />Ais ju satu dari itu tuju ana bua dari sorga yang pegang itu bokor kosong dong, datang omong deng beta bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari sini dolo! Beta mau kasi tunju sang lu Tuhan Allah pung cara hukum itu palacor yang paling jahat. Dia tu, andia itu kota bésar yang dong kasi bangun deka banya aer.<bt>And then one of those seven angels who held those empty bowls, came to speak with me saying, “Come here! I want to show you God's way of punishing that prostitute who is exceedingly evil. She is that big city which they have built near many/much water. [EXEG: while English translations vary between “whore (promiscuous woman, no pay)” and “prostitute (promiscuous, for pay)”, the Gk seems to lean toward the latter (LN, BADG).]</bt><note reference="17:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeremia 51:13</note><v n="2" />Dolu raja-raja dari mana-mana datang maen serong deng itu kota pung orang dong. Orang laen dong ju datang minum mabo, deng iko-iko itu kota pung hohongge.&gt;&gt;<bt>Previously kings from all over came frequently to play off-track (sexually) with that city's people. Other people also came drinking to the point of drunkeness and following that sexual immorality of that city. [NOTE to daughter translations: (high-level) The book-level themes, the Gk, and the Hebrew it evokes (e.g. Amos), are playing at two levels 1) sexual immorality, and 2) unfaithfulness to God [which is the primary point here at a high level]. Some terms (like maen basundal) are too restrictive to the first reading, even though they resonate nicely with prostitution. Other terms (like maen serong) can carry both senses. Try to find a broader term to carry through the remaining chapters.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** metonymy explicated"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** metonymy explicated</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="This is not the wine ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">This is not the wine = wrath metaphor. It is related, but does not symbolize wrath.</Message></Annotation><note reference="17:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 23:17, Yeremia 51:7</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ais itu, beta takaná Tuhan Allah pung Roh, ju itu ana bua dari sorga angka bawa sang beta pi satu tampa sunyi. Di situ beta dapa lia satu parampuan ada dudu di atas satu binatang buas warna mera manyala. Itu binatang pung kapala ada tuju, deng dia pung tandok, sapulu. Di dia pung badan samua ada tatulis kata-kata yang bekin hina sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>Then I was affected by God's Spirit, and that angel lifted brought me to an deserted place. There I saw a woman sitting on a red/scarlet coloured ferocious animal. That animals heads were seven, and it's horns, ten. All over its body were written words which are offensive to God. [NOTE to daughter translations: CHECK that your team and UNS's can identify who /beta/ is in first sentence. If they can't, then /beta, andia Yohanis yang ada tulis ni,/]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kai eidon: introducing a new vision."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">kai eidon: introducing a new vision. Nestle has the paragraph break in the middle of the verse.</Message></Annotation><note reference="17:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 13:1</note><v n="4" />Itu parampuan ada pake pakean alus yang warna mera deng warna ungu. Dia pung barias dong dari mas, batu mangkilat yang mahal, deng mutiara. Dia ada pegang satu cangkir mas yang ponu deng anggor di dia pung tangan kanan. Itu anggor tu, andia dia pung hohongge, deng samua hal jahat deng kotor yang laen yang dia bekin.<bt>That woman was wearing fine cloths that were red colour and purple colour. Her jewelry was from gold, expensive jewels, and from pearls. She was holding a gold glass which was full of wine in her right hand. That wine, was her sexual immorality/ promiscuity, and all the evil and dirty other things which she had done.</bt><note reference="17:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeremia 51:7</note><v n="5" />Di dia pung testa ada tatulis satu nama, yang dia pung arti masi rahasia. Itu tulisan bilang bagini:<bt>On her forehead was written a name, whose meaning was still a secret. That writing said like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Beta ni, Babel!<bt>I am Babel!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Andia, kota yang paling hebat!<bt>I am the greatest city!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Samua macam jahat di dunya,<bt>All the kinds of evil in the world,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">asal dari beta.<bt>originate from me.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Samua yang maen serong di bumi,<bt>All who are sexually improper on the earth,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ba'akar di beta.<bt>have their roots/source in me.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ais beta lia, te itu parampuan su mabok barát, tagal dia su minum Tuhan Allah pung orang dong pung dara. Dia pung arti bilang, dia su bunu Tuhan Allah pung orang dong, tagal dong sonde barenti kasi tau orang so'al Yesus.<bt>Then I saw (contrary to expectation) that woman was heavily drunk, because she had drunk God's people's blood. Meaning, she murdered God's people, because they did not stop talking about Yesus. [EXEG: see THandbook for seeing martyrs as part of God's people. NRSV, NLT]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Lia bagitu, ju beta tanganga deng heran mau mati.<bt>Seeing like that, I was open-mouthed (=dumb founded) and extremely amazed.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ma itu ana bua tanya sang beta bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko lu tanganga bodo bagitu? Mari ko beta kasi tau itu parampuan jahat pung arti. Bagitu ju deng itu binatang buas yang dia nae tu. Andia yang ada pung kapala tuju, deng tandok sapulu.<bt>But that angel asked me saying, “Why are you open-mouthed stupidly (=speechless) like that? Come, so that I can tell the meaning of that evil woman. Like that also with that aforementioned ferocious animal which she rode. That is, the one with seven heads, and ten horns.</bt><v n="8" />Dolu itu binatang buas idop di bumi, ma sakarang dia su sonde ada lai. Ma sonde lama lai, te dia datang kambali dari itu lobang sangsara yang sonde ada pung dasar. Itu waktu, ada orang yang idop di dunya, yang dong pung nama sonde tatulis dalam Domba Ana pung Tulisan yang Tuhan Allah su tulis memang waktu Dia balóm bekin ini dunya. Nanti itu orang dong tanganga lia itu binatang buas, tagal dia su kambali. Ma kalo dia su datang, na, nanti Tuhan Allah lempar buang sang dia pi dalam laut api balerang yang manyala sonde pake barenti.<bt>Previously that ferocious animal lived on the earth, but now he is no longer there/no longer exists. But not much longer (=soon), te2 (sudden or contrary to expectation) he comes again from that hole of suffering which does not have a foundation. At that time, there will be people who live in the world, whose names are not written in the Sheep Offspring's Writing, which God has written ahead of time from before He made this world. Later those people will be open-mouthed seeing that aforementioned ferocious animal, because he has returned. But if/when he has come, na, God will cast him out into the sea of fiery sulphur where the flames never stop. [DISCOURSE: don't put quote margin in here as it implies “change of speaker” in these languages.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="TERM: Book of Life"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">TERM: Book of Life</Message></Annotation><note reference="17:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 7:7, Dunya Model Baru 11:7, Lagu Puji dong 69:29</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Orang yang pintar batúl bisa mangarti ini hal. Itu binatang buas pung kapala tuju pung arti, andia tuju gunung. Itu palacor ada dudu di atas itu gunung dong. Deng itu tuju kapala dong ju pung arti, andia tuju raja.<bt>The person/whoever is truly smart/clever/wise can understand this matter. The meaning of that wild animal's seven heads, is seven mountains. That aforementioned prostitute, is sitting on those mountains. And the meaning of those seven heads, is seven kings. [EXEG: Mounce notes “This calls for a mind with wisdom” may be a warning to interpret with care, or an aside to the effect that what follows “is the clue for those who can interpret it” (NEB).]</bt><v n="10" />Dari itu tuju raja tu, lima su mati. Satu ada dudu parenta sakarang. Yang satu lai balóm datang. Ma kalo dia su datang, dia cuma pegang parenta sabantar sa.<bt>From those seven kings, five are dead. One is ruling now. The other one has not yet come. But when he comes, he will only rule for a little while.</bt><v n="11" />Sakarang beta kasi tau so'al itu binatang buas yang dolu idop, ma sakarang su mati. Dolu dia ju maso itu tuju raja, ma nanti dia kambali pegang parenta ko jadi raja nomer dalapan. Nanti dia ju kaná ancor buang.<bt>Now I will tell about that aforementioned ferocious animal who previously alive, but now is dead. Previously he also was one of that seven kings, but later he will return to rule to become king number eight. Later he will be (completely) destroyed.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Later he will recieve a tormenting"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Later he will recieve a tormenting punishment that will never end. (not justified)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Itu sapulu tandok pung arti, andia sapulu raja. Dong balóm pegang parenta. Nanti dong tarima kuasa ko pegang parenta sama-sama deng itu binatang buas, ma cuma sabantar sa.<bt>The meaning of those aforementioned ten horns, is ten kings. They have not yet ruled. Later they will receive authority to rule together with that aforementioned ferocious animal, but only for a little while. [EXEG: NLT, CEV, LN]</bt><note reference="17:12" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani di sini bisa ada dua arti. Andia: 1) cuma sabantar sa; ko, 2) satu jam sa.<bt>The Yunani language Bible here can have two meanings. That is: 1) just for a moment; or, 2) one hour.</bt></note><note reference="17:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 7:24</note><v n="13" />Te dong samua ba'akór ko ofer dong pung kuasa kasi pi itu binatang buas.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) they all agreed to hand over their authority to that aforementioned ferocious animal.</bt><v n="14" />Itu raja dong nanti pi baparáng lawan itu Domba Ana. Ma itu Domba Ana deng Dia pung orang dong nanti kasi kala sang dong samua. Itu orang-orang yang iko sang itu Domba Ana tu, andia orang yang Dia su pili deng pange ame, yang batahan iko sang Dia. Nanti dong manáng, tagal itu Domba Ana talalu hebat. Cuma Dia sa, Raja di atas samua raja, deng Bos di atas samua bos.<bt>Those kings later will go war again that Sheep Offspring. But that Sheep Offspring and His people will later defeat them all. Those people who follow that aforementioned Sheep Offspring, they are the people whom He chose and called to endure following Him. Later they will win, because that Sheep Offspring is very amazing. Only just Him is King over all kings, and the Boss over all bosses.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Deng itu aer banya yang ada deka itu palacor, andia orang dari samua suku, samua bangsa, samua bahasa, deng samua negara di bumi.<bt>And that much/many water that is near that aforementioned prostitute, that is people from every clan, every nation, every language, and every country on earth. [EXEG: Gk “multitudes/crowds” here (slightly different from other lists in REV) is OK as /bangsa/.]</bt><v n="16" />Itu sapulu raja deng itu binatang buas tu nanti mulai binci sang itu parampuan muka tabal yang sonde tau malu. Nanti dong rampas ame dia pung pakean deng barang samua, ais kasi tenga sang dia talanjang bulat di situ. Ais dong ju makan dia pung daging. Tarús, dia pung badan pung sisa, dong lempar buang pi dalam api.<bt>Those ten kings and that aforementioned ferocious animal later will begin to hate that aforementioned thick faced woman who doesn't know shame. Later they will loot her clothes and all her things, then leave her stark naked there. Then they will also eat her flesh. Next, the remains of her body, they will throw away in the fire.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="muka tabal = sonde tau malu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">muka tabal = sonde tau malu</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Tuhan Allah sandiri yang bekin sampe itu sapulu raja dong samua basakongkol, ko sarakan dong pung kuasa kasi sang itu binatang buas, sampe dia bekin ancor itu parampuan. Deng bagitu, Tuhan Allah pung rancana samua nanti jadi.<bt>God himself is the one who has made it so that those ten kings are all in agreement, to hand over their power/authority to that ferocious animal, to the point that he will destroy that woman. In that way, God's plans will all happen.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Naa! Itu palacor yang lu lia tu, andia itu kota hebat yang parenta samua raja di bumi.&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa [+shift to conclusion]! That aforementioned woman, is that great city which rules all the kings on earth.” [DISCOURSE: don't add quote margin here.] [NOTE to daughter translations: if personification doesn't work, try “leader/prominent people of that city...”]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Allah pung ana bua carita kota Babel pung rubu<bt>An angel stories about Babel city's destruction</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** extensive changes to the pronouns"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** extensive changes to the pronouns and rethinking the metonymy throughout this passage (MC, Barbara, Chuck)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="18" />
      <v n="1" />Ais itu, beta dapa lia satu ana bua laen turun datang dari sorga. Dia ada pung kuasa deng cahaya yang hebat sampe bekin taráng samua bumi.<bt>After that, I saw another angel come down from heaven. He had power/authority and brightness that was great/amazing to the point that it gave light to all the earth.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="After that, I saw another angel"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">After that, I saw another angel coming down from heaven. He had great authority and because of his great brightness the whole earth became light. 18.2 YKA Revelation 18.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Meta tauta eidon allon ...: like"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Meta tauta eidon allon ...: like the parallel passages</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Dia pake suara bésar ko kasi tau bilang,<bt>He use a loud voice to tell saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Su rubu! Su rubu! Kota Babel su rubu!<bt>“It's destroyed! It's destroyed! Babel city is destroyed!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Su jato! Su jato! Itu kota hebat tu, su jato!<bt>It's fallen! It's fallen! That great city, has fallen!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia su jadi setan dong pung tampa tenga.<bt>It has become evil spirits'1 living place.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia su jadi samua roh jahat dong pung tana asal.<bt>It has become every evil spirits'2 native land.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Gk /pantos/ all added back in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Gk /pantos/ all added back in ** Sept 2005</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia su jadi samua burung tukang makan bangke pung tampa bakumpul.<bt>It has become every bird (scavenger) gathering place.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ Gk = burung najis ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">@@ Gk = burung najis ; samua (Gk pantos) **fixed Sept 2005</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia su jadi samua binatang tar bae pung kandang.<bt>It has become the animal pen for all the yucky animals (no good).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ Gk = binatang najis ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">@@ Gk = binatang najis ; samua?? **fixed Sept 2005</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Rev. 14:8. TEXT: [kai phylakee pantos"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Rev. 14:8. TEXT: [kai phylakee pantos pneumatos akathartou] [kai phylakee pantos orneou akathartou] [kai phylakee pantos theeriou akathartou] kai memiseemenou: weak attestation for the whole list, strongest for "beast" alone, next for "bird", weakest for "spirit" alone. Recommended "Now inside dea ony get pilau kine wild animals, da kine dat everybody hate." But best to go along with the more popular English editions. NIV has "spirit" and "bird".<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="18:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 21:9, Yeremia 51:8, Dunya Model Baru 14:8, Yesaya 13:21, Yeremia 50:39</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="3" />Dia su rubu, tagal samua suku-bangsa di bumi,<bt>She has fallen, because all nations on earth</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">maen datang minum mabo dari dia pung anggor.<bt>habitually come drink to point of getting drunk from her wine.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia su jato, tagal samua suku di dunya,<bt>She has fallen, because all clans in the world</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">maen datang basundal deng itu kota pung orang.<bt>habitually come to be sexually immoral with that city's inhabitants. [NOTE: metonymy explicated.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** metonymy explicated"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** metonymy explicated</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Raja-raja dari samua negara dong,<bt>Kings from all countries</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">datang maen serong di situ.<bt>have come to have illicit sex there.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Orang dagang dari samua kota dong,<bt>Merchants from all the cities</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">datang bajual sampe dong su jadi kaya.<bt>come sell to the point that they become rich.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Tagal itu kota sama ke parampuan yang suka béli samua yang mewa.<bt>Because that city is like a woman who likes to buy every luxurious thing.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Tagal itu kota sama ke palacor yang suka cari samua yang ena-ena.&gt;&gt;<bt>Because that city is like a prostitute who likes to look for/find everything that is pleasing (to the senses/self).” [NOTE: “wine” in Gk here not wrath.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Wine of her adulteries -- again,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Wine of her adulteries -- again, not wrath: Rev. 14:8-10, 17:2. ek tees dynameoos: the wealth<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="18:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 23:17, Yeremia 51:7</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ais beta dengar lai satu suara laen pange dari langit bilang,<bt>Then I heard again another voice call from the sky saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Hoi! Beta pung orang dong samua!<bt>“Hoi! [+get attention] All of My people!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Lari kaluar dari sana su!<bt>Run away from there!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Kasi tenga itu kota su!<bt>Leave that city!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Jang bekin iko itu kota pung orang pung jahat,<bt>Don't follow/participate in the evil of the inhabitants of that city,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko jang kaná dong pung hukuman ju.<bt>so that [you] are not also afflicted with their punishment.</bt><note reference="18:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 48:20, Yeremia 50:8, 51:6, 45</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="5" />Tagal dong pung jahat<bt>Because their evil is</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">su talalu banya.<bt>way too much.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Deng dong pung sala<bt>And their sins</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">su balapis-lapis sampe di langit.<bt>are layered up to the sky.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Sakarang Tuhan Allah su sonde lupa lai<bt>Now God has not forgotten anymore</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dong pung jalan idop yang jahat.<bt>that way of life of theirs that is evil.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Sakarang Tuhan Allah su siap<bt>Now God is ready</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko mau hukum sang dong.<bt>to punish them.</bt><note reference="18:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 18:20-21, Yeremia 51:9</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="6" />Jadi bosong musti balas dong pung jahat,<bt>So (consequently), you-pl must reciprocate/ avenge/pay back (for) their evil,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sama ke dong su bekin jahat sang orang laen.<bt>in the same way they did evil to other people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ma bosong musti balas sang dong,<bt>But you must repay/reciprocate to them,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sampe dua kali lipat.<bt>to the point of two fold (=twice the amount).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dolu dong tipu orang,<bt>Previously they deceived people,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko minum dari dong pung cangkir mas yang ponu deng anggor sangsara.<bt>to drink from their gold cup that was full of suffering wine (=wine that brings suffering).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ma sakarang dong sandiri yang musti minum<bt>But now it is they themselves who must drink</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">itu anggor sangsara, sampe dua kali lipat.<bt>that suffering wine, until two fold.</bt><note reference="18:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 137:8, Yeremia 50:29</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="7" />Dong su bekin diri hebat.<bt>They have made themselves out to be great.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Deng su angka tinggi-tinggi dong pung diri.<bt>And have lifted high (=self-praise/glorification) themselves.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dong cuma mau idop mewa sa.<bt>They want only to live luxuriously (image associated with filthy rich who have no cares).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dong cuma suka yang ena-ena sa.<bt>They like only what is (self-) pleasing.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tagal itu, dong musti dapa susa barát.<bt>Because of that, they must get/experience heavy/severe difficulty.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Jadi dong musti idop sangsara.<bt>So (consequently), they must live in suffering/strife.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Te dolu dong omong sombong sama ke palacur bilang,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) previously they spoke arrogantly like a prostitute, saying</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;Beta ni, mama raja!<bt>‘I am the queen!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Beta sonde akan jadi janda!<bt>I am not going to be a widow!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Beta sonde akan manangis makarereu.<bt>I am not going to cry wailing/mourning.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Beta sonde akan pake pakean itam.&gt;<bt>I am not going to wear black (=mourning) clothes.’</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="8" />Dong omong bagitu sampe Tuhan Allah su mara sang dong.<bt>They spoke like that to the point that God is angry with them.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Sampe Tuhan Allah su mau hukum sang dong.<bt>To the point that God wants to punish them.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Nanti dalam satu hari sa,<bt>Later in just one day</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">dong rasa lapar mau mati,<bt>they will feel extreme hungry,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">dong manangis makarereu,<bt>they will wail in grief,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">deng dong mati mampos ju.<bt>and they will also die a cursed death.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sampe orang angka buang sang dong pi dalam api.<bt>To the point that people pick up and throw them into the fire.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sampe api bakar abis dong pung mayat.<bt>To the point that the fire completely burns up their corpses. [NOTE: picture builds with adding info. vs.8 anger - punishment - throw them in fire - burn up corpses - vs.9 city completely burned up.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Te Tuhan yang paling kuasa, yang kasi turun ini hukum.<bt>God who is the most powerful, is the one who hands down this punishment.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Deng Tuhan yang paling hebat, yang putus ini parkara.<bt>And God who is the most awesome, is the one who decided this case.</bt><note reference="18:7-8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 47:7-9</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="9" />Raja-raja yang dolu datang<bt>Kings who previously came</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">maen serong deng itu kota pung orang dong,<bt>playing off-track (sexually) with the inhabitants of that city,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng idop mewa di situ.<bt>and lived luxuriously there.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nanti dong lia asap yang nae dari itu api,<bt>Later they will see smoke that arises from that fire,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">nanti dong dapa tau itu kota su tabakar abis.<bt>later they will know that city is burned up.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ais dong manangis makarereu sang dia.<bt>Then they will cry wailing for her.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="10" />Ju dong rasa ngarí lia itu orang dong pung sangsara.<bt>And they will feel horrified seeing that suffering of those people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ma dong cuma barani badiri dari jao.<bt>But they only dare to stand far off.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng dong cuma barani lia-lia dari sana.<bt>And they can only watch from over there.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ais dong omong bilang,<bt>Then they speak saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;Aduu! Kasian Babel, é!<bt>‘Oh dear! Pity on Babel, é!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Aduu! Kasian kota hebat, ó!<bt>Oh dear! Pity that great city, ó!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te cuma dalam satu jam sa, lu su dapa hukum.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) in only just one hour, you have been punished.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te cuma sabantar sa, ma lu su ancor buang.&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) in just a short time, but you have been destroyed.’</bt><note reference="18:9-10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 26:16-17</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="11" />Dengar bagitu, orang yang dolu datang dari samua tampa ko badagang di situ,<bt>Hearing that, people who previously came from all places to trade there,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dong ju iko manangis makarereu.<bt>they also follow/participate in [the previous (collective)] crying wailing.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te sonde ada satu orang ju,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) there is not a single person</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">yang mau pi béli dong pung barang lai.<bt>who wants to buy their merchandise anymore.</bt><note reference="18:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 27:31, 36</note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="12" />Sonde ada yang mau pi béli<bt>There is no one who wants to go buy</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">dong pung hiasan dari mas, perak,<bt>their jewelry from gold, silver,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">batu mangkilat, ko, mutiara lai.<bt>jewels, or pearl anymore.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sonde ada yang mau pi béli<bt>There is no one who wants to go buy</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">dong pung kaen lenan, kaen sutra,<bt>their linen cloth, silk cloth,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko, kaen alus yang laen dong yang warna mera, ko, ungu.<bt>or, other refined/expensive cloths that are red or purple.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sonde ada yang mau pi béli<bt>There is no one who wants to go buy</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">dong pung barang dari kayu wangi, gading ba'ukir,<bt>their things from fragrant wood, carved elephant tusk,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko, kayu ba'ukir yang laen dong.<bt>or, other carved woods.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sonde ada yang mau pi béli<bt>There is no one who wants to go buy</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">dong pung barang dari tambaga, bési, ko, batu marmar.<bt>their things from copper/bronze, iron or marble stone.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="13" />Sonde ada yang mau pi béli<bt>There is no one who wants to go buy</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">dong pung kayu manis, ko, kuli manis macam-macam.<bt>their cinnamon, or, all sorts of spices.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ spices ??"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">@@ spices ??</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sonde ada yang mau pi béli<bt>There is no one who wants to buy</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">dong pung dara kayu wangi, ko, minya wangi macam-macam.<bt>their aromatic resin, or, different kinds of perfume/oil.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sonde ada yang mau pi béli<bt>There is no one who wants to go buy</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">dong pung aer anggor, minya saitun,<bt>their grape wine, olive oil,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">tapúng tarigu, ko, padi-gandum.<bt>wheat flour, or, wheat padi.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sonde ada yang mau pi béli<bt>There is no one who wants to go buy</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">dong pung sapi, domba, ko, kuda.<bt>their cows, sheep, or, horses.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sonde ada yang mau pi béli<bt>There is no one who wants to go buy</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">dong pung kareta,<bt>their carts/carriages/chariots, [EXEG: most English versions and AGNT say “chariot” here, but LN says a different Gk word means chariot. They say the Gk word here is “a four-wheeled carriage or wagon used for travel or the transportation of loads”; BADG say “carriage” and do not give “chariot” as a gloss. Here it is used in a list of goods bought and sold by merchants. Safer just to say /kareta/ than either /kareta barang/ or /kareta paráng/.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko, dong pung budak dong.<bt>or, their slaves. [EXEG: Mounce considers “the bodies and souls of men” to be a Hebrew biased idiom meaning “slave trafficking”. Additional support and discussion in TH.]</bt><note reference="18:12-13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 27:12, 13, 22</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="14" />Nanti itu orang dagang dong rasa manyasal bilang,<bt>Later those merchants will feel regret saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;Aduu, Babel, é!<bt>‘Oh dear, Babel, é!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Aduu, kota hebat, ó!<bt>Oh dear, great city, ó!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Lu pung barang mewa yang lu pung orang dong paling suka tu,<bt>Those luxury goods of yours which your people/inhabitants like so much,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">su sonde ada lai.<bt>are gone.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Samua-samua su ilang, sampe dong su miskin malarat,<bt>Everything has disappeared, to the point that they are desolately poor</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">sampe raroso.&gt;<bt>to the point that [you] drag on the ground.’</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="15" />Dolu itu orang dagang dong jadi kaya tagal itu kota yang sama ke palacor.<bt>Previously those merchants became rich because of that city that is like a prostitute.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ma sakarang dong su manyasal tar abis-abis.<bt>But now they are endlessly regretful.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Dong jadi taku mau mati,<bt>They have become very afraid,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">lia itu kota pung orang pung sangsara.<bt>seeing that suffering of the people of that city.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dong jadi talalu ngarí,<bt>They have become very horrified,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">lia dong pung hukuman.<bt>seeing that punishment of theirs.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ma dong cuma barani lia dari jao.<bt>But they only dare to look from afar.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dong cuma barani badiri dari sana.<bt>They only can bear to watch from over there.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="16" />Ais dong omong bilang,<bt>Then they spoke saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;Aduu! Kasian Babel, é!<bt>‘Oh dear! Pity Babel, é!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Aduu! Kasian kota hebat, ó!<bt>Oh dear! Pity the great city, ó!</bt><note reference="18:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 27:31, 36</note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dolu lu pung orang pake pakean alus yang warna mera, ko ungu,<bt>Previously your people wore fine clothes that was red, or purple,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">dari kaen yang paling mahal.<bt>from cloth that was extremely expensive.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dolu lu pung orang barias deng mas, mutiara,<bt>Previously your people decorated themselves with gold, pearls,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">deng batu mangkilat yang paling mahal.<bt>and precious/flashy stones that were extremely expensive.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="17" />Ma dalam satu jam sa,<bt>But in just one hour,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">lu pung barang-barang dong su sonde ada lai.<bt>your things are all gone.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Cuma sabantar sa,<bt>In just a short time,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">lu pung kaya dong su ilang abis!&gt;<bt>your riches have disappeared!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dolu ju ada kapten-kapten kapal deng ana bua kapal dong<bt>Previously there were also ships captains and ship crews</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">balayar pi-datang dari itu kota.<bt>sailing to and from that city.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ilang abis samua! ilang abis samua!"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">ilang abis samua! ilang abis samua!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ma sakarang dong cuma barani balabu dari jao sa.<bt>But now they only dare be at anchor from afar.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng sakarang dong cuma barani lia-lia dari sana sa.<bt>And now they only dare watch from over there.</bt><note reference="18:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 23:14, Yeskial 27:26-30</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="18" />Dong manonton asap yang kaluar dari api.<bt>They watch the smoke that come out of that fire.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ais dong dapa tau bilang, dia su tabakar abis.<bt>Then they know that she is burnt up.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ju dong manyasal bilang,<bt>Then they express regret saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;Aduu kasian! Sonde akan ada kota laen<bt>‘How pitiful! There will not be another city</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">yang sama hebat ke Babel lai.<bt>that is as great as Babel again.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Aduu kasian! Sonde akan ada kota laen,<bt>How pitiful! There will not be another city</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">yang sama bagus deng dia lai.&gt;<bt>that is as fine as her again.’</bt><note reference="18:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 27:32</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="19" />Dong ra'u abu ko taro di dong pung kapala,<bt>They scoop up ashes to put on their heads,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal dong pung hati susa.<bt>because their livers are in distress (=grief).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dong manangis makarereu,<bt>They cry wailing,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">tagal dong pung hati ancor.<bt>because their livers are crushed (=broken hearted).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ais dong omong bilang,<bt>Then they speak saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;Aduu! Kasian Babel, é!<bt>‘Oh dear! Pity Babel, é!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Aduu! Kasian kota hebat, ó!<bt>Oh dear! Pity the great city, ó!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Botong su balayar pi-datang bawa barang kasi sang lu,<bt>We-exc have sailed to and fro bringing goods to you,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">sampe botong ju iko jadi kaya.<bt>until we also have become rich.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Botong su pikol bawa lu pung muatan,<bt>We have carried your cargo,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">sampe botong ju iko idop mewa.<bt>until we also have lived luxuriously.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ma cuma dalam satu jam sa,<bt>But in only just one hour,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">samua tu, su ilang buang.<bt>all of that, has disappeared.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Cuma sabantar sa,<bt>In only just a short time,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">samua tu, su ancor abis.&gt;<bt>all of that, has been destroyed.’</bt><note reference="18:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 27:30-34</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ais, itu suara omong tamba bilang,<bt>Then, that voice added saying, [DISCOURSE: quote margin because of major shift in addressee.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;We, bosong yang idop di sorga!<bt>‘We, [+get attention] all of you who live in heaven!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">bosong pung hati su sonde parlú manoso lai.<bt>Your livers do not need to be stung (=disappointed) anymore.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">We, Tuhan pung orang!<bt>We, [+get attention] the Lord's people!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bosong pung hati su sonde parlú rasa susa lai.<bt>Your livers do not need to feel distress anymore.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">We, Tuhan pung utusan dong!<bt>We, [+get attention] the Lord's commissioned ones (*apostles)!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Biar ko bosong pung hati babunga.<bt>Let your livers flower (=be joyful).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">We, Tuhan pung jubir dong!<bt>We, [+get attention] the Lord's spokespersons (*prophets)!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Biar ko bosong pung hati sanáng.<bt>Let your livers be happy.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dolu Babel bekin susa sang bosong.<bt>Previously Babel caused you trouble.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dolu itu kota siksa sang bosong.<bt>Previously that city tortured you.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ma sakarang Tuhan su balas bosong pung sangsara.<bt>But now God has reciprocated/revenged you suffering.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te sakarang Dia su balas itu kota pung jahat.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) now He has reciprocated/revenged that city's evil.’”</bt><note reference="18:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 32:43, Yeremia 51:48</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ais itu, beta dapa lia satu ana bua dari sorga yang kuat batúl. Dia datang angka ame satu batu, bésar sama ke orang. Ais dia lempar kasi maso itu batu pi dalam laut. Dia ju kasi tau bilang,<bt>After that, I saw an angel who was very strong. He came and picked up a stone as big as a person. Then he threw that stone into the sea. He then told saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Nanti dong kasi ancor buang Babel bagitu ju.<bt>“Later they will completely destroy Babel like that.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Nanti dong kasi ilang buang itu kota hebat bagitu ju.<bt>Later they will make that Great City completely disappear just like that.</bt><note reference="18:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeremia 51:63-64, Yeskial 26:21</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="22" />Su sonde ada orang lai,<bt>There is no longer anyone</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">yang maen musik di itu kota.<bt>who plays music in that city.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Su sonde ada orang,<bt>There is no longer anyone</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">yang dapa dengar sasando, gitar, suling,<bt>who hears the sound of sasando, guitar, flutes,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">deng tarompet pung bunyi di itu kota lai.<bt>and trumpets in that city anymore.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Su sonde ada tukang,<bt>There is no longer a/any craftsman,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">yang karjá di dong pung bidang lai.<bt>who works in their trade/field of expertise anymore. [NOTE: TB is way off here, talking about performers in the fine arts. CEV is misleading talking about “setting up shop”, but meaning “workshop” rather than “store” as some of us misread it for earlier versions.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="yang buka toko di itu kota"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">yang buka toko di itu kota lai.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Su sonde ada orang,<bt>There is no longer anyone</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">yang mol padi di itu kota lai.<bt>who mills padi in that city anymore.</bt><note reference="18:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 26:13, Yesaya 24:8</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="23" />Su sonde ada orang,<bt>There is no longer anyone</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">yang bakar lampu di itu kota lai.<bt>who burns lamps in that city anymore.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Su sonde ada orang,<bt>There is no longer anyone</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">yang bekin pesta kawin di situ lai.<bt>who makes wedding feasts there anymore.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dolu itu kota pung tukang jual-beli barang dong,<bt>Previously that city's buyers of merchandise</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">su jadi talalu kaya.<bt>had become excessively rich.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dolu Babel pung orang dagang dong,<bt>Previously Babel's merchants</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">su idop talalu mewa.<bt>had lived in excessive luxury.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ma dong pake ilmu galáp,<bt>But they used black magic</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko tipu orang di bumi.<bt>to deceive people on earth.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dong pake ilmu sihir,<bt>They used sorcery</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko putar-balek manusia di dunya.<bt>to con humans in the world.</bt><note reference="18:22-23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeremia 7:34, 25:10</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="24" />Babel su dapa hukum barát ni,<bt>Babel has received this heavy/severe punishment,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal dia maen bunu bekin mati Tuhan pung jubir dong.<bt>because she habitually murdered God's spokesperson</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Itu kota hebat su ancor,<bt>That great city is destroyed,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal dia maen siksa mati Tuhan pung orang dong.<bt>because she habitually tortured the Lord's people to death.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ada ju Tuhan pung orang yang kaná bunu di tampa-tampa laen dong.<bt>There are also the Lord's people who were murdered in other places.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ma Babel yang musti pikol itu sala samua.<bt>But it is Babel who must carry all those wrongs.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Itu kota hebat yang musti pikol tanggong-jawab.&gt;&gt;<bt>It is that great city who must bear the responsibility.”</bt><note reference="18:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeremia 51:49</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Koor bésar manyanyi di sorga<bt>Big Choir in heaven</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="19" />
      <v n="1" />Itu ana bua omong abis bagitu, ju beta dengar ada suara bésar tingka ke ada koor bésar manyanyi di sorga. Dong manyanyi bilang,<bt>That angel finished speaking like that, then I heard a big noise like there was a big choir singing in heaven. They sang saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Haleluya! Haleluya!<bt>“Haleluya! Haleluya!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Kotong angka puji sang kotong pung Allah,<bt>We-inc praise our God,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">tagal Dia yang paling hebat.<bt>because He is the most great/amazing. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Haleluya! Haleluya!<bt>Haleluya! Haleluya!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Kotong angka puji sang kotong pung Allah,<bt>We praise our God,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">tagal Dia yang paling kuasa.<bt>because He is the most powerful/greatest authority.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan yang kasi salamat sang kotong,<bt>God is the one who has saved us</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dari kotong pung sala-sala dong.<bt>from our sins.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan yang bekin beres kotong<bt>The Lord is the one who straighten out things for us</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dari kotong pung idop babengko.<bt>that results from our twisted lives.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="2" />Kotong puji sang Tuhan Allah,<bt>We praise God</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal Dia yang putus parkara deng batúl.<bt>because He is the one who decides cases truly/correctly/fairly/rightly.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Kotong puji sang Tuhan Allah,<bt>We praise God</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal Dia yang kasi jato hukuman yang adil.<bt>because He is the one who hands down fair/just punishment.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan su kasi jato hukuman sang itu parampuan nakal,<bt>The Lord has handed down punishment to that aforementioned prostitute woman,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal dia maen buju orang-orang di dunya,<bt>because she habitually enticed people in the world,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko iko maen serong sama-sama deng dia,<bt>to go along with/participate in playing off-track (sexually) with her,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">deng iko-iko dia pung jahat.<bt>and follow her evil.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan su balas itu parampuan jahat,<bt>The Lord has repaid/reciprocated that aforementioned evil woman,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal dia maen bunu bekin mati<bt>because she habitually murdered</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Tuhan pung orang suru-suru dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>the Lord's servants.”</bt><note reference="19:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 32:43, 2 Raja-raja dong 9:7</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ais itu, dong manyanyi lagu laen lai di sorga bilang,<bt>After that, they sang yet another song in heaven saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Haleluya! Puji-puji sang Tuhan!<bt>“Haleluya! Praise the Lord!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Haleluya! Angka tinggi-tinggi Dia pung nama!<bt>Haleluya! Lift His name up high!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tagal asap dari api yang bakar itu parampuan pung mayat tu,<bt>Because smoke from the fire which burns that aforementioned woman's corpse,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">nae tarús sonde tau barenti-barenti.<bt>arises continually without ever stopping.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Deng asap dari api yang bakar itu kota hebat tu,<bt>And smoke from the fire which burns that aforementioned great city,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nae tarús sonde tau abis-abis.&gt;&gt;<bt>arises continually without ever ending.”</bt><note reference="19:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 34:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ais ju itu 24 katua deng itu 4 binatang luar biasa tu, jato tikam lutut ko sémba mangada pi Tuhan Allah pung korsi parenta. Dong kasi hormat sang Dia bilang,<bt>After that, those 24 elders and those aforementioned four extra-ordinary animals, fell kneeling to worship facing God's ruling chair. They gave honour to Him saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Batúl! Mari ko kotong puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah!<bt>“True! Let's praise the Lord God!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Haleluya! Mari ko kotong angka tinggi-tinggi Dia pung nama!&gt;&gt;<bt>Haleluya! Let's lift his name up high!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Domba Ana pung pesta kawin<bt>The Sheep Offspring's wedding feast</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ais beta dengar satu suara lai datang dari itu korsi parenta bilang,<bt>Then I heard another voice come from that ruling chair saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;We, Tuhan Allah pung orang suru-suru dong!<bt>“We, [+get attention] God's servants!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">We, Tuhan Allah pung ana-ana dong!<bt>We, [+get attention] God's children!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Mari ko kotong angka tinggi-tinggi Tuhan Allah pung nama.<bt>Let us-inc lift God's name up high.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Mari samua kici-bésar puji sang Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>Let us all small-big praise the Lord.”</bt><note reference="19:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 115:13</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ais beta dengar tingka ke ada banya orang yang ba'omong. Dong pung suara babunyi bésar sama ke aer tarjún, deng karás sama ke guntur basambung. Dong omong bilang,<bt>Then I heard as if there were many people speaking to each other. That voice of theirs, sounded big like a waterfall, and loud like rumbling thunder. They spoke saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Haleluya! Botong puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>“Haleluya! We praise God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Haleluya! Botong angka tinggi-tinggi Dia pung nama.<bt>Haleluya! We lift His name up high.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tagal Dia yang paling kuasa.<bt>Because He is the one who has the most authority/power.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng Dia yang parenta samua.<bt>And He is the one who rules everything.</bt><note reference="19:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 1:24, Lagu Puji dong 93:1, 97:1, 99:1</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="7" />Sakarang, kotong pung hati su sanáng.<bt>Now our livers are happy.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sakarang, kotong pung hati su babunga.<bt>Now are livers are flowering (=joyful).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Kotong puji-puji sang Dia,<bt>We (inc) praise Him, [EXEG: Gk: give him the glory]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal Domba Ana pung hari kawin su sampe.<bt>because the Sheep Offspring's wedding day has arrived.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Kotong angka tinggi-tinggi Dia pung nama,<bt>We lift His name up high,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal Domba Ana pung baroit su siap.<bt>because the Sheep Offspring's bride is ready.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="8" />Tuhan Allah su kasi dia pakean baroit dari kaen alus.<bt>God has given bride clothes made from fine cloth.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tuhan Allah su kasi dia pakean yang puti mangkilat.&gt;&gt;<bt>God has given clothes that are shiny white.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">(Itu pakean puti mangkilat tu, andia Tuhan Allah pung orang dong pung karjá yang bae dong.)<bt>(Those aforemention shiny white clothes, are God's people's good deeds.) [NOTE: modelled on NLT for explanatory background info.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ju itu ana bua dari sorga kasi tau sang beta bilang, &lt;&lt;Yohanis! Lu musti tulis bagini:<bt>Then that angel told me saying, “Yohanis! You must write like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Samua orang yang dapa undang datang di Domba Ana pung pesta kawin tu, nanti dong ontong batúl!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>&lt;All people who receive an invitation to come to that Sheep Offspring wedding feast, later they will be truly fortunate!”&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: this is the same Gk word /makarizw/ “how fortunate are...” that is used in the beatitudes in Mat. 5 and Luke 6. See C. Grimes Word Study. A feeling of “happiness” is only secondarily part of the meaning (result) of the Gk word.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais, itu ana bua sambung dia pung omong lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata ni, memang batúl!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then that angel continued his speaking again saying, “This Words of God, are indeed true!”</bt><note reference="19:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 22:2-3</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ju beta jato tikam lutut ko mau sémba sang itu ana bua. Ma dia togor sang beta bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu jang sémba sang beta bagitu! Te beta ju Tuhan pung orang suru-suru sama ke lu, deng lu pung sodara dong yang kasi tau orang so'al Yesus. Jubir yang kasi tau Tuhan Allah pung pasán dong, samua ju kasi tunju sang Yesus ko biar orang sémba sang Dia. Te itu Tuhan pung Roh pung mau bagitu. Jadi jang sémba sang beta, ma sémba sang Tuhan Allah sa!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then I fell kneeling in order to worship that angel. But he scolded me saying, “You don't worship me like that! Cuz (elaboration) I am also God's servant like you, and your siblings who tell people about Yesus. Spokespeople (*prophets) who tell/told God's message/s, all point to Yesus so that people will worship Him. Cuz (elaboration) that is the desire of God's Spirit. So (consequently), don't worship me, but worship only God!” [EXEG: Gk “having/holding the testimony of Jesus ... For the testimony of Jesus is the spirit of prophecy”; For last part, see discussion in Mounce and TH. We explicate follow lead of NLT and discusssion in TH to make sense in context. Interestingly CEV takes a direction that TH says “does not seem likely”--both UBS sources. Revision initiated by consultant.] [EXEG: recurring phrase in Rev. “the testimony of Jesus”. 1:2; 1:9; 12:11; 12:17; 19:10; 20:4. Much discussion (and disagreement) in the commentaries.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) revised, note added; testimony"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** (2009) revised, note added; testimony of Jesus (x2), spirit of prophecy</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te beta ju Tuhan pung orang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Te beta ju Tuhan pung orang suru-suru sama ke lu, deng lu pung sodara dong yang kasi tau orang so'al Yesus. Te Yesus pung ajaran tu, sama deng itu ajaran yang dolu Tuhan Allah su kasi sang Dia pung jubir dong. Jadi, jang sémba sang beta, ma sémba sang Tuhan Allah sa!&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus datang di atas kuda puti<bt>The Lord Yesus comes on top a white horse</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ais beta angka muka, ju beta dapa lia sorga tabuka. Takuju, beta lia ada satu kuda puti kaluar datang. Orang yang dudu di itu kuda tu, ada pung nama, &lt;&lt;Orang yang Pegang Janji&gt;&gt; deng &lt;&lt;Orang yang Batúl&gt;&gt;. Waktu Dia putus parkara, Dia putus deng batúl. Kalo Dia pi paráng, Dia pi deng hati lurus.<bt>Then I lifted my face, and saw heaven open. Suddenly, I saw there was a white horse coming forth/out. The person who sat on that horse, his name was, “Person who Keeps Promises” and “Person who is True/Correct/Right”. When He decided/judged cases, He judged correctly. If He went to war, He went with a straight liver (=with righteous intentions). [EXEG: Although NLT has “a white horse standing there”, there is nothing in the Gk to push “standing”. Rather vs. 14 has armies following him, so a dynamic picture of action here is a better fit.] [NOTE to daughter translations: check if /sorga tabuka/ works, or if it needs to be /sorga pung pintu tabuka/, or /langit/.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="War: Rev. 2:16."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">War: Rev. 2:16.</Message></Annotation><note reference="19:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 1:1, Lagu Puji dong 96:13, Yesaya 11:4</note><v n="12" />Dia pung mata manyala sama ke api. Dia ada pake banya topi raja di atas Dia pung kapala. Dia pung nama ada tatulis di Dia pung badan, ma cuma Dia sandiri sa yang tau itu nama pung arti.<bt>His eyes blazed like fire. He was wearing many king hats on top of His head. His name was written on His body, but it was only just He himself who knew the meaning of that name. [EXEG: NLT, CEV]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Eyes like flame of fire: Rev."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Eyes like flame of fire: Rev. 1:14, 2:18. Crowns: Rev. 12:3, 13:1.<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>No one knows but himself: Rev. 2:17.</Message></Annotation><note reference="19:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 10:6</note><v n="13" />Dia pung pakean, su tacalóp dalam dara. Orang subu sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata&gt;&gt;.<bt>His clothes, had been dipped in blood. People mention/label him saying, “God's Words”.</bt><v n="14" />Beta ju dapa lia tantara-tantara dari sorga dong ada nae kuda puti ko iko sang Dia. Dong samua pake pakean alus yang puti barisi ju.<bt>I also saw soldiers from heaven were riding white horses to follow Him. They all also wore fine clothes that was pure/clean white.</bt><v n="15" />Ada satu kalewang tajam yang kaluar dari Dia pung mulu. Dia pake itu kalewang, ko pi baparáng lawan samua suku-bangsa di bumi. Ais Dia kasi kala sang dong. Ju Dia jadi dong pung Raja. Dia parenta sang dong deng tangan bési, sampe dong ju dapa rasa Tuhan yang paling kuasa pung mara. Itu sama ke orang inja-inja bekin ancor anggor pung bua ko parés kasi kaluar dia pung aer.<bt>There was a sharp fighting sword that came out of His mouth. He used that sword there, to go war against all the nations on earth. Then He defeated them. And He became their King. He ruled them with an iron hand, until they also felt the anger of God who is most mighty. That was the same as people stepping all over destroying grape fruits, to express make their juice come out.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Rule with a rod of iron:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Rule with a rod of iron: Rev. 2:27, 12:5.</Message></Annotation><note reference="19:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 2:9, Yesaya 63:3, Yoel 3:13, Dunya Model Baru 14:20</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Di itu Orang pung pakean, deng di Dia pung paha, ada tatulis bagini:<bt>On that Person's clothing, and on His thigh there was written like this: [EXEG: Gk in two places with /epi xx kai epi yy/; CEV wrong.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Gk in two places with /epi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Gk in two places with /epi xx kai epi yy/; CEV wrong; **fixed Sept 2005</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Raja di atas samua raja.<bt>King above all kings.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bos di atas samua bos.<bt>Bos above all bosses.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi kala binatang buas deng dia pung tantara dong [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus defeats the ferocious animal and his armies/soldiers [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ais itu, beta dapa lia satu ana bua dari sorga badiri di atas matahari. Ju dia eki kasi samua burung makan bangke yang ada tarbáng tinggi-tinggi di langit bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari ko bosong samua bakumpul di sini su, ko iko makan Tuhan Allah pung pesta bésar!<bt>After that, I saw an angel standing on the sun. Then he yelled out to all the corpse-eating birds who were flying high in the sky saying, “Come for you all to gather here, so that you can eat at God's big feast! [EXEG: corpse-eating birds from context (vs.17) + NLT; cf vs.18,21.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***birds &gt; corpse-eating birds from context"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">***birds &gt; corpse-eating birds from context (vs.17) + NLT; check vs.21</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Bosong bole makan samua orang mati dong pung daging: andia raja-raja, panglima-panglima, deng tantara dong. Bosong bole makan kuda-kuda deng tantara yang dudu di atas itu kuda dong pung daging. Bosong bole makan budak ko orang bebas ko, orang kici ko orang bésar dong pung daging. Pokonya, bosong bole makan samua pung daging.&gt;&gt;<bt>You may eat all the dead people's meat: they are kings, army commanders, and soldiers. You may eat the meat of horses and the soldiers which sit on top of them. You may eat the meat of slaves or free people, small [ranking] people or big [ranking] people. The important thing is, you may the meat of all those.”</bt><note reference="19:17-18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 39:17-20</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ais itu, beta dapa lia itu binatang buas yang dolu kaluar dari laut. Dia pi basakongkol deng samua raja di bumi, deng dong pung tantara dong. Ais dong pi baparáng lawan itu Orang yang ada dudu di atas itu kuda puti, sama-sama deng Dia pung tantara dari sorga dong.<bt>After that, I saw that aforementioned ferocious animal who previously came out of the sea. He went to plot/plan with all the kings on earth, and with their soldiers. Then they went to war against that Person who was sitting on top of that aforementioned white horse, together with His army/soldiers from heaven. [NOTE to daughter translations: CHECK if for discourse reasons you need to say “gathered together and then went to war”.]</bt><v n="20" />Ma itu Orang yang dudu di atas itu kuda puti tu, tangkap ame itu binatang buas deng dia pung jubir tukang putar-balek. Itu jubir tu, andia yang dolu bekin tanda heran macam-macam ko putar-balek orang yang su tarima itu binatang buas pung cap deng yang su songgo dia pung patong. Ma sakarang, itu Orang yang dudu di atas itu kuda puti tu, pi lempar buang itu binatang buas deng dia pung jubir pi dalam laut api balerang yang manyala sonde pake barenti.<bt>But that Person who sat on that aforementioned white horse, captured that ferocious animal with his deceptive spokesperson. That aforementioned spokesperson, was who previous did all sorts of miracles to trick people who accepted that wild animal's stamp and who worshipped his statue. But now, that Person who is sitting on top of that aforementioned white horse, went to throw away that ferocious animal and his aforementioned deceptive spokesperson into the sulfur sea of fire that burns without ever stopping.</bt><note reference="19:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 13:1-18</note><v n="21" />Ais, itu Orang yang dudu di atas itu kuda, pi bunu bekin mati itu tantara yang laen dong, pake Dia pung kalewang yang kaluar dari Dia pung mulu. Ais itu ju, burung makan bangke dong datang makan abis itu mayat dong samua.<bt>Then that Person who sits on top of that aforementioned horse, went to kill those other soldiers, using His fighting sword that came out of His mouth. After that, then the vulture birds came and ate up all those corpses.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong ika ular naga deng rante sampe saribu taon<bt>They tie up the dragon snake with a chain for a thousand years</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="20" />
      <v n="1" />Ais ju beta dapa lia satu ana bua dari sorga turun datang dari langit. Dia ada pegang satu rante bésar, deng ada pegang konci lobang sangsara yang sonde ada pung dasar.<bt>After that I saw an angel come down from the sky. He was holding a big chain, and the key to the suffering hole which does not have a foundation.</bt><v n="2" />Ais dia pi tangkap itu ular naga, andia, setan dong pung bos, yang dong subu bilang, &lt;&lt;Iblis&gt;&gt;. Dia yang su tipu manusia dari dolu-dolu. Ju itu ana bua ika itu ular naga deng rante, ko mau tahan sang dia pi dalam itu lobang sampe saribu taon.<bt>The he went and captured that dragon snake, who is, the evil spirit's boss that they refer to as “The Devil”. He is the one who tricked people from long ago. Then that angel tied that dragon snake up with that chain, to detain him a thousand years in that hole.</bt><note reference="20:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 3:1</note><v n="3" />Tarús itu ana bua tola buang itu ular naga pi dalam itu lobang sangsara. Ais dia segel mati itu lobang pung pintu, ko biar tahan itu ular di situ, sampe abis saribu taon. Deng bagitu, itu ular su sonde bisa putar-balek suku-bangsa di bumi salama saribu taon. Ais itu, baru kasi lapás sang dia, ma cuma sabantar sa.<bt>Next that angel threw that dragon snake away into that aforementioned suffering hole. Afterwards he sealed tight that hole's door, in order to detain that snake there, for a thousand years. In that way, that snake could not deceive the nations on earth for a thousand years. After that, then they freed him, but only briefly.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Tarús beta lia ada korsi parenta pung banya lai, deng ada orang-orang yang dudu di atas. Tuhan Allah su angka sang dong ko putus parkara. Dong tu, orang yang dolu pi kasi tau orang so'al Yesus pung Kabar Bae, deng Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata, sampe orang bunu bekin mati sang dong. Dong tu, yang sonde songgo itu binatang buas deng dia pung patong. Dong ju yang sonde mau tarima itu binatang pung cap di testa ko, di tangan. Dong kaná bunu, ma Tuhan Allah su kasi idop kambali sang dong, ko biar dong pegang parenta sama-sama deng Kristus sampe saribu taon.<bt>Next I saw there were many ruling chairs, and there were people who sat on top of them. God had elevated/appointed them up to decide disputes/litigations/cases. They were the people who previously had gone to tell people about Yesus' Good News, and God's Words, until people murdered them. They were the ones who didn't worship that ferocious animal and his statue. They were the ones who didn't accept that animal's stamp on their forehead or arm/hand. They were murdered, but God had make them live again, so that they could rule together with Kristus for a thousand years. [EXEG: “the testimony of Jesus” again. NLT, CEV, Mounce.] [EXEG: recurring phrase in Rev. “the testimony of Jesus”. 1:2; 1:9; 12:11; 12:17; 19:10; 20:4. Much discussion (and disagreement) in the commentaries.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><note reference="20:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 7:9, 22</note><v n="5-6" />Deng bagitu dong su jadi orang partama yang Tuhan Allah kasi idop kambali dari mati. Jadi dong ni, ontong batúl, te dong su jadi Tuhan pung orang. Dong sonde kaná buang di itu tampa sangsara, ko sonde rasa mati yang kadua. Te dong yang jadi sama ke kapala agama yang layani sang Tuhan Allah deng Kristus. Deng dong ju iko pegang parenta sama-sama deng Kristus sampe saribu taon.<bt>In that way they had become the first people whom God caused to live again from death. So (consequently) they are the ones who are truly fortunate, cuz (elaboration) they are God2's people. They will not be cast out/evicted to that suffering place, to/or will not experience a second death. Cuz (elaboration) they have become like *priests who serve God and Kristus. And they are who will also rule together with Kristus for a thousand years.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma orang mati yang laen dong, musti tunggu sampe saribu taon, baru Tuhan Allah kasi idop kambali sang dong.<bt>But the other dead people, must wait for a thousand years, until God causes them to live again.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong buang setan dong pung bos pi dalam laut api<bt>They throw the evil spirit's boss in to the sea of fire</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Waktu itu saribu taon su abis, nanti Tuhan suru kasi lapás itu ular naga dari itu lobang sangsara.<bt>When those one thousand years are over, later God will tell them to free that dragon snake from that suffering hole. [EXEG: Gk: Satan, but here use dragon for higher level referent tracking of what has been detained in the pit. So ‘Satan’ KT moved to title.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Satanaas: da Devil"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Satanaas: da Devil</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Ais dia pi putar-balek suku-bangsa yang dong subu bilang, Gog deng Magog, yang datang dari mana-mana di dunya. Nanti dia kumpul dong pung orang ko pi baparáng. Dong pung banya, sama ke biji pasir di pante.<bt>The he will go deceive nations whom they call saying Gog and Magog from all over the world. Later he will gather their people to go to war. Their number is like sand grains on the edge of the sea.</bt><note reference="20:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 7:2, 38:2, 9, 15</note><v n="9" />Ais itu, tantara Gog deng Magog babaris ko maju sampe jao-jao di bumi pung huk-huk sana. Ais dong kapúng kuliling Tuhan pung kota yang Dia sayang, deng Dia pung orang dong. Ma Tuhan kasi turun api dari langit ko bakar bekin abis itu tantara dong samua.<bt>Then those Gog and Magog soldiers will line up in formation and march forward until way at the corners of the earth over there. Then they will surround (military term) God's city and His people whom He loves. But God will send fire from the sky to burn up all those soldiers. [EXEG: in Gk ‘beloved’ modifies city (and probably saints).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kapúng = surround (military)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">kapúng = surround (military)</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Ais Tuhan pung orang dong tangkap ame setan dong pung bos yang su tipu banya orang tu, andia Iblis. Ju dong lempar buang sang dia pi dalam itu laut api balerang yang manyala sonde pake barenti. Nanti dia takurung di sana sama-sama deng itu binatang buas deng dia pung jubir tukang putar-balek. Di situ, dong dapa siksa deng sangsara tarús siang-malam, sampe salamanya.<bt>Then the Lord's people captured the bos of the evil spirits who had tricked those many people, that is Iblis. Then they threw him into the sulfur fire sea which burns without ever stopping. Later he would be caged/shut up there together with ferocious animal and his aforemention deceptive spokesperson. There, they will tortured and suffer continually night and day, for ever. [EXEG: note this is the devil here, not the dragon.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** clarify referent 2007"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** clarify referent 2007</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Allah putus samua orang pung parkara<bt>God decides/judges all people's cases</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ais itu ju, beta dapa lia ada satu korsi parenta puti bésar. Deng Tuhan Allah ada dudu di atas itu korsi parenta. Takuju ju, bumi deng langit lari fuik, sampe dong ilang buang deng sonde dapa lia sang dong lai, te dong sonde tahan badeka deng Tuhan pung kuasa deng Dia pung hebat.<bt>After that, then I saw there was a big white ruling chair. And God was sitting on that ruling chair. Unexpectedly, the earth and the sky got up and ran away, until they disappeared completely and they could not be seen anymore, because they could not endure God's power/authority and amazingness (*glory). [EXEG: “flee from His presence” was undertranslated in OV. Fixed 2019, based on Dela 2005, MC.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** last sentence deleted from earlier"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** last sentence deleted from earlier versions, Sept 2005</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ais beta dapa lia orang yang su mati dong. Dong samua kici-bésar ada badiri mangada pi itu korsi parenta. Ju ana bua dari sorga dong datang buka buku-buku yang ada tulis manusia pung bekin-bekin samua. Ais dong buka lai satu tulisan laen, andia tulisan yang ada tulis nama-nama dari orang yang nanti idop deng Tuhan Allah sampe salamanya. Ju Dia putus itu orang mati dong pung parkara, iko apa yang dong satu-satu su bekin sama ke yang ada tatulis di dalam itu tulisan dong.<bt>Then I saw the people who had died. They all small-big [rank] were standing facing that ruling chair. And angels came opening writings which had written all the deeds of humans. Then they opened again another writing, which was the writing which had written the names of the people who later would live with God forever. And He decided/judged those dead people's cases, according to what each one of them had done just like what was written in those writings.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** added paragraph"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">*** added paragraph</Message></Annotation><note reference="20:11-12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 7:9-10</note><v n="13" />Ais samua orang mati datang ko badiri mangada pi itu korsi parenta. Dong tu, samua orang yang parná mati, biar di darat, ko, di laut. Ais Tuhan Allah putus dong pung parkara satu-satu, iko dong pung bekin-bekin.<bt>Then all the dead people came out to come stand in front of that ruling chair. They were all the people who had died, whether on land or the sea. Then God judged each one of their cases, according to their deeds.</bt><v n="14" />Ais itu ju, Tuhan Allah lempar buang Mati pi dalam itu laut api yang manyala sonde pake barenti tu. Dia ju lempar buang Tampa Orang Mati, pi dalam itu laut api. Te itu laut api tu, andia tampa mati yang kadua.<bt>After that then God threw Death into that sea of fire that burns without stopping. He also threw out the Place of the Dead People into that sea of fire. Cuz (elaboration) that aforementioned sea of fire, it is the place of second death.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@Tampa Orang Mati Dong pung Jiwa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">@@Tampa Orang Mati Dong pung Jiwa doesn't make any sense grammatically; Gk /hades/ KT checked extensively is "tampa orang mati" **fixed Sept 2005</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ho thanatos kai ho haaidees: switch"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">ho thanatos kai ho haaidees: switch to keep the sentences manageable.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Orang yang dong pung nama sonde tatulis di dalam itu tulisan, ju kaná buang pi dalam itu laut api. Te itu tulisan tu, andia daftar orang yang idop tarús-tarús deng Tuhan Allah.<bt>People whose names were not written in that writing also were thrown into that aforementioned sea of fire. Cuz (elaboration) that aforementioned writing, it is the list of people who will live continually with God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yohanis dapa lia langit deng bumi model baru<bt>Yohanis gets to see the new style sky and earth</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="21" />
      <v n="1" />Ais beta lia langit model baru deng bumi model baru, te langit yang lama deng bumi yang lama su ilang buang. Laut ju su sonde ada lai.<bt>Then I saw a new style sky and a new style earth, cuz (elaboration) the old sky and the old earth had completely disappeared. The sea also was no longer.</bt><note reference="21:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 65:17, 66:22, 2 Petrus 3:13</note><v n="2" />Ais beta lia Tuhan Allah pung kota barisi, andia Yerusalem Baru, turun datang dari sorga. Itu kota su siap sama ke baroit parampuan yang mau pi sambut dia pung laki.<bt>Then I saw God's holy/clean city, which is New Yerusalem, come down from heaven. That city was prepared the same as a bride who was going to meet her husband.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="the holy city, the new Jerusalem:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">the holy city, the new Jerusalem: Rev. 3:12. adorned: Rev. 21:19, 1 Timothy 2:9.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="21:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 52:1, Dunya Model Baru 3:12, Yesaya 61:10</note><v n="3" />Ais beta dengar satu suara karás datang dari itu korsi parenta, ko bilang,<bt>Then I heard a loud voice come from that ruling chair, to say,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Lia bae-bae!<bt>“Look carefully!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Mulai sakarang, Tuhan Allah pung Ruma ada di manusia pung teng-tenga.<bt>Starting from now God's House is in the midst of humans.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Mulai ini hari, Tuhan su idop sama-sama deng Dia pung orang dong.<bt>Starting from today God lives together with His people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te Dia su jadi dong pung Tuhan Allah.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) He has become their God;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng dong su jadi Dia pung ana-ana dong.<bt>And they have become His children.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nanti Dia ada tarús-tarús deng dong.<bt>Later He will exist continually with them.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng Dia sama-sama deng dong tar abis-abis.<bt>And He will be together with them forever. [NOTE to daughter translations: avoid pos-neg structure that implies God had once abandoned them]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Deng Dia sonde akan kasi tenga"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Deng Dia sonde akan kasi tenga sang dong lai.</Message></Annotation><note reference="21:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 37:27, Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 26:11, 12</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="4" />Nanti Dia hapus kasi karíng dong pung aer mata samua,<bt>Later He will wipe dry all their tears,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko dong sonde manangis makarereu lai.<bt>so they will not cry wailing anymore.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Tagal di situ sonde ada yang saki lai.<bt>Because there there is no one who is sick anymore.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Deng di situ sonde ada yang mati lai.<bt>And there there is no one who dies anymore.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Samua yang bekin susa dari dolu-dolu, su sonde ada lai.<bt>Everything which caused difficulty in those previous times, doesn't exist anymore.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Samua yang bekin sangsara dari dolu-dolu, su ilang buang.&gt;&gt;<bt>Everything which caused suffering in those previous times, has disappeared gone.”</bt><note reference="21:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 25:8, 35:10, 65:19</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ais Dia yang dudu di itu korsi parenta omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Lia bae-bae, te Beta su bekin samua jadi baru.&gt;&gt; Ais Dia omong lai deng beta bilang, &lt;&lt;Tulis su! Samua orang dong bisa parcaya Beta pung Kata-kata ni, te samua ni, memang su batúl!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then He who sat in that ruling chair spoke saying, “Look carefully, cuz (elaboration) I have made everything become new.” Then He spoke again with me saying, “Write! All people can believe these Words of Mine, cuz (elaboration) all of this, is indeed true!” [NOTE to daughter translations: RL's may have to get rid of these two extra quote margins in vs.5-6, They are heavy and probably signal “change of speaker” (which they are not). Check extensively. Problem, the three quote contents have real shifts between them, so if the quote margins are deleted, strong discourse particles indicating the shift may be needed. KM gets away with it on the back of Indonesian, not on its own merits (in my humble opinion).]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ais Dia kasi tau lai sang beta bilang,<bt>Then He told me again saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Samua-samua yang Beta su janji dari dolu tu, su jadi.<bt>“Everything which I have promised from long ago, has happened.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Te Beta ni,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) I am</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Alfa sampe Omega.<bt>Alfa until Omega.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Deng Beta ni,<bt>And I am</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">A sampe Z,<bt>A until Z,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Samua asal dari Beta,<bt>Everything originates from Me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">mulai dari partama sampe abis.<bt>beginning from its beginning until the end.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Samua orang yang aus,<bt>All people who are thirsty,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nanti Beta kasi minum farei-farei,<bt>later I will give [them] to drink without paying</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">dari itu mata aer yang bawa idop, ko biar orang idop batúl.<bt>from that water spring which brings life so that people can truly live. [EXEG: (KT): phrased as in other Johannine writings. Compare with 7:17]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="TERM: Well of the water of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">TERM: Well of the water of life, as in 7:17</Message></Annotation><note reference="21:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 55:1</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="7" />Samua orang yang batahan iko Tuhan pung jalan idop yang lurus,<bt>All people who endure following God's straight way of life,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nanti dong tarima ame ini berkat samua.<bt>later they will receive all this blessing.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Te nanti Beta jadi dong pung Tuhan Allah,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) later I will become their God,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">deng dong jadi Beta pung ana-ana.<bt>and they will become My children.</bt><note reference="21:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Samuel 7:14, Lagu Puji dong 89:26-27</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="8" />Ma ada ju orang yang nanti kaná lempar buang,<bt>But there are also people who will be thrown out/discarded,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">pi dalam itu laut api balerang, yang manyala sonde pake barenti.<bt>into that sulfur sea of fire that burns without ever ending.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Macam ke orang pana'u,<bt>Such as cowards,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">orang yang bale balakang sang Yesus,<bt>people who turn their backs on Yesus,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">orang kamomos,<bt>dirty/defiled people,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">orang maen serong deng orang yang bukan dong pung laki ko dong pung bini,<bt>(sexually) immoral people, [EXEG: (KT): Gk /pornois/ here, so should be same as used for ‘fornication’ elsewhere.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">tukang bunu orang,<bt>murderers,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">tukang songgo-songgo,<bt>habitual false worshipers,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">tukang suanggi,<bt>sorcerers,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">deng tukang putar-balek.<bt>and deceivers.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Nanti dong samua kaná lempar buang pi dalam laut api,<bt>Later they all will be thrown into that sea of fire,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">yang orang bilang, &lt;tampa mati yang kadua.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>which people refer to as ‘the place of second death.’”</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yohanis dapa lia kota Yerusalem model baru<bt>Yohanis gets to see Yerusalem city new style</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Tarús beta dapa lia satu dari itu tuju ana bua dari sorga yang dolu pegang bokor yang ta'isi deng Tuhan pung mara. Dia datang katumu sang beta, ais dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari sini dolo! Te beta ada mau kasi lia sang lu baroit parampuan yang mau kawin deng Domba Ana.&gt;&gt;<bt>Next I saw one of those seven angels who previously was holding the bowls that were filled with God's anger. He came to meet me, then he said, “Come here! I want to show you the bride who wants to marry the Sheep Offspring.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Tarús beta takaná Tuhan pung Roh, ju ana bua satu dari sorga angka bawa sang beta pi satu gunung yang talalu tinggi. Di situ dia kasi tunju sang beta kota Yerusalem, andia Tuhan Allah pung kota barisi yang ada turun datang dari Tuhan di sorga.<bt>Next I was affected by God's Spirit and an angel lifted took me to a very high mountain. There he showed me Yerusalem city, which is that holy city of God's, which was coming down from God2 in heaven.</bt><note reference="21:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 40:2</note><v n="11" />Itu kota talalu bagus! Ada cahaya yang basambar kaluar dari Tuhan Allah pung hebat, sama ke batu intan yang mangkilat. Sampe itu kota samua jadi taráng.<bt>That city is incredibly fine! There is light that strikes out coming from God's awesomeness, like diamonds which are flashing/shiny. To the point that that entire city is lit up. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="yaspis probably clear like diamond"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">yaspis probably clear like diamond</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Ada tembok tinggi bésar kuliling itu kota, deng 12 pintu garbáng. Ada ju 12 ana bua dari sorga yang jaga itu pintu dong. Di itu 12 pintu ada tatulis 12 suku Isra'el pung nama.<bt>There is a tall big wall surrounding that city, with 12 outside doors/gates. There are also 12 angels who guard those doors. On those 12 doors is written the names of the 12 Israel clans. [NOTE to daughter translations: TB has “di atas” which is ambiguous and could be read incorrectly as “above the doors”. While possible, more likely from the whole verse (a gapping construction in the Gk leaning on the vb of the previous clause) is “on the doors”. Just be aware of teams bringing noise from the TB on this.]</bt><note reference="21:12" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Iko orang yang pintar so'al Alkitab, nomer 12 tu, nomer yang kasi tunju nomer manusia langkáp.<bt>According to people who are knowledgeable about the Bible, that number 12, is a number that shows a complete number of humans. [NOTE: manusia yg mengcukupi, enough to be complete, all that is needed, everyone who should be there is]</bt></note><v n="13" />Tiga pintu garbáng mangada pi sablá matahari nae. Tiga mangada pi sablá matahari turun. Tiga mangada pi sablá utara. Deng tiga lai mangada pi sablá salatan.<bt>Three outside doors face to the east side. Three face to the west side. Three face to the north side. And three more face to the south side.</bt><note reference="21:12-13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 48:30-35</note><v n="14" />Itu tembok badiri di atas 12 batu fanderen yang bésar. Di batu satu-satu ada tatulis nama-nama dari Domba Ana pung 12 utusan yang layani sang Dia di dunya.<bt>That wall stands on top of 12 foundation rocks which are big. On each rock is written the names of the Sheep Offspring's 12 apostles who served Him on earth. [EXEG: one name on each stone. See CEV, LN, Hughes.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="12 people &gt; 12 apostles **fixed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">12 people &gt; 12 apostles **fixed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pung 12 utusan yang iko tarús-tarús"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">pung 12 utusan yang iko tarús-tarús sang dia di dunya.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ais, itu ana bua yang omong sang beta, ada pegang ame satu tongkat ukur dari mas, ko mau ukur itu kota deng dia pung pintu garbáng deng dia pung tembok.<bt>Then that angel who spoke to me, was holding a measuring stick from gold, to measure that city and its outer doors and its wall.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="measuring rod: Rev. 11:1."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">measuring rod: Rev. 11:1.</Message></Annotation><note reference="21:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 40:3</note><v n="16" />Dia ukur lebe dolu itu kota pung tembok yang sagí ampa. Dia pung panjang deng lebar deng tinggi samua sama, andia 2.220 kilometer.<bt>He measured first that city's wall which was square. It's length and width and height were all the same, that is 2.220 kilometers.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NOTE: ftn changed from 12 &gt;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">NOTE: ftn changed from 12 &gt; 12.000 stadia. In text, 2.400 &gt; 2.220 following NLT ftn. **fixed</Message></Annotation><note reference="21:16" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, 12.000 <span class="Italic">stadia</span>.<bt>The Yunani language Bible writes saying, 12,000 <span class="Italic">stadia</span>.</bt></note><v n="17" />Ais dia ukur itu tembok pung tabal tu, ada 65 meter, iko manusia pung ukuran.<bt>Then he measured that wall's thickness there, it was 65 meters, according to human's measurements. [EXEG: NLT note + metric equivalent of CEV.]</bt><note reference="21:17" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani tulis di sini bilang, <span class="Italic">&lt;&lt;144 peihon&gt;&gt;.</span> Satu <span class="Italic">peihon</span> tu, sama deng satu hasta. Naa, 12 kali 12, andia 144. Jadi kalo 12 pung arti bilang, langkáp, 144 pung arti, yang paling langkáp.<bt>The Yunani language Bible writes here, saying <span class="Italic">“144 peihon”. </span>One <span class="Italic">peihon</span> is the same as a hasta (Indo: cubit -still commonly used in villages). Naa, 12 times 12 is 144. So (consequently), if 12 means complete, 144 means most complete.</bt></note><v n="18" />Itu tembok, dong bekin dari batu mangkilat, nama <span class="Italic">yaspis. </span>Deng samua yang ada dalam itu kota tu, dong bekin dari mas tulen yang silo sama ke kaca barisi.<bt>That wall, was made from a jewel, named <span class="Italic">yaspis. </span>And all that was in that city, was made from pure gold which is blinding/glares/reflects/shines like clean glass. [EXEG: (Lole 2014): Q: There is a practical problem of trying to visualise gold being clear as glass, even though that is what the Gk says and many English translations say, and TB says. So is there a better solution that is both faithful to the Gk and makes sense in Kupang and related lgs? A: Considerations: Gk words in 21:18 &amp; 21:21 are different. We need to reflect that, even though some English translations (e.g. NLT, CEV) do not preserve the difference. AGNT, NRSV, TB, Uma &amp; Kankanay Back Trans do. Technically we had it framed in Kupang OV as a simile, which allows a bit of slop, but the problem of trying to visualise gold being clear/transparent remains. The obvious calon is /manyala/, but we can't use that in this context, since Kupang UNSs and their Daughter Language equivalents pointed out when discussed, that /manyala/ evokes a glow from an inner source, rather than an external reflection. /bacaya/ and /basinar/ also have similar problems, and have different perspectives. /mangkilat/ is fine in 21:21, and that is also the quality associated with precious stones. •Building on the Gk “pure gold like pure glass”, I suggest we go to /silo/ blinding/glares/reflects/shines like the sun off clean glass or a new roof. I think this is faithful to the Gk and gets the collocations and imagery right.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">***</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-03-28 04:18:02Z">•So /mangkilat/ is fine in 21:21, and that is also the quality associated with precious stones</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mangkilat sama ke kaca."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">mangkilat sama ke kaca.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Itu 12 batu fanderen tu, ada hias deng macam-macam batu mangkilat yang mahal. Yang partama, ada pake batu <span class="Italic">yaspis</span> yang manyala warna ijo. Nomer dua, ada pake batu <span class="Italic">nilam</span> yang manyala warna biru. Nomer tiga, ada pake batu <span class="Italic">mirah</span> yang manyala warna mera. Nomer ampa, ada pake batu <span class="Italic">samrud,</span> yang manyala warna ijo.<bt>Those 12 foundation stones, were adorned with all kinds of jewels which were expensive. That first one, used <span class="Italic">yaspis </span>stone which shone a green colour. Number two, used <span class="Italic">nilam </span>stone which shone a blue colour. Number three, used <span class="Italic">mirah </span>stone which shone a red colour. Number four, used <span class="Italic">samrud </span>stone, which shone a green colour.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">***</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Nomer lima, ada pake batu <span class="Italic">unam</span> yang balapis coklat-puti. Nomer anam, ada pake batu <span class="Italic">sardius,</span> yang manyala warna mera. Nomer tuju, ada pake batu <span class="Italic">ratna cempaka,</span> yang manyala warna kuning mas. Nomer dalapan, ada pake batu <span class="Italic">beril,</span> yang manyala warna biru-ijo. Nomer sambilan, pake batu <span class="Italic">krisolit,</span> yang manyala warna kuning-kuning. Nomer sapulu, ada pake batu <span class="Italic">krisopras,</span> yang manyala warna ijo muda. Nomer sablás, ada pake batu <span class="Italic">lasuardi,</span> yang manyala warna biru laut. Deng nomer dua blas, ada pake batu <span class="Italic">kecubung,</span> yang manyala warna ungu.<bt>Number five, used <span class="Italic">unam </span>stone which was layered brown and white. Number six, used sardius stone, which shone a red colour. Number seven, used <span class="Italic">ratna cempaka</span> stone, which shone a gold yellow colour. Number eight, used <span class="Italic">beril </span>stone, which shone a blue-green colour. Number nine, used <span class="Italic">krisolit </span>stone, which shone a yellowish colour. Number ten, used <span class="Italic">krisopras </span>stone, which shone a light green colour. Number eleven, used <span class="Italic">lasuardi </span>stone, which shown a sea blue colour. And number twelve, used <span class="Italic">kecubung </span>stone, which shone a purple colour. [EXEG: see Martins article.] [NOTE: TB stuffed up the names here, mismatching the Gk (Gk chrysolite is seventh, but in TB it is ninth), but just go with it.]</bt><v n="21" />Deng itu 12 pintu garbáng tu, bekin dari mutiara 12 biji. Satu pintu bekin dari mutiara satu biji. Deng itu kota pung istarát, dong bekin dari mas tulen yang mangkilat sama ke kaca.<bt>And those 12 aforementioned gates, were made of 12 pearls. One door was made from one pearl. And that city's streets, were made from pure gold that shone like glass. [EXEG: Gk word for “clear as glass” in 18 is different from the word here. Here it must be something that gold can do.]</bt><note reference="21:18-21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 54:11-12</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ma beta lia, sonde ada ruma sambayang di itu kota. Tagal Tuhan Allah yang paling kuasa deng itu Domba Ana ada di situ tarús-tarús. Andia ko orang dong langsung pi sémba sang Dong.<bt>But I saw, there wasn't a worship house in that city. Because God who has the most power/authority and that Sheep Offspring are there continually. That's why people go straight to worship Them.</bt><v n="23" />Itu kota ju sonde parlú matahari deng bulan ko bekin taráng sang dia, tagal Tuhan Allah pung cahaya yang bekin taráng di situ. Deng itu Domba Ana su jadi sama ke lampu yang manyala.<bt>That city also does not need the sun and moon to make it light, because God's radiance has made light there. [EXEG: Gk: glory here] And that Sheep Offspring has become like a lamp which shines.</bt><note reference="21:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 60:19-20</note><v n="24" />Orang dari samua suku-bangsa di dunya nanti datang bajalan di itu taráng. Raja-raja di bumi ju bawa datang dong pung harta yang hebat pi situ.<bt>People from every nation in the world later will come and walk in that light. Kings on earth will also come bringing their incredible wealth there.</bt><note reference="21:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 60:3</note><v n="25" />Di situ sonde ada malam lai. Andia ko dong sonde parlú tutu pintu maso kota.<bt>There there is no night. That's why they don't need to close city gates/doors.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***doors &gt; city gates, Sept 2005"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">***doors &gt; city gates, Sept 2005</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Nanti dong ju bawa maso pi dalam itu kota, samua yang bae deng samua hormat dari samua negara di bumi.<bt>Later they will bring into that city, everything that is good and all honour from all the nations on earth. [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="yang hebat &gt; hormat **fixed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">yang hebat &gt; hormat **fixed</Message></Annotation><note reference="21:25-26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 60:11</note><v n="27" />Ma yang sonde bole maso pi situ, andia samua yang jahat, tingka ke tukang songgo-songgo, tukang maen serong, deng tukang putar-balek dong. Yang bole maso, andia cuma orang yang dong pung nama ada tatulis di itu Domba Ana pung tulisan yang daftar nama dari orang yang idop tarús-tarús deng Tuhan Allah.<bt>But those who cannot enter that city, are all who are evil, such as people who follow traditional worship, people who habitually play off-track (sexually), and liars/deceivers. Those who can enter, are only people whose names are written in that Sheep Offspring's writing which has listed names of the people who live continually with God.</bt><note reference="21:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 52:1, Yeskial 44:9</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kali yang ada pung aer yang bawa idop, deng pohon yang bawa idop [\s2]<bt>A/the river which has water that brings life, and the tree that brings life [\s2] [NOTE to daughter translations: ALT: The water and tree that bring life]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="22" />
      <v n="1" />Ais ju itu ana bua dari sorga kasi tunju sang beta kali satu, yang dia pung aer bawa idop. Itu aer jarní sama ke kaca. Dia malele kaluar dari Tuhan Allah deng itu Domba Ana pung korsi parenta.<bt>Then that angel showed me a river, whose water brings life. That water was clear like glass. It flowed out from God and that Sheep Offspring's ruling chair.</bt><note reference="22:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeskial 47:1, Sakaria 14:8</note><v n="2" />Tarús dia malele pi tenga istarát bésar di itu kota. Di itu kali pung sablá-sablá, ada satu pohon yang bawa idop. Itu pohon babua satu taon, 12 kali; satu bulan, satu kali. Dia pung daon bisa jadi obat ko bekin bae suku-bangsa di bumi.<bt>Next it flowed in the middle of the big street in that city. On that river's sides, there was a tree that brings life. Thàt tree bore fruit in one year, 12 times; one month, one time. It's leaves could be/become medicine to heal the nations on earth.</bt><note reference="22:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 2:9</note><v n="3" />Ma samua yang Tuhan Allah parná tola deng kasi kutuk dong, sonde ada di itu kota. Yang ada, andia Tuhan Allah deng Domba Ana yang dudu parenta di Dong pung korsi parenta, deng Dong pung orang suru-suru yang sémba sang Dong.<bt>But all that God ever refused/rejected and cursed, they are not in that city. Those who are there, are God and the Sheep Offspring who sit ruling on Their ruling chairs, and Their servants who worship Them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="TERM: katathema 'curse'."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">TERM: katathema 'curse'.</Message></Annotation><note reference="22:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Sakaria 14:11</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Dong samua bisa dapa lia Tuhan Allah pung muka. Deng Tuhan pung nama ada tatulis di dong pung testa.<bt>They all can see God's face. And the Lord's name is written on their forehead.</bt><v n="5" />Di situ, sonde ada malam. Jadi Tuhan pung orang dong su sonde parlú matahari ko, lampu ko, tagal Tuhan Allah sandiri yang bekin taráng itu kota. Nanti dong iko pegang parenta di situ sampe salamanya.<bt>There, there is no night. So God's people don't need the sun or, lamps or (whatever), because God himself is the one who makes that city light. Later they will rule there forever.</bt><note reference="22:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 60:19, Daniel 7:18</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus tutu Dia pung pasán<bt>The Lord Yesus closes His requests</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ais, itu ana bua kasi tau sang beta bilang, &lt;&lt;Samua yang beta su kasi tau sang lu ni, memang batúl. Samua orang bisa parcaya beta pung omong ni. Dolu Tuhan Allah pake Dia pung Roh ko kasi tau Dia pung Kata-kata sang dia pung jubir dong. Ma sakarang, Dia su pake Dia pung ana bua dari sorga ko kasi tau Dia pung ana-ana dong so'al ini hal samua yang sonde lama lai musti jadi.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then that angel told me saying, “All that I have told you here, is certainly true. All people can believe that speaking of mine. Previously God used His Words to tell His spokespersons. But now He has sent His angel to tell His children about all these things which must soon happen.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Rev. 19:10."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Rev. 19:10.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ais itu, Yesus omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Inga, é! Sonde lama lai, te Beta su datang. Di ini tulisan su tatulis samua, so'al apa yang nanti jadi. Samua orang yang iko ini tulisan pung kata-kata dong, nanti dong yang paling ontong.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yesus spoke saying, “Listen, é! Not much longer (=soon), I will have come. In this writing everything has been written, about what will happen. All people who follow this writings words, later they will be most fortunate.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Yang tulis ini tulisan ni, andia beta, Yohanis. Beta ni, yang su dengar deng su lia ini hal dong samua. Dengar abis ju, beta jato tikam lutut ko sémba di itu ana bua dari sorga pung kaki. Te dia yang su kasi tunju ini hal samua sang beta.<bt>The one who writes this writing, is me, Yohanis. I here, am the one who has heard and seen all these things. After hearing them, I fell kneeling to worship at the feet of that angel. Cuz (elaboration) he is the one who showed all these things to me. [NOTE to daughter translations: not worship the angel, but worship before his feet; remember earlier when John tried to worship the angel it was rejected as improper, as in vs 9 below.]</bt><v n="9" />Ma dia togor sang beta bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh! Lu jang bekin bagitu! Lu musti sémba sang Tuhan Allah sa. Jang sémba sang beta. Te beta ju Tuhan pung orang suru-suru sama ke lu, deng lu pung sodara dong yang su jadi Dia pung jubir, deng samua orang laen dong yang bekin iko apa yang ada tatulis dalam ini tulisan.<bt>But he forbade me saying, “Hee [+protest]! You don't do like that! Don't worship me. But you must worship only God. Cuz (elaboration) I also am God's servant the same as you, and your siblings who have become His spokespersons, and all the other people who have done according to what is written in this writing.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Rev. 19:10."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Rev. 19:10.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Lu jang sambunyi ini tulisan pung isi dari orang laen. Te sonde lama lai, samua yang su tatulis dalam ini tulisan, pasti jadi.<bt>You don't hide this writing's contents from other people. Cuz (elaboration) not much longer, everything which is written in this writing, surely will have happened. [DISCOURSE: do not put quote margin here. There is no shift of speaker or audience.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="11" />Samua orang yang bekin kamomos, na,<bt>All people who do dirty/defiling things, na,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">kasi tenga pi ko dong maen bekin kamomos tarús.<bt>just leave them so they just keep on doing evil.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ma samua yang idop barisi,<bt>But all who live holy,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dong musti idop barisi tarús.<bt>they must keep on living holy.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Samua orang yang bekin jahat,<bt>All people who do evil,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">kasi tenga pi ko dong maen bekin jahat tarús.<bt>just let them go on doing evil continually.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ma samua yang bekin bae,<bt>But everyone who does good/well</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dong musti bekin yang bae tarús.&gt;&gt;<bt>must continue doing good.”</bt><note reference="22:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 12:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ais itu, Yesus omong ulang lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Inga bae-bae! Te sonde lama lai, Beta su datang. Nanti Beta balas kasi samua orang, iko apa yang dong su bekin.<bt>After that, Yesus spoke again saying, “Remember well! Cuz (elaboration) not much longer, I will come. I will repay/reciprocate to each person, according to what they have done.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Rev. 11:8, 18:6, 2:23, 20:12,13."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Rev. 11:8, 18:6, 2:23, 20:12,13.</Message></Annotation><note reference="22:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 40:10, 62:11, Lagu Puji dong 28:4, Yeremia 17:10</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="13" />Beta ni,<bt>I am</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Alfa sampe Omega.<bt>Alfa until Omega.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Beta ni,<bt>I am</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">A sampe Z.<bt>A until Z.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Samua-samua asal dari Beta,<bt>Everything originates from Me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">mulai dari partama sampe abis.<bt>beginning from it's beginning until the end.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="TERM: First and last: Rev. 1:8,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">TERM: First and last: Rev. 1:8, 17, 18, 2:8, 21:6. Phrased a little bit different each time.</Message></Annotation><note reference="22:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dunya Model Baru 1:8, Yesaya 44:6, 48:12, Dunya Model Baru 1:17, 2:8</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="14" />Orang-orang yang su cuci kasi barisi dong pung pakean, dong yang ontong.<bt>The people who have washed clean those clothes of theirs, they are the ones who are fortunate. [EXEG: Gk /makarioi/, handle like Mat. 5 &amp; Luk 6.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te nanti dong dapa hak ko maso iko pintu garbáng pi dalam itu kota.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) later they will have the right to enter those gates going into that city.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Orang-orang yang su idop barisi, dong yang ontong.<bt>Those people who live holy, they are the ones who are fortunate.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Te nanti dong dapa isin ko makan itu bua yang bekin orang idop tarús-tarús.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) later they will be given permission to eat that fruit which makes people live forever.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Rev. 7:14, 22:2."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Rev. 7:14, 22:2.</Message></Annotation><note reference="22:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 2:9, 3:22</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="15" />Ma orang laen, sonde bole maso di situ.<bt>But other people, may not enter there.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Yang bukan Tuhan pung orang, sonde bole tenga di situ.<bt>Those who are not God's people, may not stay/live there.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Andia, orang yang sonde parcaya sang Tuhan,<bt>That is, people who don't believe in God, [EXEG: Gk “dogs”. See ftn.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Gk: dogs"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">Gk: dogs</Message></Annotation><note reference="22:15" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;anjing&gt;&gt;. Orang Yahudi suka pake kata &lt;&lt;anjing&gt;&gt; ko jadi kiasan yang kasi tunju orang bukan Yahudi, andia orang laen dong &lt;&lt;yang sonde parcaya sang Tuhan&gt;&gt;. Dalam ini ayat ni, Yohanis omong so'al kalompok macam-macam yang sonde jadi maso sorga. Yang partama, andia, &lt;&lt;orang yang sonde parcaya sang Tuhan&gt;&gt;. Ini bukan parkara so'al anjing maso sorga, ko sonde.<bt>The Yunani language Bible writes saying, “dogs”. Yahudi people often used the word “dog” as a figurative way to refer to non-Yahudi people, that is other (category) people “who don't believe in God2”. In this verse, Yohanis is speaking about various groups who won't be able to get into heaven. The first/foremost is “people who don't believe in God2”. This is not a dispute over whether dogs can get into heaven, or not.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tukang maen serong, tukang songgo-songgo,<bt>(sexually) immoral people, habitual worshipers of idols,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tukang bunu orang, tukang suanggi,<bt>murderers, sorcerers,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng tukang putar-balek.<bt>and habitual liars/deceivers.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dong samua tu, sonde bole maso.<bt>All those aforementioned, may not enter.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dong samua tu, kasi tenga pi, di luar sa.<bt>All those aforementioned, are just left outside.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Rev. 21:8."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Rev. 21:8.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Beta ni, Yesus. Beta yang kirim datang Beta pung ana bua dari sorga ko buka ini hal samua, ko bosong nanti pi kasi tau Beta pung pasán sang itu tuju jama'at dong.<bt>I am Yesus. I am the one who sent My angel from heaven to reveal/open these things, so that you later go tell My instructions/message/requests to those seven congregations.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="to those seven churches KM high"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">to those seven churches KM high level discourse; ***adjusted Sept 2005</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Beta ni, raja Daud pung turunan.<bt>I am raja Daud's descendant.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Beta ni, Raja yang pegang parenta.<bt>I am the Raja who rules/governs.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Beta pung cahaya, taráng mau mati,<bt>My radiance is extremely bright,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sama ke bintang timur.<bt>like the east star.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Beta pung sinar talalu tajam,<bt>My rays are very sharp (=strong),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sama ke bintang fajar.&gt;&gt;<bt>like the almost daylight star.” [NOTE to daughter translations: These 2 stars need to be understood to be the same.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Morning Star: seems to refer to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Morning Star: seems to refer to the Messiah, Numbers 24:17, Rev. 2:28.</Message></Annotation><note reference="22:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 11:1, 10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Tuhan Allah pung Roh ada undang bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari sini su!&gt;&gt;<bt>God's Spirit is inviting saying, “Come here!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Itu baroit parampuan ju pange bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari datang su!&gt;&gt;<bt>That bride also calls out saying, “Come on!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Biar ko samua yang dengar ju iko bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari su!&gt;&gt;<bt>Let all who hear also follow saying, “Come on!”</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Biar ko samua yang aus, datang ko minum su!<bt>Let everyone who is thirsty, come and drink!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Biar ko samua yang mau minum itu aer yang bawa idop,<bt>Let everyone who wants to drink that water that brings life,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">na, mari ame su!<bt>na, come and get it!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Orang bole ame itu aer<bt>People can take that water</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng farei-farei.<bt>unimpeded/without cost/free.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Orang bole minum itu aer<bt>People can drink that water</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng sonde pake bayar.<bt>with out paying.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="The bride: Christ's people: Rev. 19:7."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">The bride: Christ's people: Rev. 19:7.</Message></Annotation><note reference="22:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 55:1</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yohanis pung pasán tarahir<bt>Yohanis' final request/instruction/message</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Beta, Yohanis ni, kasi inga samua orang yang nanti dengar apa yang Tuhan Allah su buka memang kasi sang beta di ini tulisan, bagini: kalo ada orang yang tamba apa-apa lai di ini tulisan, nanti Tuhan Allah hukum tamba sang dia deng itu tuju calaka yang Dia po'a pi bumi.<bt>I, Yohanis here, want to remind/warn all people who will hear what God has revealed beforehand to me in this writing, like this: if there is a person who adds anything more to this writing, later God will add a punishment to him of those seven aforementioned catastrophes which He poured out on the earth.</bt><v n="19" />Deng kalo ada orang yang kasi kurang apa-apa lai dari ini tulisan, nanti Tuhan Allah cabu buang dia pung hak ko dia jang maso pi dalam kota barisi, deng dia jang makan itu bua yang bekin orang idop tarús-tarús.<bt>And if there is a person who takes away anything more from this writing, later God will yank away his right so that he can't enter that holy city, and he can't eat that fruit which makes people live forever.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Their share: rev. 20:6, 21:8."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z" status="Information">Their share: rev. 20:6, 21:8.</Message></Annotation><note reference="22:18-19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 4:2, 12:32</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Yesus sandiri yang su buka kasi lia ini hal samua. Dia su janji bilang, &lt;&lt;Itu batúl! Sonde lama lai, te Beta su mau datang.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus himself is the one who has open/revealed shown these things. He has promised saying. “It's true! Not much longer, cuz (elaboration) I have come.”</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Naa, Tuhan Yesus, datang su!<bt>Naa, [+shift] Lord Yesus come on!</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Beta minta ko Tuhan Yesus kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang Dia pung orang dong samua. Amin!<bt>I request the Lord Yesus to show His grace/goodness/ generosity to all of His people. Amin!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="changed to &quot;grace&quot; **fixed Sept 2005"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:10:06Z">changed to "grace" **fixed Sept 2005</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dari beta,<bt>From me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yohanis<bt>Yohanis</bt></p>
  </book>
</bible>